\mt1 Numbers
\is1 Introduction
\ip The English word вҖҳNumbersвҖҷ relates to the census of Israeli fighting men. Hebrew readers call this document вҖҳBemidbarвҖҷ which is the fourth word in the Hebrew and means вҖҳIn the wildernessвҖҷ. Some European and other translations call it вҖҳThe fourth book of Mosheh/MosesвҖҷ.
\ip This document tells about the descendants of Yisrael (called вҖҳIsraelвҖҷ in older translations) inside of forty years from removal their of Mt. Sinai, until arrived them there to east of land promised of God to give them. The name of this document, there is/are kalabetan of very important part of this account is the listing of Mosheh of descendants of Israel there to Mt. Sinai of not yet them left there. вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ of forty years, made e again the listing there to Moab, direction of east of River Jordan. Te middle of this the twice listing of people, went the descendants of Israel of Kadesh-Barnea of south boundary of Kanaan. But from Kadesh-Barnea, not/none them entered of land promised of God to give them. вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ of many years of living their of that place, went them of land direction of east of River Jordan. The one group of people Lived there, and the other crossed of River Jordan going to Kanaan.
\ip The вҖҳNumbersвҖҷ document tells again concerning the people always naawei of looking forward to, afraid middle of difficulty, and migsukul of God and to Moses chosen by God so that is to lead them. telling again this concerning the pegkamatinumanen of God and of pegsagman he/his of his people without ending even still nenaawaan them of looking forward to, and disobedient. telling again this concerning the not ending serving Moses of God and of his people even still of there is/are times he's lacking humility.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The Israelis prepare to depart from Sinai \ior 1:1вҖ“9:23\ior*
\io2 a. The first listing of Mosheh Yisrael's descendants \ior 1:1вҖ“4:49\ior*
\io2 b. The various laws and beliefs \ior 5:1вҖ“8:26\ior*
\io2 c. The second Festival of вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ of Messenger \ior 9:1-23\ior*
\io1 From Mt. Sinai to Moav \ior 10:1вҖ“21:35\ior*
\io1 The events in Moav \ior 22:1вҖ“32:42\ior*
\io1 The places passed through by descendants of Israel \ior 33:1-49\ior*
\io1 Warnings before crossing the Yarden river \ior 33:50вҖ“36:13\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 The first census of the Israelis by Mosheh
\rem /s1 The First Census of Israel; The Census; Israel's First Census; Israel in the wilderness of Sinai
\p
\v 1 In April of the yearВҰ61073 afterВҰ61075 the Israeli people \add вүҲescaped from\add* EgyptВҰ61077 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*, YahwehВҰ61062 spokeВҰ61061 to MoshehВҰ61065 \add (MosesВҰ61065)\add* in the SinaiВҰ61067 wildernessВҰ61066 in the \add вүҲsacredВҰ61068\add* tent, saying,\x + \xo 1:1-46: \xt Num 26:1-51.\x*
\v 2 вҖң\add вүҲCount all the men who are Yisrael's descendants by their clansВҰ61090 and families, being sure to list all their namesВҰ61094\add*.
\v 3 \add Only include those\add* who are twentyВҰ61101 or older and able \add to be recruited\add* as soldiers. You and Aharon must enrolВҰ61109 them into militaryВҰ61111 divisionsВҰ61111.
\v 4 \add вүҲThe leader of each tribeВҰ61119 will accompany\add* you.
\p
\v 5 These are the namesВҰ61128 of the menВҰ61129 who will \add вүҲassist\add* you:
\li1 ElitsurВҰ61134 (Shedeyur's son) from Reuven,
\li1
\v 6 ShelumielВҰ61140 (Tsuri-Shaddai'sВҰ61143 son) from Shimeon \add (Simeon)\add*,
\li1
\v 7 NahshonВҰ61146 (Amminadav's son) from Yehudah \add (Judah)\add*,
\li1
\v 8 NetanelВҰ61152 (Tsuar'sВҰ61155 son) from Yissakar \add (Issachar)\add*,
\li1
\v 9 Eliav (Helon'sВҰ61161 son) from Zevulun,
\li1
\v 10 Elishama (Ammihud'sВҰ61169 son) from Yosef'sВҰ61164 son Efrayim,
\li1 Gamliel (Pedahtsur's son) from Yosef's son Menashsheh \add (ManassehВҰ61170)\add*,
\li1
\v 11 Avidan (Gideoni's son) from Benyamin,
\li1
\v 12 AhiezerВҰ61183 (Ammishaddai'sВҰ61186 son) from Dan,
\li1
\v 13 PagielВҰ61189 (Okran's son) from Asher,
\li1
\v 14 Elyasaf (Reuel'sВҰ61198 son) from Gad,
\li1
\v 15 AhiraВҰ61201 (Enan'sВҰ61204 son) from Naftali.
\v 16 TheyВҰ61215 were the leaders of their tribesВҰ61211вҖ”chosen out of their communitiesВҰ61209, and leaders of \add units of\add* one thousand \add soldiers\add*.
\p
\v 17 MoshehВҰ61219 andВҰ61220 AharonВҰ61220 tookВҰ61218 those menВҰ61222 whose names had been \add вүҲgiven\add*
\v 18 andВҰ61228 they assembled the entireВҰ61229 communityВҰ61231 that April. \add вүҲFor each tribe,\add* they recorded theirВҰ61248 ancestryВҰ61241 by clan, counting the namesВҰ61243 of those men who were twentyВҰ61245 or over,
\v 19 just as YahwehВҰ61252 had commandedВҰ61251 MoshehВҰ61255. \add вүҲSo\add* heВҰ61251 countedВҰ61256 them \add there\add* in the SinaiВҰ61258 wildernessВҰ61257,
\v 20-21 individually counting those \add in each tribe below\add* by theirВҰ61273 clan, and only including males who were twentyВҰ61278 or older and able to fight in battle:
\li1 46,500 men from the tribe of Reuven,
\li1
\v 22-23 59,300 men from the tribe of Shimeon \add (SimeonВҰ61296)\add*,
\li1
\v 24-25 45,560 men from the tribe of GadВҰ61327,
\li1
\v 26-27 74,600 men from the tribe of YehudahВҰ61354 \add (Judah)\add*,
\li1
\v 28-29 54,400 men from the tribe of Yissakar \add (IssacharВҰ61380)\add*,
\li1
\v 30-31 57,400 men from the tribe of ZevulunВҰ61406,
\li1
\v 32-33 40,500 men from the tribe of EfrayimВҰ61434,
\li1
\v 34-35 32,200 men from the tribe of Menashsheh \add (ManassehВҰ61459)\add*,
\li1
\v 36-37 35,400 men from the tribe of BenyaminВҰ61484,
\li1
\v 38-39 62,700 men from the tribe of DanВҰ61510,
\li1
\v 40-41 41,500 men from the tribe of AsherВҰ61536,
\li1
\v 42-43 53,400 men from the tribe of NaftaliВҰ61562.
\p
\v 44 Those were the ones that MoshehВҰ61591 and Aharon and the twelve IsraeliВҰ61593 leadersВҰ61593 (one from each tribe) listed.
\v 45 They were all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ61609\add* who were counted according to theirВҰ61614 \add вүҲancestryВҰ61614\add*, being men who were twentyВҰ61616 or older, andВҰ61618 \add вүҲcapable of going off to battle\add*вҖ”
\v 46 603,550 of them in total.
\v 47 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the Levites \add вүҲweren't listed along with the other tribesВҰ61640\add*
\v 48 \add вүҲbecause\add* YahwehВҰ61648 had told MoshehВҰ61651,
\v 49 вҖңDon't list the Levites \add вүҲor count them with the other IsraelisВҰ61667\add*.
\v 50 \add вүҲInstead,\add* appointВҰ61671 \add *them\add* to manage the tentВҰ61677 \add вүҲwhere the copy of the agreement is kept\add*, along with all itsВҰ61700 equipment. They must serve inside it as \add required\add*, andВҰ61670 they should \add вүҲset their tents up aroundВҰ61701 it\add*.
\v 51 \add вүҲWhenВҰ61714 it's time to leave that place\add*, the LevitesВҰ61709 must takeВҰ61707 \add @the tentВҰ61706\add* down andВҰ61705 when camp \add вүҲis set up\add*, they must erect it \add again\add*, \add вүҲbut\add* any stranger who approaches it must be \add вүҲexecuted\add*.
\v 52 \add WhenВҰ61721\add* the \add other\add* \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ61720\add* set up camp, each manВҰ61726 must set up with his army divisionВҰ61730 by theirВҰ61730 banner,
\v 53 \add вүҲbut\add* the LevitesВҰ61747 will camp there aroundВҰ61734 the \add вүҲsacred tentВҰ61735\add* andВҰ61732 look after itВҰ61739. \add вүҲThat way,\add* the IsraeliВҰ61744 community won'tВҰ61737 make \add Yahweh\add* angry.
\v 54 \add вүҲSoВҰ61754 the IsraelisВҰ61756 did everything\add* that YahwehВҰ61760 had instructedВҰ61759 MoshehВҰ61763.
\c 2
\s1 Camp layout by tribe
\rem /s1 The Arrangement of the Tribal Camps; The Arrangement of the Tribes in Camp; The Order of Encampment and Marching; Organization for Israel's Camp
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ61769 told MoshehВҰ61772 and Aharon:
\p
\v 2 вҖңThe \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ61787\add* must camp \add вүҲwith each family joining theirВҰ61784 tribe\add*, \add вүҲwhich will be displaying its\add* bannerВҰ61782. They must camp aroundВҰ61789 the \add вүҲsacredВҰ61790 tent but\add* at a distanceВҰ61788.
\p
\v 3 On the easternВҰ61796 side facing the sunriseВҰ61797 will be Yehudah'sВҰ61800 \add (Judah's)\add* banner andВҰ61802 theirВҰ61801 army divisionsВҰ61801, led by Amminadav's son NahshonВҰ61805
\v 4 with 74,600 in his divisionВҰ61810.
\v 5 The tribeВҰ61820 of Yissakar \add (IssacharВҰ61821)\add* will \add вүҲset up\add* next to them, led by Tsuar'sВҰ61828 son NetanelВҰ61825,
\v 6 with 54,400 in his divisionВҰ61830.
\v 7 Then the tribeВҰ61839 of Zevulun, led by Helon'sВҰ61847 son Eliav,
\v 8 with 57,400 in his divisionВҰ61849.
\v 9 The total number in the divisionsВҰ61872 in the YehudahВҰ61861 camp is 186,400, and \add вүҲwhen travelling\add*, \add вүҲthey'll all go at the front\add*.
\p
\v 10 On the southernВҰ61880 side \add of the sacred tent\add* will be Reuven's banner, led by Shedeyur's son Elitsur
\v 11 with 46,500 in his divisionВҰ61890.
\v 12 The tribeВҰ61900 of Shimeon \add (SimeonВҰ61901)\add* will \add вүҲset up\add* next to them, led by Tsuri-Shaddai's son ShelumielВҰ61905
\v 13 with 59,300 in his divisionВҰ61912.
\v 14 ThenВҰ61920 the tribeВҰ61920 of GadВҰ61921, led by Reuel'sВҰ61928 son Elyasaf.
\v 15 with 45,650 in his divisionВҰ61930.
\v 16 The total number in the divisionsВҰ61953 in the Reuven camp is 151,450, and \add вүҲwhen travelling\add*, \add вүҲthey'll all go secondВҰ61954\add*.
\p
\v 17 Then the LevitesВҰ61963 will go next with theirВҰ61974 own banners in the order that they were camped, \add carrying\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ61959 tent\add*.
\p
\v 18 On the western side \add of the sacred tent\add* will be Efrayim's banner, led by Ammihud'sВҰ61988 son Elishama
\v 19 with 40,500 in his divisionВҰ61990.
\v 20 The tribeВҰ61998 of Menashsheh \add (ManassehВҰ61999)\add* will \add вүҲset up\add* next to them, led by Pedahtsur's son Gamliel
\v 21 with 32,200 in his divisionВҰ62008.
\v 22 ThenВҰ62015 the tribeВҰ62015 of BenyaminВҰ62016 led by Gideoni's son Avidan
\v 23 with 35,400 in his divisionВҰ62025.
\v 24 The total number in the divisionsВҰ62044 in the Efrayim camp is 108,100, and \add вүҲwhen travelling\add*, \add вүҲthey'll all go thirdВҰ62045\add*.
\p
\v 25 OnВҰ62056 the northernВҰ62052 side \add of the sacred tent\add* will be Dan'sВҰ62051 banner, led by Ammishaddai'sВҰ62060 son AhiezerВҰ62057
\v 26 with 62,700 in his divisionВҰ62062.
\v 27 The tribeВҰ62072 of Ahser will \add вүҲset up\add* next to them, led by Okran's son PagielВҰ62077
\v 28 with 41,500 in his divisionВҰ62082.
\v 29 ThenВҰ62090 the tribeВҰ62090 of NaftaliВҰ62091 led by Enan'sВҰ62098 son AhiraВҰ62095
\v 30 with 53,400 in his divisionВҰ62100.
\v 31 The total number in the divisions in the DanВҰ62112 camp is 157,600, and \add вүҲwhen travelling\add*, \add вүҲthey'll all go last\add* with theirВҰ62122 banners.
\p
\v 32 ThoseВҰ62129 are the listed \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ62127 by their ancestralВҰ62131 tribes\add* \add вүҲwith a total of 603,500 fighting men\add*.
\v 33 However, \add вүҲfollowing\add* Yahweh's instructions, the Levites weren't listed among them.
\p
\v 34 \add вүҲSoВҰ62160\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ62162\add* did everythingВҰ62163 that YahwehВҰ62167 commandedВҰ62166 MoshehВҰ62170. They campedВҰ62173 under their banners, and \add вүҲtravelled grouped in their tribes and clans\add*.
\c 3
\s1 Aharon's sons
\rem /s1 The Levites; The Sons of Aaron; Levites Appointed for Service; Aaron's Sons
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲThe following\add* are the descendantsВҰ62185 of Aharon \add (AaronВҰ62186)\add* andВҰ62187 Mosheh as on the dayВҰ62188 when YahwehВҰ62190 spokeВҰ62189 with Mosheh on Mt. SinaiВҰ62195:
\v 2 Aharon's sonsВҰ62199 were: Nadav (the oldest), Avihu, EleazarВҰ62206, andВҰ62197 ItamarВҰ62207.\x + \xo 3:2: \xt Num 26:60.\x*
\v 3 TheyВҰ62212 were \add all\add* anointedВҰ62214 as priests and \add вүҲservedВҰ62219 in that role\add*,
\v 4 \add вүҲexcept that\add* Nadav and Avihu diedВҰ62221 \add вүҲin front\add* of YahwehВҰ62225 when they offeredВҰ62226 \add вүҲunacceptable\add* fireВҰ62227 to \add *him\add* in the SinaiВҰ62232 wildernessВҰ62231, and \add so\add* they had no sons. \add вүҲSoВҰ62221\add* EleazarВҰ62239 and ItamarВҰ62240 servedВҰ62238 as priestsВҰ62238 \add вүҲalongside\add* theirВҰ62245 fatherВҰ62245 Aharon.\x + \xo 3:4: \xt Lev 10:1-2; Num 26:61.\x*
\s1 The Levites as ransom for their sons
\rem /s1 The Duties of the Levites; The Levites Are Appointed to Serve the Priests
\p
\v 5 Then YahwehВҰ62249 told MoshehВҰ62252,
\v 6 вҖңSummon the Levites to come and stand in frontВҰ62262 of Aharon the priestВҰ62264, so they can assistВҰ62265 him.
\v 7 They must performВҰ62268 dutiesВҰ62271 for himВҰ62271 and for the entireВҰ62275 communityВҰ62277 at and around the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62285 tentВҰ62285\add*,
\v 8 including looking after all of its equipment andВҰ62295 \add вүҲfulfilling the obligations\add* of the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ62299\add*.
\v 9 You must assign the LevitesВҰ62309 to AharonвҖ”out of all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ62317\add* it's them who are assigned \add to serve the priests\add*.
\v 10 Appoint Aharon and his sonsВҰ62325 as priests and to preserve the priesthood. Any other person \add вүҲwho tries to act as a priest\add* \add вүҲmust be executed\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 Then YahwehВҰ62337 told MoshehВҰ62340,
\v 12 вҖңOut of all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ62350\add*, I've takenВҰ62345 the Levites instead of the \add вүҲoldest son from everyВҰ62353 family\add*. The Levites \add вүҲwill be the ransom for those sonsВҰ62358\add*, andВҰ62360 so theyВҰ62360 belong to me,
\v 13 because every firstborn male person and animal is set aside as belongingВҰ62387 to me ever since I killed those firstborn males in EgyptВҰ62375. I am YahwehВҰ62389.вҖқ
\s1 The census of the Levites
\rem /s1 A Census of the Levites; The Census of the Levites
\p
\v 14 Then in the SinaiВҰ62398 wildernessВҰ62397, YahwehВҰ62393 told MoshehВҰ62396,
\v 15 вҖңList all the maleВҰ62411 Levites that are at least one monthВҰ62414 old. Count them by their families and clansВҰ62408.вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ62418\add* MoshehВҰ62420 listed them exactly as YahwehВҰ62424 had commandedВҰ62426 him to,
\v 17 and theseВҰ62430 were Levi'sВҰ62433 sonsВҰ62431: GershonВҰ62435, KohatВҰ62436, and MerariВҰ62437.
\v 18 Gershon'sВҰ62443 sonsВҰ62441 were: LivniВҰ62445 andВҰ62446 ShimeiВҰ62446.
\v 19 Kohat'sВҰ62449 sonsВҰ62448 were: Amaran, Yitshar, Hevron, andВҰ62448 Uzziyel.
\v 20 Merari'sВҰ62457 sonsВҰ62456 were MahliВҰ62459 andВҰ62456 MushiВҰ62460.
\m Those were the families of the LevitesВҰ62464 by their clans.
\p
\v 21 Gershon's descendants were the Livnites andВҰ62471 the Shimites, so theyВҰ62474 made up the Gershonites.
\v 22 They had 7,500 males that were at least a monthВҰ62485 old.
\v 23 The Gershonite clansВҰ62493 were to camp on the western side of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62496 tentВҰ62496\add*,
\v 24 andВҰ62500 \add *their\add* leaderВҰ62500 was Lael'sВҰ62508 son Elyasaf.
\v 25 Gershon'sВҰ62513 descendantsВҰ62511 were responsibleВҰ62510 for the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62516 tentВҰ62516\add*, including itsВҰ62518 coveringВҰ62518 andВҰ62510 the entranceВҰ62520 curtain,
\v 26 the courtyard curtains, andВҰ62524 the courtyard entranceВҰ62529 curtain, thatВҰ62531 surrounded \add *it\add*. Also the ropesВҰ62540 \add вүҲused to hold them\add*.
\p
\v 27 Kohat's descendants were the Amramites, the Yitsharites, the Hevronites, andВҰ62544 the Uzziyelites, so theyВҰ62554 made up the Kohatites.
\v 28 They had 8,600 males that were at least a monthВҰ62564 old. They were in charge of the running of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62572 tentВҰ62572\add*.
\v 29 The Kohatite clansВҰ62574 were to camp of the southernВҰ62582 side of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62581 tentВҰ62581\add*,
\v 30 andВҰ62584 \add *their\add* leaderВҰ62584 was Uzziyel's son Elitsafan.
\v 31 They were in charge of the box, the tableВҰ62598 and the lampstandВҰ62599, the altarsВҰ62600 and all the utensils used for ministry, the \add inside\add* curtain and its gear.
\p
\v 32 The man who organised the LevitesВҰ62612 was Aharon's son, EleazarВҰ62613 the priestВҰ62617. He had oversightВҰ62618 over all those who were responsible for the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62621 tentВҰ62621\add*.
\p
\v 33 Merari's descendants were the Mahlites andВҰ62626 the Mushites, so theyВҰ62629 made up the Merarites.
\v 34 They had 6,200 males that were at least a monthВҰ62640 old,
\v 35 andВҰ62646 their leaderВҰ62646 was Avihayil's son TsurielВҰ62652. They were to camp on the northernВҰ62660 side of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62658 tentВҰ62658\add*.
\v 36 \add *They\add* were in charge of all the framesВҰ62666 for the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62667 tentВҰ62667\add*, its crossbars, posts, basesВҰ62670, all its containers andВҰ62662 equipmentВҰ62673,
\v 37 as well as the pillarsВҰ62677 \add used to make\add* the courtyardВҰ62678 with their basesВҰ62680, pegs, andВҰ62677 ropesВҰ62682.
\p
\v 38 MoshehВҰ62694 and Aharon and his sonsВҰ62697 \add вүҲset up their tents\add* \add вүҲin front of\add* \add the entrance on\add* the easternВҰ62687 side of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62700 tent\add*. They were in charge of that tent and \add ?вүҲthe needs of\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ62702\add*. Any stranger who approached had to be \add вүҲexecuted\add*.
\v 39 MoshehВҰ62714 and Aharon listed 22,000 LeviteВҰ62711 males that were at least a monthВҰ62727 old, listing them by theirВҰ62721 clansВҰ62721 as \add вүҲper Yahweh's instructions\add*.
\s1 Paying the price for the firstborn sons
\rem /s1 The Redemption of the Firstborn; The Levites Take the Place of the First-Born Sons; Redeeming the Firstborn Sons
\p
\v 40 Then YahwehВҰ62735 told MoshehВҰ62738, вҖңList all the \add other\add* maleВҰ62743 \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ62745\add* that are at least one monthВҰ62748 old and \add вүҲcount them\add*.
\v 41 The LevitesВҰ62758 are for me, YahwehВҰ62761, in the place of the firstborn males from every \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ62766\add* family, andВҰ62755 their animals are in place of the \add вүҲIsraelis'\add* firstborn male animals.вҖқ
\v 42 \add вүҲSoВҰ62779\add* MoshehВҰ62780 listed the firstbornВҰ62789 IsraelisВҰ62790 exactly as YahwehВҰ62783 had commandedВҰ62782 him to.
\v 43 andВҰ62793 the total number of firstbornВҰ62796 males a monthВҰ62802 old or more whose namesВҰ62799 were listed came to 22,273.
\p
\v 44 Then YahwehВҰ62814 spokeВҰ62813 to MoshehВҰ62817,
\v 45 вҖңTake the Levites instead of everyВҰ62825 firstbornВҰ62827 male IsraeliВҰ62828, and the Levites' animals instead of theirВҰ62835 animals, and the Levites will be mineвҖ”I am YahwehВҰ62841.
\v 46 To redeem the 273 firstbornВҰ62852 IsraelisВҰ62854 who outnumberВҰ62848 the LevitesВҰ62851,
\v 47 collectВҰ62856 five silver coins for each one of them. (Use the same silver coins weighing eleven grams, that the priests use in the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62862 tentВҰ62862\add*.)
\v 48 Give that \add вүҲmoneyВҰ62869\add* to Aharon andВҰ62871 his sonsВҰ62871 as payment of the ransomВҰ62872 for those excessВҰ62873 273 males.вҖқ
\v 49 \add вүҲSoВҰ62876\add* MoshehВҰ62877 collected that ransom moneyВҰ62879 to cover the ransom of the excessВҰ62882 \add not covered by the number of\add* LevitesВҰ62885.
\v 50 HeВҰ62890 collected 1,365 silver coins from the firstbornВҰ62888 IsraeliВҰ62889 males (using the standard weight of silver from the sanctuaryВҰ62901)
\v 51 and gaveВҰ62903 \add *it\add* to Aharon and his sonsВҰ62910 just as YahwehВҰ62914 had commandedВҰ62916.
\c 4
\s1 Kohat's descendants' duties
\rem /s1 The Duties of the Levite Clan of Kohath; Duties of the Kohathite Clan; The Kohathites
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ62924 told MoshehВҰ62927 \add (MosesВҰ62927)\add* and Aharon \add (AaronВҰ62930)\add*,
\v 2 вҖң\add вүҲTakeВҰ62941 a detailed census\add* of Kohat'sВҰ62938 male descendants by their clansВҰ62942 and families
\v 3 \add вүҲwho are from twenty-five up to fiftyВҰ62953 years old\add* and who goes into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62961 tent\add* to minister.
\p
\v 4 This is what the Kohatites are responsible for concerning the \add вүҲsacredВҰ62971 tent including the inner room\add*:
\v 5 When \add вүҲit's time to break camp\add*, Aharon and his sonsВҰ62976 must enter and takeВҰ62979 down the curtainВҰ62981 that veils it, and thenВҰ62974 use that to coverВҰ62983 the box \add вүҲcontaining the agreement\add*.
\v 6 ThenВҰ62990 they must cover it with \add ?вүҲfine\add* leather, followed by a blue cloth, andВҰ62990 thenВҰ62990 put itsВҰ63002 \add carrying\add* polesВҰ63002 \add through the rings\add*.
\p
\v 7 They must spreadВҰ63008 a blue cloth over the \add вүҲsacred bread tableВҰ63006\add*, thenВҰ63004 place the dishesВҰ63018, pans, bowlsВҰ63021, andВҰ63004 jugs for the drink-offerings on top of that, along with the \add вүҲsacred\add* bread.
\v 8 ThenВҰ63030 they must spreadВҰ63030 a scarlet cloth over all that, and coverВҰ63035 that again with \add ?вүҲfine\add* leather, and thenВҰ63030 put itsВҰ63043 polesВҰ63043 \add through the rings\add*.
\p
\v 9 They must spread a blue cloth over the lampstand with its \add oil\add* lamps, its tongs and traysВҰ63062, and the oil containers thatВҰ63068 are used for it.
\v 10 ThenВҰ63074 they must wrap the lampstand and all its equipment in \add ?вүҲfine\add* leather, and place it \add all\add* on its carryingВҰ63089 frameВҰ63089.
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ63091 the must spreadВҰ63095 a blue cloth over the goldВҰ63094 \add incense\add* altarВҰ63093, and coverВҰ63098 that again with \add ?вүҲfine\add* leather, and thenВҰ63091 put itsВҰ63106 polesВҰ63106 \add through the rings\add*.
\v 12 ThenВҰ63108 they must get all the \add other\add* utensils that they use in the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63119 tentВҰ63119\add*, and coverВҰ63125 that again with \add ?вүҲfine\add* leather, and place it \add all\add* on its carryingВҰ63133 frameВҰ63133.
\v 13 They need to remove the ashesВҰ63135 from the \add bronze\add* altarВҰ63138 andВҰ63139 spreadВҰ63139 a purpleВҰ63142 clothВҰ63142 over it,
\v 14 and put all the utensilsВҰ63150 they use on top of it: the trays, meat forksВҰ63160, shovelВҰ63163 and basinsВҰ63166 for the altarВҰ63169. ThenВҰ63144 they must coverВҰ63172 it with \add ?вүҲfine\add* leather, and thenВҰ63144 put its polesВҰ63176 \add through the rings\add*.
\v 15 Aharon and his sonsВҰ63181 must finishВҰ63178 coveringВҰ63182 the \add вүҲsacred tent\add* and all its utensils and equipment when \add вүҲthey're about to move camp\add*. ThenВҰ63178 the Kohatites can comeВҰ63197 to carry it all without touchingВҰ63204 the \add вүҲinner room\add* so they won'tВҰ63202 dieВҰ63208. That's the responsibility of Kohat'sВҰ63200 descendantsвҖ”\add carrying\add* the \add вүҲsacred tent\add*.
\p
\v 16 EleazarВҰ63218 (son of AharonВҰ63222 the priestВҰ63223) is in chargeВҰ63217 of the lamp oil and the fragrantВҰ63227 incenseВҰ63226, the regularВҰ63229 grainВҰ63228 offeringВҰ63228, the anointingВҰ63231 oil, and the oversightВҰ63232 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63241 tentВҰ63241\add* and the inner room, including everything that's used inside them.
\p
\v 17 Then YahwehВҰ63246 told MoshehВҰ63249 and Aharon,
\v 18 вҖңDon't allow the Kohatite LevitesВҰ63264 to \add вүҲget wiped out\add* \add by mishandling the most sacred items\add*,
\v 19 \add вүҲbut take these precautions on their behalf so\add* they won'tВҰ63271 dieВҰ63272 when they approach the \add вүҲmost sacredВҰ63276 items\add*: Get Aharon and his sonsВҰ63279 to goВҰ63280 and show \add вүҲeach of them personally\add* the \add вүҲcorrect and proper way to do his duties\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲHowever,\add* they must never \add goВҰ63294 early\add* to \add вүҲset their eyes on\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63299 objectsВҰ63299\add*, \add вүҲeven briefly\add*, or they'll dieВҰ63300.вҖқ
\s1 Gershon's descendants' duties
\rem /s1 The Gershonites; Duties of the Gershonite Clan; The Duties of the Levite Clan of Gershon; The Gershonites and Merarites
\p
\v 21 Then YahwehВҰ63304 told MoshehВҰ63307,
\v 22 вҖң\add вүҲTake a detailed census\add* of Gershon'sВҰ63315 male descendantsВҰ63314 by their clansВҰ63321 and families
\v 23 \add вүҲwho are from thirtyВҰ63324 up to fiftyВҰ63330 years old\add* andВҰ63326 who goes into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63341 tent\add* to minister.
\p
\v 24 This is what the Gershonites are responsible for working with andВҰ63349 carrying:
\v 25 They must carryВҰ63351 the \add inner\add* curtains from the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63355 tentВҰ63355\add*, the covering, the \add ?вүҲfine\add* leatherВҰ63362 covering, the entranceВҰ63370 curtain,
\v 26 the courtyard curtains, and the courtyard gate curtain, along with the ropesВҰ63394 and other equipment for using them. That will be their ministry.
\v 27 Aharon and his sonsВҰ63413 \add вүҲwill direct\add* the Gershonites in theirВҰ63424 duties and assignВҰ63425 all \add the items\add* to them.
\v 28 That will be the ministry of Gershon's descendantsВҰ63436 with the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63438 tent\add*, andВҰ63440 it will all be under the supervision of Aharon's son ItamarВҰ63442 the priestВҰ63446.
\s1 Merari's descendants' duties
\rem /s1 The Duties of the Levite Clan of Merari; Duties of the Merarite Clan; The Merarites
\p
\v 29 вҖң\add вүҲTake a detailed census\add* of Merari'sВҰ63450 descendantsВҰ63449 by their clansВҰ63451 and families,
\v 30 listing the men who are from thirtyВҰ63459 to fiftyВҰ63465 years old and who goes into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63476 tent\add* to minister.
\v 31 Their duties are carryingВҰ63481 the framesВҰ63487, crossbars, posts, andВҰ63479 sockets for the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63488 tentВҰ63488\add*,
\v 32 the courtyardВҰ63494 pillarsВҰ63493 and their basesВҰ63496, their pegs and ropesВҰ63498, and all their equipment. Every man must be assignedВҰ63505 by nameВҰ63504 as to what equipment he must carryВҰ63510.
\v 33 That will be the ministry of Merari'sВҰ63516 descendantsВҰ63515 with the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63520 tent\add*, and it will all be under the supervision of Aharon's son ItamarВҰ63523 the priestВҰ63527.
\s1 The totals from the Levite census
\rem /s1 The Numbering of the Levite Clans; Census of the Levites; The Census of the Levites
\p
\v 34 \add вүҲSoВҰ63529\add* MoshehВҰ63530 and Aharon and the communityВҰ63533 leadersВҰ63532 listed the Kohatites by their clansВҰ63538 and families,
\v 35 \add counting\add* the men from thirtyВҰ63543 to fiftyВҰ63549 years old who go into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63556 tent\add* to minister,
\v 36 andВҰ63559 the total for all the clansВҰ63561 was 2,750.
\v 37 That was from the Kohatite clansВҰ63569 who ministered at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63574 tent\add* and were listed by Mosheh and Aharon just as YahwehВҰ63583 had instructed Mosheh.
\v 38 They countedВҰ63589 the Gershonites by their clansВҰ63592 and families,
\v 39 \add counting\add* the men from thirtyВҰ63597 to fiftyВҰ63603 years old who go into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63610 tent\add* to minister,
\v 40 andВҰ63613 the total for all the clansВҰ63615 was 2,630.
\v 41 That was from the Gershonite clansВҰ63625 who ministered at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63631 tent\add* and were listed by Mosheh and Aharon just as YahwehВҰ63640 had instructed Mosheh.
\v 42 They countedВҰ63642 the Merarites by their clans andВҰ63642 families,
\v 43 \add counting\add* the men from thirtyВҰ63651 to fiftyВҰ63657 years old who go into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63664 tent\add* to minister,
\v 44 andВҰ63672 the total for all the clansВҰ63669 was 3,200.
\v 45 That was from the Merarite clansВҰ63676 who ministered at the \add вүҲsacred tent\add* and were listed by Mosheh and Aharon just as YahwehВҰ63686 had instructed Mosheh.
\v 46 \add вүҲSo\add* MoshehВҰ63696, Aharon, and the IsraeliВҰ63698 leadersВҰ63698 counted \add all\add* the LevitesВҰ63702 by their clansВҰ63703 and families,
\v 47 \add counting\add* the men from thirtyВҰ63708 to fiftyВҰ63714 years old who go into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ63724 tent\add* to minister and also help with carryingВҰ63723 it,
\v 48 andВҰ63727 the total came to 8,580.
\v 49 Those were the ones countedВҰ63752 by Mosheh \add вүҲfollowing Yahweh's instructions\add*. Each man's name was listed by Mosheh, along with his duties and what was his responsibility to carryВҰ63751.
\c 5
\s1 Handling ceremonial вҖҳuncleannessвҖҷ
\rem /s1 The Purity of the Camp; Purity in Israel's Camp; Unclean People; Unclean Persons
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ63763 told MoshehВҰ63766 \add (MosesВҰ63766)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңOrderВҰ63773 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ63772\add* that anyone with a skin diseaseВҰ63780 or a dischargeВҰ63783, and anyone who's вҖҳuncleanВҰ63785вҖҷ becauseВҰ63786 they touched a corpseВҰ63786, must be sent outside the camp.
\v 3 Whether they're male or femaleВҰ63791, they must be sent outsideВҰ63795 the camp so thatВҰ63803 the whole camp doesn't become вҖҳuncleanВҰ63799вҖҷ \add because\add* I'm livingВҰ63805 there \add right\add* amongst them.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ63808 the IsraelisВҰ63811\add* did what YahwehВҰ63821 told MoshehВҰ63824, andВҰ63808 sent those people outsideВҰ63817 the camp.
\s1 Reparations for crimes
\rem /s1 Confession and Restitution; Restitution for Wrongs; Repayment for Wrongs Done
\p
\v 5 Then YahwehВҰ63832 told MoshehВҰ63835,
\v 6 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ63841\add* that when any man or a womanВҰ63846 \add вүҲdisobeys God by doing any of the things that humansВҰ63852 do\add* when they're unfaithfulВҰ63853 towards Yahweh, then that person is guiltyВҰ63856
\v 7 andВҰ63860 they must confessВҰ63860 their \add вүҲdisobedience\add*. ThenВҰ63860 thatВҰ63864 person must make full reparation to whoever they wrongedВҰ63869, along with an extra twenty percent \add of the cost\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if reparation to \add вүҲthe victim isn'tВҰ63881 possible\add* \add for some reason\add*, thenВҰ63879 it must be paid to YahwehВҰ63889 via a priestВҰ63890, in addition to the ram \add that will be offered\add* for that person's atonement.
\v 9 AnyВҰ63908 sacredВҰ63905 contributionsВҰ63902 by the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ63906\add* thatВҰ63909 are presented to a priestВҰ63912 will belongВҰ63914 to him.
\v 10 Each person's sacredВҰ63919 contributions will be their own, \add but\add* anything given to a priestВҰ63926 will belong to himВҰ63919.вҖқ
\s1 Testing for an unfaithful wife
\rem /s1 Concerning an Unfaithful Wife; Cases of Wives with Suspicious Husbands; Protecting Marital Faithfulness; The Test for an Unfaithful Wife
\p
\v 11 Then YahwehВҰ63932 told MoshehВҰ63935,
\v 12 вҖңTellВҰ63942 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ63941\add* that if any man's wife \add вүҲhas an affair\add* and is unfaithfulВҰ63951 towards him,
\v 13 when another man secretly has sex with her, thenВҰ63955 she becomes вҖҳuncleanВҰ63966вҖҷ, even though there'sВҰ63968 no witnessВҰ63967 against her andВҰ63955 she wasn't caughtВҰ63972.
\v 14 \add вүҲIf the husband becomes suspicious, whether or not she's actually\add* become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ,
\v 15 thenВҰ64000 \add *he\add* should take \add *her\add* to a priestВҰ64007. He must also bringВҰ64034 an offering on her behalf: two litres of barleyВҰ64016 flourВҰ64015. It must not have any oil or \add вүҲspices mixed into it\add* because it's a grain offering for suspicionвҖ”\add вүҲfor determining if unfaithfulness has occurred\add*.
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ64037 the priestВҰ64039 must \add вүҲlead her forward\add* andВҰ64037 standВҰ64040 her in frontВҰ64041 of YahwehВҰ64042.
\v 17 He must \add вүҲfill\add* a pottery jar with sacredВҰ64047 water, andВҰ64044 thenВҰ64044 mix some dust from the floorВҰ64056 of \add Yahweh's\add* residence into the water.
\v 18 ThenВҰ64065 the priest must standВҰ64065 the woman \add вүҲin frontВҰ64070\add* of YahwehВҰ64071 andВҰ64065 \add вүҲlet her hair down\add*, thenВҰ64065 he must place the suspicion grain offering on her palm. (It's a grain offering for jealousyВҰ64085.) The priest must be \add вүҲholding\add* the waterВҰ64090 of bitternessВҰ64091 that bringsВҰ64092 a curseВҰ64092
\v 19 and tell the womanВҰ64100 to make this oath: вҖңIf no \add other\add* man \add вүҲslept\add* with you, and if you didn'tВҰ64103 \add вүҲdirty yourself while you're married\add*, thenВҰ64094 be free from this waterВҰ64115 of bitternessВҰ64116 that bringsВҰ64117 a curseВҰ64117.
\v 20 \add вүҲButВҰ64120\add* if you \add вүҲhave cheated on\add* your husband and become вҖҳuncleanВҰ64126вҖҷ and slept with some otherВҰ64133 guy, \add there'll be consequences\add*.
\v 21 ThenВҰ64136 the priest will make the womanВҰ64140 take that curse as an oath, and \add *he'll\add* tell \add *her\add*, вҖңYahweh will \add вүҲmake your experience\add* a curse and your peopleВҰ64152 \add вүҲwill see the results of the\add* oath, when Yahweh gives \add вүҲdisease to your genitals\add* and makesВҰ64153 your belly swell.
\v 22 This waterВҰ64165 will \add вүҲinvoke\add* the curseВҰ64166 to make your bellyВҰ64170 swellВҰ64169 andВҰ64164 your \add вүҲgenitals shrivel\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ64164 the womanВҰ64174 must sayВҰ64173, вҖңIndeed, let it be so.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ64179 the priestВҰ64184 must writeВҰ64179 those cursesВҰ64182 on a scrollВҰ64185, thenВҰ64179 wipe \add the ink\add* into the waterВҰ64189 of bitternessВҰ64190.
\v 24 He must make the womanВҰ64195 drink that waterВҰ64192 of bitternessВҰ64199 that bringsВҰ64200 the curseВҰ64200, andВҰ64201 \add *it\add* will enterВҰ64201 into herВҰ64202.
\v 25 ThenВҰ64207 he'll take the grain offering of suspicion from her hand, and hold it up \add вүҲin frontВҰ64218\add* of YahwehВҰ64219, and thenВҰ64207 take it to the altarВҰ64224.
\v 26 \add *He'll\add* takeВҰ64226 some of the grainВҰ64230 as a memorialВҰ64233 portion andВҰ64226 burnВҰ64234 it on the altarВҰ64235. ThenВҰ64226 he'll make the womanВҰ64240 drinkВҰ64237 the waterВҰ64243.
\v 27 \add вүҲAfter she's drunk it\add*, if she was вҖҳuncleanВҰ64252вҖҷ and unfaithfulВҰ64253 to her husbandВҰ64255, the water will carry that curse into her, and her belly will swellВҰ64261 and her \add вүҲgenitals will get diseased\add*, and the womanВҰ64266 will becomeВҰ64265 a curse among her peopleВҰ64269.
\v 28 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if she hadn't defiled herselfВҰ64274 and is pure, thenВҰ64271 she'll be free and \add be able to\add* \add вүҲhave children\add*.
\p
\v 29 That's the rule about jealousyВҰ64284 when a wifeВҰ64287 \add вүҲcheats on\add* her husbandВҰ64289 andВҰ64290 defilesВҰ64290 herself,
\v 30 or when a \add вүҲhusband\add* \add вүҲbecomes jealousВҰ64298 and suspicious\add* and he standsВҰ64303 \add вүҲhis wife\add* \add вүҲin frontВҰ64307\add* of YahwehВҰ64308, and the priestВҰ64311 applies this ruling to her.
\v 31 ThenВҰ64318 \add вүҲthe husband\add* will be \add вүҲinnocent\add*, andВҰ64321 that women will \add вүҲbear the consequences\add* of herВҰ64326 wrongdoing.
\c 6
\s1 Instructions for the Nazirite vow
\rem /s1 The Nazirites; The Nazirite; Nazirite Laws; Rules for Nazirites
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ64330 told MoshehВҰ64333,
\v 2 вҖңTellВҰ64340 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ64339\add* that when any man or womanВҰ64346 wants to make a solemn vow to separateВҰ64352 themself to YahwehВҰ64353 as a NaziriteВҰ64351,
\v 3 they must keep away from wine and strong drink, and \add even\add* vinegar made from wine or strong drink, plus they mustn't drink grape juiceВҰ64366 or eat either grapes or raisins.\x + \xo 6:3: \xt Luk 1:15.\x*
\v 4 For the entireВҰ64379 time of their separationВҰ64378, they mustn't eatВҰ64389 anything coming from a grapevineВҰ64382, \add вүҲnot even\add* the seedsВҰ64384 or the skins.
\p
\v 5 вҖңFor the entire timeВҰ64406 of their vow to YahwehВҰ64410 as a NaziriteВҰ64409, they mustn't cut their hairвҖ”they must sacredВҰ64411 and grow their hair long.
\p
\v 6 вҖңFor the entire time of their separationВҰ64421 to YahwehВҰ64422, they mustn't approach any deadВҰ64426 body,
\v 7 even if it's their fatherВҰ64430 or motherВҰ64431, or brotherВҰ64432 or sisterВҰ64433. They mustn't defile themselves with death, because their consecrationВҰ64440 to their godВҰ64441 is on their head.
\v 8 They must remain holy to YahwehВҰ64451 for the whole time.
\p
\v 9 вҖң\add вүҲHowever,\add* if someone right next to them suddenlyВҰ64459 died, that would defileВҰ64460 their consecratedВҰ64462 head, andВҰ64453 after the \add regular\add* sevenВҰ64468 days of purification, they would have to shave their head.
\v 10 ThenВҰ64471 on the eighthВҰ64472 dayВҰ64471, they'd have to take two doves or youngВҰ64478 pigeons to the priestВҰ64482 at the entranceВҰ64485 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ64486 tent\add*,
\v 11 and \add *he\add* would take one for a sinВҰ64492 offering and the otherВҰ64493 for a burntВҰ64494 offeringвҖ”making atonementВҰ64495 for their transgression with the corpseВҰ64501. ThenВҰ64489 they would consecrateВҰ64502 their head again that dayВҰ64506
\v 12 andВҰ64509 \add вүҲrestart\add* their days of separation, as well as bringingВҰ64515 a one-year old male lamb as a guiltВҰ64520 offeringВҰ64520. (TheirВҰ64510 initial days of separation \add вүҲwon't count\add* because they were made вҖҳuncleanВҰ64525вҖҷ.)
\p
\v 13 вҖңNow these are the instructions for the Nazirites: Once their daysВҰ64533 of separationВҰ64534 are fulfilled, \add someoneВҰ64535\add* must take them to the entranceВҰ64539 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ64540 tent\add*
\v 14 and they will presentВҰ64543 their offerings to YahwehВҰ64547вҖ”an unblemished, one-year old, male lamb as a burntВҰ64554 offering, and an unblemished, one-year old, female lamb as a sinВҰ64561 offering, plus an unblemished ram as a peace/fellowshipВҰ64566 offering,
\v 15 \add вүҲalong with\add* a basketВҰ64568 of flat breads, flourВҰ64570 mixedВҰ64572 with oil, and wafersВҰ64574 spread with \add olive\add* oil, and their grainВҰ64578 and drinkВҰ64579 offeringsВҰ64578.
\v 16 The priestВҰ64582 must presentВҰ64581 all that to YahwehВҰ64584, and \add вүҲhandle\add* their sinВҰ64588 offering and burntВҰ64591 offering.
\v 17 The ram and the basketВҰ64601 of flat breadsВҰ64602 will be offered as a peaceВҰ64598 offering to YahwehВҰ64599, and the priestВҰ64604 will offer their grain and wine offerings.
\v 18 ThenВҰ64612 the Nazirite must shaveВҰ64612 their head of separation at the opening to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ64615 tent\add*, andВҰ64612 taking the hair, must put it on the fireВҰ64630 underВҰ64633 their peace-offering sacrificeВҰ64634.
\p
\v 19 вҖңThe priestВҰ64638 will thenВҰ64637 take the boiledВҰ64642 shoulderВҰ64641 from the ram, and one flat bread roll and one waferВҰ64652 from the basketВҰ64651, and place them on the palmsВҰ64658 of that Nazirite with their consecratedВҰ64664 head that's been shavedВҰ64661.
\v 20 Then the priest will raise them as a raised offering to YahwehВҰ64672. Those raised breads and the shoulder \add вүҲare now sacredВҰ64673 and belong to\add* the priest. Then the Nazirite can drinkВҰ64683 some wine.
\p
\v 21 Those are the instructions for the Nazirite who makes a solemn oath to YahwehВҰ64693 for their separationВҰ64696, \add вүҲplus what they're able to give\add*. \add вүҲThey must do exactly what they promised\add* as per these instructions.вҖқ
\s1 The priests' prayer for blessing
\rem /s1 The Priestly Benediction; The Priestly Blessing
\p
\v 22 Then YahwehВҰ64714 told MoshehВҰ64717 \add (MosesВҰ64717)\add*,
\v 23 вҖңTell Aharon \add (AaronВҰ64723)\add* and his sonsВҰ64726 that when the blessВҰ64729 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ64732\add*, this is what they must say:
\q1
\v 24 May YahwehВҰ64739 blessВҰ64738 you and protect you.
\q1
\v 25 May \add вүҲYahwehВҰ64744 give you prosperity and show grace toward\add* you.
\q1
\v 26 MayВҰ64752 \add *he\add* \add вүҲwatch over\add* you and giveВҰ64756 you peaceВҰ64758.
\p
\v 27 вҖң\add вүҲIn that way,\add* they'll put my nameВҰ64764 on the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ64767\add*, and I will blessВҰ64770 them.вҖқ
\c 7
\s1 The leaders' offerings at the altar dedication
\rem /s1 Offerings of the Leaders; The Offerings of the Leaders; Offerings of Dedication; Offerings at the Dedication of the Tabernacle
\p
\v 1 When MoshehВҰ64776 \add (MosesВҰ64776)\add* had finishedВҰ64775 settingВҰ64777 up the \add вүҲsacredВҰ64780 tentВҰ64780\add*, he anointed it \add with oil\add* and consecrated it and all its furnitureВҰ64789, as well as the altarВҰ64792 and all its equipment.
\v 2 ThenВҰ64802 Yisrael's leaders presented \add <gifts\add*. They were the leaders of the tribesВҰ64810 who ruled over those who'd been listed \add for duties\add*.
\v 3 They broughtВҰ64817 theirВҰ64820 gifts to Yahweh's \add вүҲpresenceВҰ64837\add* in six cartsВҰ64825 \add pulled by\add* twelve bulls. Each cart was from two leadersВҰ64834, andВҰ64817 each of the bulls was from one leader.
\v 4 ThenВҰ64842 YahwehВҰ64844 told MoshehВҰ64847:
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲAccept their gifts because they'll be useful for the running of the sacredВҰ64857 tent\add*. \add вүҲDistribute them appropriately to the LevitesВҰ64863, depending on each man's duties\add*.вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ64868\add* MoshehВҰ64869 tookВҰ64868 the cartsВҰ64872 and the cattle and distributed them to the LevitesВҰ64880,
\v 7 giving twoВҰ64884 cartsВҰ64885 andВҰ64886 fourВҰ64887 bullsВҰ64888 to the GershonitesВҰ64891 to help them with theirВҰ64893 assigned duties.
\v 8 ThenВҰ64895 he gaveВҰ64902 fourВҰ64897 cartsВҰ64898 andВҰ64895 eightВҰ64900 bullsВҰ64901 to the Merarites to help them with theirВҰ64906 assigned duties under the supervision of the priestВҰ64912 (Aharon's son) ItamarВҰ64908.
\v 9 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the Kohaties weren't given any because they were responsible for carryingВҰ64924 the very holy objects, andВҰ64914 those had to be carriedВҰ64924 on their shouldersВҰ64923.
\p
\v 10 The dayВҰ64931 that the altar was dedicatedВҰ64929 and anointedВҰ64932, the leaders brought theirВҰ64938 gifts and presented them at the altar,
\v 11 andВҰ64942 YahwehВҰ64943 told MoshehВҰ64946, вҖң\add вүҲEach day\add* \add for the next twelve days\add*, one leader must present his offeringВҰ64956 for the altarВҰ64958 dedicationВҰ64957.вҖқ
\p
\v 12-83 \add вүҲThese were the leaders who presented their offerings:\add*
\li1 On the firstВҰ64964 day, Amminadav's son NahshonВҰ64968 \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of YehudahВҰ64973,
\li1 on the second day, Zuar's son Netanel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Yissakar,
\li1 on the third day, Helon's son Eliav \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Zevulun,
\li1 on the fourth day, Shedeyur's son Elitsur \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Reuven,
\li1 on the fifth day, Tsurishaddai's son Shelumiel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Shimeon,
\li1 on the sixth day, Deuel's son Elyasaf \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Gad,
\li1 on the seventh day, Ammihud's son Elishama \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Efrayim,
\li1 on the eighth day, Pedahzur's son Gamaliel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Menashsheh,
\li1 on the ninth day, Gideoni's son Avidan \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Benyamin,
\li1 on the tenth day, Ammishaddai's son Ahiezer \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Dan,
\li1 on the eleventh day, Okran's son Pagiel \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Asher,
\li1 and on the twelfth day, Enam's son Ahira \add on behalf of\add* the tribe of Naftali.
\p \add вүҲEach of the leaders presented the following offerings:\add*
\li1 a silver dish (1.5 kgвҖ”\add вүҲall weights\add* by the standard temple measurement) and a silver bowl (800g)вҖ”both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil as a grain offering,
\li1 a small gold dish (110g) filled with incense,
\li1 a young bull, a ram and a one-year-old male lamb for a burnt offering,
\li1 a male goat for a sin offering,
\li1 two cows, five rams, five male goats, and five one-year-old rams for the peace offering.
\p
\v 84 That was the dedicationВҰ65962 of the altarВҰ65963 in the dayВҰ65964 it was anointedВҰ65965, when Yisrael's leadersВҰ65968 \add presented\add* twelve silver dishesВҰ65970, twelve silver bowlsВҰ65974, and twelve goldВҰ65980 pans.
\v 85 Each silver dish weighed 1.5kg (\add вүҲall weights\add* by the standard temple measurement) and the silver bowls were 800g. The total weight of the silver was around 27 kg.
\v 86 The gold pans that had been filled with incenseВҰ66008 weighed 110g and their total weight came to 1.3kg.
\v 87 For the burntВҰ66024 offerings there was: twelve bullsВҰ66027, twelve rams, and twelve male one-year-old lambsВҰ66032 along with theirВҰ66038 grainВҰ66038 offerings. There were twelve male goats for a sin offering.
\v 88 For the peaceВҰ66049 offering, there were 24 bullsВҰ66052, 60 rams, 60 male goatsВҰ66055, 60 male one-year-old lambsВҰ66057. All of those were part of the dedicationВҰ66063 offerings for the altarВҰ66064 afterВҰ66065 it was anointedВҰ66066.
\v 89 ThenВҰ66069 MoshehВҰ66070 entered the \add вүҲsacred tent\add* to speakВҰ66075 with \add @Yahweh\add*. He heard the voiceВҰ66080 speakingВҰ66081 to him from betweenВҰ66090 the twoВҰ66091 images of winged-creatures thatВҰ66085 were on the platform above the sacred box. That's how \add @Yahweh\add* spokeВҰ66093 to him.
\c 8
\s1 Lighting the seven lamps
\rem /s1 The Seven Lamps; Setting Up the Lamps; Placing the Lamps; Preparing the Lamps
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ66098 told MoshehВҰ66101 \add (MosesВҰ66101)\add*,\x + \xo 8:1-4: \xt Exo 25:31-40; 37:17-24.\x*
\v 2 вҖңTell Aharon \add (AaronВҰ66107)\add* that when he \add вүҲplaces\add* the sevenВҰ66120 lamps \add on\add* the lampstand, \add вүҲthey must lightВҰ66119 up the area in frontВҰ66116 of it\add*.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ66123\add* Aharon did it just as YahwehВҰ66135 had instructedВҰ66134, setting up the lamps on the lampstand to faceВҰ66129 forwards.
\v 4 The lampstand from the base to its blossoms had been made by hammering \add a single sheet\add* of goldВҰ66144, just as YahwehВҰ66156 had shownВҰ66155 MoshehВҰ66159.
\s1 The dedication of Levites
\rem /s1 Consecration and Service of the Levites; The Setting Apart of the Levites; The Purification and Dedication of the Levites; The Levites Dedicated
\p
\v 5 Then YahwehВҰ66168 told MoshehВҰ66171,
\v 6 вҖң\add вүҲOutВҰ66180 of all the IsraelisВҰ66179\add*, take the LevitesВҰ66177 andВҰ66181 purify them.
\v 7 This is how to make them pure: sprinkle the sin-offering waterВҰ66191 on them, thenВҰ66184 they must shaveВҰ66193 their \add вүҲentireВҰ66197 bodies\add* and wash themselves and their clothesВҰ66201.
\v 8 They must take a \add вүҲyoung\add* bull along with its grainВҰ66209 offering of flourВҰ66210 mixedВҰ66211 with oil, plus a \add вүҲsecondВҰ66215 young\add* bull for a sin offering.
\v 9 YouВҰ66236 must have the LevitesВҰ66225 stand at the frontВҰ66226 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ66227 tent\add* andВҰ66229 summon the rest of the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ66235\add* \add there too\add*.
\v 10 ThenВҰ66238 you must present the LevitesВҰ66241 \add вүҲin frontВҰ66242 of\add* YahwehВҰ66243 andВҰ66244 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ66247 men\add* must place theirВҰ66250 handsВҰ66250 on them.
\v 11 \add вүҲOut of all the IsraelisВҰ66264,\add* Aharon must presentВҰ66255 the LevitesВҰ66259 as a raised offering to Yahweh \add вүҲso theyВҰ66266 can serve Yahweh\add* \add with their assigned duties\add*.
\v 12 ThenВҰ66273 the Levites must place theirВҰ66277 handsВҰ66277 on the bulls' heads, and one must be given as a sinВҰ66285 offering and the other as a burntВҰ66289 offering to Yahweh, to make the Levites \add вүҲinnocent in Yahweh's eyes\add*.
\p
\v 13 вҖңThe LevitesВҰ66299 must standВҰ66296 in front of Aharon andВҰ66296 his sonsВҰ66303, thenВҰ66296 they can be offered as a raised offering to YahwehВҰ66307.
\v 14 That's how \add *they'll\add* be \add вүҲdistinguished from the other IsraelisВҰ66314\add*, andВҰ66316 thenВҰ66309 \add *they'll\add* belong to me.
\v 15 ThenВҰ66320 the LevitesВҰ66324 will goВҰ66323 to serveВҰ66325 at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ66328 tent\add* afterВҰ66320 you've purified them andВҰ66320 presentedВҰ66332 them as a raised offering,
\v 16 because they're given to me by all the IsraeliВҰ66342 peopleВҰ66342вҖ”I've takenВҰ66353 them for myself in placeВҰ66344 of their firstborn male sonsВҰ66351,
\v 17 because every firstborn IsraeliВҰ66362 male person and animal belongs to me. I set them apartВҰ66373 for myself when I killed every \add other\add* firstborn in EgyptВҰ66372,
\v 18 \add вүҲso\add* I'veВҰ66386 \add now\add* takenВҰ66377 the LevitesВҰ66380 instead of the firstbornВҰ66384 IsraeliВҰ66385 sonsВҰ66385.
\v 19 ThenВҰ66388 I've given the LevitesВҰ66391 out of all the Israelis, to Aharon and his sons to serve \add вүҲthe whole country\add* by servingВҰ66402 in the \add вүҲsacred tent\add* and making \add вүҲthe Israelis innocent in Yahweh's eyes\add*. That way, a plagueВҰ66417 won'tВҰ66413 strike the Israelis when they approach the \add вүҲsacred tent\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ66426\add* Mosheh and Aharon and all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ66432\add* did to the LevitesВҰ66435 \add just\add* what YahwehВҰ66440 had instructedВҰ66439 Mosheh.
\v 21 The LevitesВҰ66453 purifiedВҰ66452 themselves and washedВҰ66454 theirВҰ66455 clothesВҰ66455, and Aharon offered them to Yahweh as a raised offering, and Aharon offered a sacrifice to \add вүҲmake them innocent in Yahweh's eyes\add*.
\v 22 After that, the Levites wentВҰ66470 to do theirВҰ66475 \add assigned\add* duties at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ66476 tent\add* \add вүҲworking under\add* Aharon andВҰ66480 his sonsВҰ66481. \add вүҲThe Israelis did exactly what YahwehВҰ66484 told MoshehВҰ66487 to do with\add* the Levites.
\p
\v 23 Then YahwehВҰ66497 told MoshehВҰ66500,
\v 24 вҖңThese are the instructions for the LevitesВҰ66505: from the age of twenty-five, LeviteВҰ66505 men will begin servingВҰ66513 the workВҰ66513 in the \add вүҲsacredВҰ66515 tent\add*
\v 25 until the age of fiftyВҰ66519 when they must retire from that workВҰ66522.
\v 26 They may thenВҰ66528 assistВҰ66528 theirВҰ66542 fellow LevitesВҰ66541 with guardВҰ66534 dutiesВҰ66542, but they can no longer workВҰ66536 \add directly\add* with the \add вүҲsacredВҰ66532 tent\add*.вҖң
\c 9
\s1 The вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ celebration
\rem /s1 The Passover; The Passover at Sinai; The Second Passover
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ66546 spokeВҰ66545 to MoshehВҰ66549 \add (MosesВҰ66549)\add* in the SinaiВҰ66552 wildernessВҰ66550, in the firstВҰ66559 monthВҰ66558 of the secondВҰ66554 yearВҰ66553 \add вүҲafterВҰ66555 they'd left\add* EgyptВҰ66557,
\v 2 вҖңThe \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ66565\add* must observeВҰ66562 вҖҳpass-overВҰ66568вҖҷ at the appointedВҰ66569 timeВҰ66569.
\v 3 You all must \add вүҲcelebrate\add* it on the evening of the 14th of this monthВҰ66575, \add вүҲfollowing all the instructions that you've all been given previously\add*.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ66592\add* MoshehВҰ66593 \add вүҲordered\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ66596\add* to \add вүҲprepare\add* the вҖҳpass-overВҰ66599вҖҷ,
\v 5 andВҰ66601 they \add вүҲcelebrated\add* it in the SinaiВҰ66613 wildernessВҰ66612 \add вүҲstarting\add* on the evening of the 14th of that firstВҰ66605 monthВҰ66609, \add вүҲfollowing all the instructions that YahwehВҰ66617 had given\add* MoshehВҰ66620.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲHowever,\add* there were some men who were вҖҳuncleanВҰ66630вҖҷ (because they'd touched a dead body) and hence they weren't able to \add вүҲcelebrate\add* the вҖҳpass-overВҰ66638вҖҷ that day, \add вүҲso\add* they \add вүҲapproached\add* MoshehВҰ66643 and Aharon
\v 7 andВҰ66649 \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңWeВҰ66668 were вҖҳuncleanВҰ66654вҖҷ because we'd touched a dead body, \add but\add* \add вүҲhow come we're excluded\add* from presenting an offeringВҰ66663 to YahwehВҰ66664 \add вүҲalong with the other IsraelisВҰ66667\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add вүҲWait here\add*,вҖқ MoshehВҰ66672 \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңandВҰ66670 I'll \add ask\add* YahwehВҰ66678 \add вүҲwhat heВҰ66677 wants you all to do\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Then YahwehВҰ66683 told MoshehВҰ66686,
\v 10 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ66692 that\add* for this and future generations, if a person is вҖҳuncleanВҰ66701вҖҷ or \add вүҲfar from home\add*, then they can \add still\add* \add вүҲobserveВҰ66711\add* Yahweh's вҖҳpass-overВҰ66712вҖҷ.
\v 11 They can \add вүҲstart\add* it on the evening of the 14th of the \em secondВҰ66716\em* monthВҰ66715, and eatВҰ66728 it \add as usual\add* with flat breadВҰ66726 and bitterВҰ66727 herbsВҰ66727.
\v 12 They must not breakВҰ66739 \add вүҲany of the lambs bones\add*, must not leaveВҰ66732 any of it untilВҰ66734 the morningВҰ66736, and must observeВҰ66746 it \add вүҲfollowing all the normal instructions\add*.\x + \xo 9:12: \xt Exo 12:46; Yhn 19:36.\x*
\v 13 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ66768,\add* any person who isn'tВҰ66755 вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ or far away, but yet who didn'tВҰ66755 celebrate the вҖҳpass-overВҰ66760вҖҷ \add вүҲthat first month\add*, must be \add вүҲdriven out of the community\add* andВҰ66749 will have to bear their \add own\add* sinВҰ66772.
\p
\v 14 IfВҰ66784 an \add вүҲoutsider is living amongВҰ66780 you\add* andВҰ66777 \add вүҲcelebrates\add* the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ, they must also do it according to \add вүҲall the same instructions\add*вҖ”\add вүҲthere's only one way to do it whether it's\add* you all, or a foreigner, or a nativeВҰ66795 of the land.
\rem /s1 The journey from Sinai to Edom; The Cloud Above the Tabernacle; The Fiery Cloud; The Cloud and the Fire
\rem /r (Exodus 40.34-38)
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲWhen the sacred tent was dedicated\add*, the cloudВҰ66805 coveredВҰ66804 the \add вүҲinner room of the tent\add*, and \add вүҲevery eveningВҰ66811 it would look like fireВҰ66818 above\add* the residence, untilВҰ66819 morningВҰ66821 \add came\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲIt remained like that\add* continuallyВҰ66825вҖ”the cloudВҰ66826 would coverВҰ66827 it \add during the day\add*, and then at nightВҰ66831, it \add вүҲwould appearВҰ66828 like\add* fireВҰ66830.
\v 17 \add вүҲWhenever\add* the cloud \add вүҲwould be lifted up\add* from the tent, \add вүҲthenВҰ66833 the Israelis\add* would \add вүҲleave that placeВҰ66844\add*. \add ThenВҰ66833\add* wherever the cloud settledВҰ66846 down, \add вүҲthat's where the Israelis would set up camp\add*,
\v 18 \add so in that way,\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ66861 would leave a place whenever YahwehВҰ66858 told them, and would set up camp whenever he told them\add*. AsВҰ66865 long as the cloudВҰ66872 stayed above the residence, they would \add stay\add* camped \add in that place\add*.
\v 19 Whenever the cloudВҰ66879 remained above the residence for a \add вүҲlong time\add*, thenВҰ66878 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ66886\add* would \add вүҲfollow\add* Yahweh's \add вүҲguidance\add* andВҰ66878 wouldn't \add вүҲpack up camp\add*.
\v 20 SometimesВҰ66913 the cloudВҰ66899 would only remain above the residence for a few daysВҰ66900, in which case they'd \add вүҲleave where they'd just camped, andВҰ66910 move on as YahwehВҰ66908 commanded\add*.
\v 21 If the cloud was lifted up the next morning, then they'd \add вүҲmove on\add*вҖ”\add in fact\add* whether dayВҰ66932 or nightВҰ66933 if the cloud was lifted up, then they would \add вүҲmove on\add*.
\v 22 Whether it was two days or a monthВҰ66943 or \add вүҲa year\add* that the cloudВҰ66948 stayedВҰ66952 above the residence, then the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ66957\add* camp would remain in that place, until \add eventually\add* \add вүҲmoving on\add* when it was liftedВҰ66960 up \add again\add*.
\v 23 \add In that way,\add* \add вүҲwhen Yahweh ordered them to camp, they would, and when order to move on, they'd do that\add*вҖ”thus they \add вүҲobeyed\add* Yahweh's \add вүҲinstructions to\add* MoshehВҰ66984.
\c 10
\s1 The silver trumpets
\rem /s1 The Silver Trumpets
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ66988 told MoshehВҰ66991 \add (MosesВҰ66991)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңMake twoВҰ66996 hammeredВҰ66999 silverВҰ66998 trumpetsВҰ66997 for yourself to use for \add вүҲassembling the communityВҰ67005\add* and for \add signalling when it's time\add* to leave the camp.
\v 3 \add вүҲWhen both are sounded, the whole communityВҰ67017 is to assembleВҰ67013 in front of\add* youВҰ67014 at the entranceВҰ67020 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ67021 tent\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲIfВҰ67033 just one is sounded,\add* thenВҰ67024 it's \add only\add* the leadersВҰ67030 andВҰ67028 headsВҰ67031 of clans who must assembleВҰ67028.
\v 5 A \add вүҲsingle blast\add* means that the campsВҰ67038 on the easternВҰ67040 side should \add start\add* moving out.
\v 6 A \add вүҲdouble blast\add* means that the campsВҰ67046 on the southernВҰ67048 side should \add start\add* moving out. \add вүҲSoВҰ67042 the blasts will signal them to get going\add*.
\v 7 (To assembleВҰ67056 the community \add as above\add*, \add вүҲuse long blows, not short blastsВҰ67057\add*.)
\v 8 The priestsВҰ67063 (Aharon's descendants) must be the ones to blow the trumpetsВҰ67065. That is a \add вүҲpermanent\add* regulationВҰ67068.
\p
\v 9 When you \add вүҲneed to defend yourselves against an attackerВҰ67080\add*, thenВҰ67072 you must soundВҰ67082 an alarmВҰ67082 with the trumpetsВҰ67083, and you'll all be \add вүҲnoticed\add* by YahwehВҰ67087, and you'll be savedВҰ67089 from your enemiesВҰ67090.
\p
\v 10 On festival days and at times of celebrations and at the beginningВҰ67095 of each new monthВҰ67096, thenВҰ67092 the trumpetsВҰ67098 will be blown as the burntВҰ67100 offerings and peaceВҰ67103 offerings are made as a memorial for you all towards your god. I am your god, YahwehВҰ67110.
\s1 The Israelis leave Sinai
\rem /s1 The Israelites Leave Sinai; Departure from Sinai; The Israelites Break Camp
\p
\v 11 Then on the 20th of the second month in that second yearВҰ67115 \add (after leaving Egypt)\add*, the cloudВҰ67122 was lifted up from above the \add вүҲsacredВҰ67124 tentВҰ67124\add*
\v 12 andВҰ67127 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ67130\add* \add вүҲstarted moving out from the SinaiВҰ67133 wilderness as per the pre-arranged order\add*. The cloudВҰ67135 moved to the ParanВҰ67137 wilderness.
\v 13 That was the firstВҰ67140 time that they had moved \add вүҲas a result of YahwehВҰ67144 signalling MoshehВҰ67147\add* \add by means of the cloud\add*.
\p
\v 14 YehudahВҰ67154 tribeВҰ67152 with theirВҰ67156 banner \add вүҲwas the firstВҰ67155 to leave under the leadership of\add* Amminadav'sВҰ67163 son NahshonВҰ67160.
\v 15 Tsuar'sВҰ67174 son NetanelВҰ67171 led the company from YissakarВҰ67170 tribeВҰ67168,
\v 16 andВҰ67176 Helon'sВҰ67185 son Eliav led the company from Zevulun tribeВҰ67179.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ67187 the \add вүҲsacred tent\add* was disassembled, and the men of GershonВҰ67192 and MerariВҰ67194 set off, carryingВҰ67195 the tent.
\p
\v 18 Reuven tribe with theirВҰ67203 banner \add вүҲwas next to leave under the leadership of\add* Shedeyur's son Elitsur.
\v 19 Tsurishaddai's son ShelumielВҰ67218 led the company from Shimeon tribeВҰ67215.
\v 20 Deuel'sВҰ67234 son ElyasafВҰ67231 led the company from GadВҰ67230 tribeВҰ67227.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ67236 the \add вүҲsacred utensils\add* were carriedВҰ67238 out by the KohatiteВҰ67237 \add men\add*, who \add вүҲthenВҰ67236 helped set up the sacred tentВҰ67243 when they arrivedВҰ67246\add*.
\p
\v 22 Efrayim tribeВҰ67252 with theirВҰ67255 banner \add вүҲwas next to leave under the leadership of\add* Ammihud'sВҰ67262 son Elishama.
\v 23 Pedahtsur's son GamalielВҰ67270 led the company from Menashsheh tribeВҰ67267.
\v 24 Gideoni's son Avidan led the company from BenyaminВҰ67282 tribeВҰ67280.
\p
\v 25 DanВҰ67294 tribe with theirВҰ67299 banner \add вүҲwas last to leave as the rear guard under the leadership of\add* Ammishaddai'sВҰ67306 son AhiezerВҰ67303.
\v 26 Okran'sВҰ67318 son PagielВҰ67315 led the company from AsherВҰ67314 tribeВҰ67312.
\v 27 Eynan'sВҰ67329 son AhiraВҰ67326 led the company from NaftaliВҰ67325 tribeВҰ67323.
\v 28 ThatВҰ67335 was \add вүҲthe order of the departures of the companies of the IsraeliВҰ67333 tribes when they\add* set off.
\p
\v 29 Then Mosheh told Hovav (son of the Midianite ReuelВҰ67345 who was Mosheh's father-in-law), вҖңWe're heading towards the placeВҰ67354 thatВҰ67355 Yahweh said he'd giveВҰ67359 us. Come \add вүҲand join us, and we'll look after you, because Yahweh has promised to look after\add* YisraelВҰ67373.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 вҖң\add Thank you but\add* \add вүҲno\add*,вҖқ Hovav \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңI'll \add вүҲreturn\add* to my land andВҰ67375 to my relativesВҰ67387.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 вҖңPlease don'tВҰ67391 leaveВҰ67394 us,вҖқ Mosheh \add вүҲinsisted\add*, вҖңbecause you're \add the one who\add* knows about camping in the wildernessВҰ67403, andВҰ67390 you \add вүҲcould be our guide\add*.
\v 32 When you come with us, YahwehВҰ67419 \add вүҲwill be blessing us so we'll also bless\add* you.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The People Set Out
\p
\v 33 ThenВҰ67424 they \add вүҲleft\add* Yahweh's mountain \add вүҲandВҰ67424 travelled for\add* three days, with the box \add вүҲcontaining\add* Yahweh's agreement \add вүҲbeing carried at the frontВҰ67435\add* to find a restingВҰ67441 placeВҰ67441 for them,
\v 34 andВҰ67443 Yahweh'sВҰ67444 cloudВҰ67443 was over them \add each\add* dayВҰ67446 as they set out from theirВҰ67447 stop.
\p
\v 35 \add вүҲAs the box started moving\add*, MoshehВҰ67459 would say, вҖңYahwehВҰ67462, take action and then your enemiesВҰ67464 will scatterВҰ67463, and the ones hating you will flee away from your \add вүҲpresenceВҰ67467\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 10:35: \xt Psa 68:1.\x*
\v 36 ThenВҰ67469 \add at the end of the day\add* when it came to rest, he would say, вҖңYahwehВҰ67472, returnВҰ67471 \add to\add* the \add вүҲtens of thousandsВҰ67473 of IsraelisВҰ67474\add*.вҖқ
\c 11
\s1 Complaints and fire from Yahweh
\rem /s1 The People Complain to Moses; The Place Named Taberah; Fire From the Lord; Complaining in the Desert
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day,\add* the peopleВҰ67481 were complainingВҰ67482 \add about their situation\add* and \add вүҲwhen YahwehВҰ67485 heard them, it made him angry\add* \add вүҲso he sent a fireВҰ67493 that burnt up the edges of their camp\add*.
\v 2 The peopleВҰ67500 criedВҰ67499 out to Mosheh \add for help\add*, and \add *he\add* prayedВҰ67504 to YahwehВҰ67508, and the fireВҰ67510 stopped,
\v 3 andВҰ67512 they named that placeВҰ67515 Taverah \add (which means вҖҳburningвҖҷ)\add* because Yahweh's fireВҰ67522 had burnt among them.
\s1 The choosing of seventy elders
\rem /s1 Quail From the Lord; Moses Chooses Seventy Leaders
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲHowevever\add*, there was a \add вүҲgroup of stirrers among the peopleВҰ67533\add* thatВҰ67526 \add вүҲbadly wanted to have meat and other foods to eat\add*. \add ?вүҲThat spread to all the IsraelisВҰ67533 who wept and asked\add*, вҖңWho'll give us meat to eat?
\v 5 We rememberВҰ67540 the fishВҰ67543 thatВҰ67544 weВҰ67546 ateВҰ67546 in EgyptВҰ67547 for free, \add as well as\add* the cucumbersВҰ67550, melonsВҰ67552, leeksВҰ67555, onionsВҰ67558, and garlicВҰ67561,
\v 6 \add вүҲbut\add* now ourВҰ67564 appetiteВҰ67564 \add вүҲhas shrivelled up because we don'tВҰ67566 see anythingВҰ67567 to eat exceptВҰ67568 this вҖҳstuffвҖҷ\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 (The вҖҳstuffвҖҷ \add they ate every day\add* was \add a bit\add* like corianderВҰ67577 seed \add except kind of clear\add*.\x + \xo 11:7-8: \xt Exo 16:31.\x*
\v 8 \add Each morning\add* the peopleВҰ67584 wentВҰ67583 around gatheringВҰ67585 it, then groundВҰ67586 it with a \add stone\add* mill or poundedВҰ67589 it in a mortarВҰ67590, then they boiledВҰ67591 it and made \add вүҲsomething like breadВҰ67595 rolls with\add* it. They tastedВҰ67597 like fresh \add olive\add* oil.
\v 9 The вҖҳstuffвҖҷ actually descended on the camp during the nightВҰ67607 with the dew.)\x + \xo 11:9: \xt Exo 16:13-15.\x*
\p
\v 10 Mosheh heard the peopleВҰ67616 weepingВҰ67617 in their tentsВҰ67621 (set up by tribe and clan). \add *He\add* thought it was wrong, and \add it made\add* YahwehВҰ67625 \add вүҲvery angry\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ67631\add* MoshehВҰ67632 \add вүҲasked\add* YahwehВҰ67635, вҖңWhy \add вүҲhave you caused me, your servantВҰ67638, to be in trouble\add* \add like this\add*? \add вүҲDon't you approve of me?\add*. \add вүҲWhy\add* has the burdenВҰ67648 of all this peopleВҰ67651 group \add landed\add* on me?
\v 12 \add вүҲWas it me who\add* conceivedВҰ67656 \add *it\add*? \add вүҲDid I carryВҰ67670 it to the land promised to their ancestorsВҰ67682, like I was a wet-nurse\add*?
\v 13 All these peopleВҰ67690 come to me to ask me to give them meat to eat. Where would I get \add enough\add* meat \add to feed all\add* them?
\v 14 I can't bear \add the load of\add* this entireВҰ67711 peopleВҰ67713 group by myselfВҰ67707вҖ”it's too heavyВҰ67716 for me.
\v 15 If that's what you'reВҰ67723 doingВҰ67725 to me, pleaseВҰ67728 kill me now if I've foundВҰ67732 favourВҰ67733 in your eyes. \add вүҲThenВҰ67719 I wouldn't have to suffer like this\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Moses Chooses Seventy Leaders; The Seventy Elders
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehВҰ67742 told MoshehВҰ67745, вҖңBring me seventyВҰ67749 of Yisrael's elders who you knowВҰ67754 \add вүҲare good leaders\add*, and take them to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ67765 tent\add*, and \add вүҲlet them take their positions\add* thereВҰ67768 with you.
\v 17 I'll comeВҰ67771 down and talk with you thereВҰ67774, and I'll takeВҰ67775 some of the spiritВҰ67778 that's on you and put \add <it\add* on them, and thenВҰ67771 they'll carry the burdenВҰ67785 of the peopleВҰ67786 along with you. ThenВҰ67771 you won'tВҰ67787 \add have to\add* carry \add <it\add* by yourselfВҰ67791.
\v 18 \add вүҲAlso,\add* tell the peopleВҰ67795 that because they wept in my hearingВҰ67803 about not having meat to eat like you all did in EgyptВҰ67813, they must \add вүҲpurify\add* themselves for tomorrowВҰ67798, because I'll provide meat for you all to eat.
\v 19 You won'tВҰ67824 \add just\add* have meat for a day or two, or for five, ten, or twentyВҰ67834 days,
\v 20 you have it for a \add whole\add* monthВҰ67839 untilВҰ67841 it comes out your nostrilsВҰ67845. \add Yes,\add* it'll make you all nauseous becauseВҰ67849 you rejectedВҰ67852 YahwehВҰ67855 who's among you, and you all wept \add вүҲin front of him, complaining\add*, вҖҳWhy did we ever leave EgyptВҰ67864?вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 21 MoshehВҰ67867 \add вүҲqueried\add*, вҖңThere's 600,000 \add вүҲable to serve in the army\add* \add plus women andВҰ67866 children\add*, yet you say thatВҰ67874 you'll give them \add all\add* enough meat to eat \add every\add* day for monthВҰ67883!
\v 22 \add вүҲEven if we killed all the cattle and sheep, or caught all the fish in the seaВҰ67898, that wouldn't be enough meat\add* for \add all\add* them.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 вҖң\add Do you think that\add* Yahweh's \add вүҲpowerlessВҰ67910\add*?вҖқ Yahweh \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲSoon\add* you'll seeВҰ67914 whetherВҰ67915 or not my statement will \add вүҲcomeВҰ67915 true\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ67921\add* MoshehВҰ67922 went out and \add вүҲpassed on\add* Yahweh's messageВҰ67928 to the people. ThenВҰ67921 he gatheredВҰ67930 seventyВҰ67931 men from the \add вүҲIsraeli\add* eldersВҰ67933 and stood them aroundВҰ67937 the tent.
\v 25 ThenВҰ67940 YahwehВҰ67941 came down in the cloudВҰ67943 and spokeВҰ67944 to \add @Mosheh\add*, and he took \add вүҲsome of\add* the spirit away from him and put it on those seventyВҰ67955 eldersВҰ67957. As the spirit restedВҰ67959 on them, they prophesiedВҰ67962 \add вүҲ(but they never did thatВҰ67950 again)\add*.
\p
\v 26 Two of the menВҰ67969 who were listed (named EldadВҰ67975 and Meydad), had remainedВҰ67966 in the \add main\add* camp (not going to the \add sacred\add* tent), and the spiritВҰ67981 had \add also\add* restedВҰ67979 on them and they prophesiedВҰ67987 in the camp.
\v 27 A youngВҰ67991 manВҰ67991 ranВҰ67990 to MoshehВҰ67993 and told him that EldadВҰ67995 and Meydad were prophesyingВҰ67997 \add there\add* in the camp.
\p
\v 28 ThenВҰ68000 Nun'sВҰ68004 son Yehoshua (who had helped Mosheh since his youthВҰ68007) \add вүҲrespondedВҰ68000\add*, вҖңMy masterВҰ68009 Mosheh, stop them \add from that\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲButВҰ68013\add* MoshehВҰ68015 replied, вҖңAre youВҰ68017 being jealousВҰ68016 \add вүҲon my behalf\add*? \add вүҲI'd be happy if\add* YahwehВҰ68024 would put his spirit on \em all\em* the peopleВҰ68023 andВҰ68019 \add вүҲmake them into\add* prophetsВҰ68025.вҖқ
\v 30 ThenВҰ68035 MoshehВҰ68036 andВҰ68041 the eldersВҰ68041 \add вүҲwent back to their tents\add*.
\s1 Yahweh sends quails for meat
\rem /s1 The Lord Sends Quails; The Quails; The Lord Sends Quail
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ68044 YahwehВҰ68048 sent a wind that blew quailsВҰ68050 from the ocean, andВҰ68044 \add вүҲthey dropped\add* on the ground a day's walk in every direction aroundВҰ68064 the camp \add until they were piled\add* a metre high.
\v 32 \add вүҲSoВҰ68072\add* the peopleВҰ68073 went out and collected the quailВҰ68088вҖ”\add вүҲeach family getting at leastВҰ68089 the equivalent of tenВҰ68091 large barrels full\add*, and they spread the meat aroundВҰ68096 the camp \add to sun dry\add*.
\v 33 ThenВҰ68110 when they started to \add cook and\add* eat \add some of the fresh\add* meat, YahwehВҰ68106 \add вүҲgot very angry\add* and struckВҰ68109 the people with a terrible plagueВҰ68112 before they could even chew it.
\v 34 \add вүҲSoВҰ68116\add* that placeВҰ68121 was named Kivrot-HattaavahВҰ68124 \add (which means вҖҳGraves of the craversвҖҷ)\add*, because that was where theyВҰ68128 buriedВҰ68128 the peopleВҰ68131 who had craved \add <meat\add*.
\v 35 From Kivrot-Hattaavah, the peopleВҰ68137 \add вүҲmoved on\add* to Hatserot andВҰ68139 \add вүҲstayed\add* \add *there\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Miryam's punishment
\rem /s1 Aaron and Miriam Jealous of Moses; The Complaints of Miriam and Aaron; Miriam Is Punished; Miriam and Aaron Oppose Moses
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day,\add* Miryam and Aharon spokeВҰ68143 out against MoshehВҰ68146 because he'd taken an \add Ethiopian\add* woman (Kushitess) as a wife,
\v 2 andВҰ68160 they \add вүҲchallenged\add*, вҖңDid Yahweh really only speak through MoshehВҰ68164? Doesn't he also speak through us?вҖқ Yahweh heard \add what they saidВҰ68160\add*.
\v 3 (Now MoshehВҰ68176 was \add actually\add* a very humble manВҰ68175вҖ”more humble than anyone else \add вүҲalive\add*.)
\p
\v 4 Then YahwehВҰ68190 suddenlyВҰ68191 told MoshehВҰ68194, Aharon, and Miryam, вҖңGo out, the three of you, to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ68205\add* tent.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* the three of them wentВҰ68207 there.
\v 5 and YahwehВҰ68211 descendedВҰ68210 in a pillarВҰ68212 of cloudВҰ68213 and stoodВҰ68214 at the tent opening and calledВҰ68217 Aharon and Miryam, and the two of them \add вүҲstepped forward\add*,
\v 6 and heВҰ68230 saidВҰ68223, вҖң\add вүҲListen to me\add*. When there's a prophetВҰ68231 of YahwehВҰ68232, I make myselfВҰ68235 knownВҰ68235 to him in a visionВҰ68233 and speakВҰ68237 to him in a dreamВҰ68236,
\v 7 \add but\add* \add вүҲI don't do that to\add* my servantВҰ68244 MoshehВҰ68245. He's the \add most\add* faithfulВҰ68249 \add вүҲof all my people\add*\x + \xo 12:7 \xt Heb 3:5.\x*
\v 8 \add and\add* I speak to him \add вүҲdirectly\add*вҖ”\add вүҲface-to-face, and not in parables, and he's able to see my\add* form. \add вүҲSo\add* why weren't you afraidВҰ68267 to speak against my servantВҰ68269 MoshehВҰ68270?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ68272\add* YahwehВҰ68275 \add вүҲwas angry\add* at \add @Miryam andВҰ68277 Aharon\add*. ThenВҰ68272 he departedВҰ68277
\v 10 andВҰ68279 the cloudВҰ68279 \add вүҲmoved\add* from the tent. ThenВҰ68279 wow, Miryam had leprosyвҖ“her skin had gone as white as snow. As Aharon turnedВҰ68287 to her, he saw, wow, she was leprous,
\v 11 and \add *he\add* \add вүҲbegged\add* MoshehВҰ68299, вҖңPleaseВҰ68296, my masterВҰ68301, pleaseВҰ68304 don'tВҰ68302 \add вүҲmake us suffer for our foolishВҰ68309 disrespect and disobedience\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲDon't let her be like a still-born baby that's already starting to decompose when its motherВҰ68321 gives birth to it\add*.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ68326\add* MoshehВҰ68327 \add вүҲpleaded with\add* YahwehВҰ68330, вҖңGodВҰ68332, please, please healВҰ68334 her!вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲIf\add* her fatherВҰ68344 had spit in her face, wouldn't she \add вүҲstay inside in disgrace\add* for seven days?вҖқ YahwehВҰ68340 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add So\add* she must be put outsideВҰ68355 the camp for seven days, then afterВҰ68357 that, she \add вүҲcan enter again\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 12:14: \xt Num 5:2-3.\x*
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ68360\add* Miryam was sent outsideВҰ68362 the camp for sevenВҰ68364 daysВҰ68365, andВҰ68366 the peopleВҰ68366 didn'tВҰ68367 \add вүҲmove on\add* untilВҰ68369 after she \add was allowed\add* \add вүҲto return\add*.
\v 16 After that, the peopleВҰ68376 left Hatserot andВҰ68378 set up camp in the ParanВҰ68380 wildernessВҰ68379.
\c 13
\s1 Twelve scouts sent into Kanaan
\rem /s1 Exploring Canaan; Spies Sent into Canaan; Twelve Scouts Explore Canaan; The Spies
\r (Deu. 1:19-33)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ68384 told MoshehВҰ68387 \add (MosesВҰ68387)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңSend some men in to explore KanaanвҖ”the land that I'm giving to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ68403\add*. Send one man from each \add вүҲancestralВҰ68410\add* tribeвҖ”a leaderВҰ68413 within that tribe.вҖқ
\v 3 ThenВҰ68416 \add вүҲat Yahweh's command\add*, MoshehВҰ68418 sentВҰ68416 them off from the ParanВҰ68420 wildernessВҰ68419. They were all \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ68428\add* leaders
\v 4 andВҰ68433 theirВҰ68434 namesВҰ68434 were:
\li1 ShammuaВҰ68437 (Zakkur's son) from Reuven tribeВҰ68435,
\li1
\v 5 ShafatВҰ68444 (Hori'sВҰ68447 son) from ShimeonВҰ68443 tribeВҰ68442,
\li1
\v 6 Kalev \add (CalebВҰ68451вҖ”\add*Yefunneh'sВҰ68454 son) from YehudahВҰ68450 \add (Judah)\add* tribeВҰ68449,
\li1
\v 7 Yigal (Yosef'sВҰ68461 son) from Yissakar tribeВҰ68456,
\li1
\v 8 HosheaВҰ68465 (Nun'sВҰ68468 son) from EfrayimВҰ68464 tribeВҰ68463,
\li1
\v 9 PaltiВҰ68472 (Rafu'sВҰ68475 son) from BinyaminВҰ68471 tribeВҰ68470,
\li1
\v 10 GaddiyelВҰ68479 (Sodi'sВҰ68482 son) from ZevulunВҰ68478 tribeВҰ68477,
\li1
\v 11 GaddiВҰ68488 (Susi'sВҰ68491 son) from Yosef tribe,
\li1
\v 12 AmmiyelВҰ68495 (Gemalli'sВҰ68498 son) from DanВҰ68494 tribeВҰ68493,
\li1
\v 13 SeturВҰ68502 (Mikael'sВҰ68505 son) from AsherВҰ68501 tribeВҰ68500,
\li1
\v 14 NahbiВҰ68509 (Vofsi'sВҰ68512 son) from NaftaliВҰ68508 tribeВҰ68507, and
\li1
\v 15 GeuelВҰ68516 (Maki'sВҰ68519 son) from GadВҰ68515 tribeВҰ68514.
\p
\v 16 Mosheh calledВҰ68532 (Nun'sВҰ68537 son) HosheaВҰ68534, вҖҳYehoshuaвҖҷ \add (Joshua)\add*. Those were the namesВҰ68522 of the menВҰ68523 that Mosheh sentВҰ68526 out to explore \add @Kanaan\add*.
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ68540\add* MoshehВҰ68542 sentВҰ68540 them to explore Kanaan, telling them, вҖңGo through the NegevВҰ68552 andВҰ68540 thenВҰ68540 up into the hill countryВҰ68556.
\v 18 \add вүҲFind out\add* what the land's like, and whetherВҰ68572 the peopleВҰ68567 living there are \add militarily\add* strongВҰ68570 or weak, and if they're many or few.
\v 19 \add вүҲFind out\add* whetherВҰ68586 the land is goodВҰ68586 or badВҰ68590, what citiesВҰ68592 they live in, andВҰ68579 \add вүҲhow fortifiedВҰ68600 they are\add*.
\v 20 \add Find out\add* whether the soil is fertileВҰ68604 or not, whether or not there's trees there. \add вүҲBe courageous\add* andВҰ68602 bringВҰ68617 back some of the produceВҰ68618 from that land.вҖқ (He said that because it was the timeВҰ68620 \add of the year\add* when \add вүҲgrapesВҰ68623 were starting to ripen\add*.)
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ68625\add* \add @the twelve men\add* wentВҰ68625 andВҰ68625 explored the region from the TsinВҰ68632 wildernessВҰ68630 \add in the south, all the way\add* up to RehobВҰ68635 at LevoВҰ68636-HamatВҰ68637 \add in the north\add*.
\v 22 \add They started\add* in the NegevВҰ68640, andВҰ68639 wentВҰ68639 as far as Hevron where some of Anak'sВҰ68650 descendents lived: AhimanВҰ68646, Sheshay, TalmaiВҰ68648. Hevron had been builtВҰ68654 sevenВҰ68652 yearsВҰ68653 \add вүҲbefore\add* TsoanВҰ68656 in EgyptВҰ68657 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.
\v 23 When they got to the Eshkol riverbed, they cut off a branchВҰ68666 \add вүҲwith\add* a clusterВҰ68667 of grapesВҰ68668, and carriedВҰ68670 itВҰ68670 on a pole between twoВҰ68672 of them, \add вүҲalong with some\add* pomegranatesВҰ68675 and figsВҰ68678.
\v 24 (That placeВҰ68680 was then calledВҰ68682 Eshkol, \add meaning вҖҳclusterвҖҷ\add*, because of the cluster \add of grapes\add* they'd taken from thereВҰ68691.)
\s2 The reports from the scouts
\rem /s1 The Report of the Spies; The Scouting Report
\p
\v 25 Forty days \add вүҲlater\add*, they returnedВҰ68695 from exploring that land
\rem /s1 Report on the Exploration
\v 26 and wentВҰ68703 to KadeshВҰ68722 in the ParanВҰ68721 wildernessВҰ68720. There theyВҰ68703 reported back to MoshehВҰ68706 and Aharon and all the assembled peopleВҰ68715, and showedВҰ68731 them the fruitВҰ68734 from the land,
\v 27 and told \add #them\add*, вҖңWe wentВҰ68741 to the land where you sentВҰ68746 us, and it is indeed flowingВҰ68748 with milk and honeyВҰ68750, and this is its fruitВҰ68754.
\v 28 However, the people living in that land are powerful, and the citiesВҰ68763 are very well fortifiedВҰ68764. Also, some of the AnakВҰ68770 people group live thereВҰ68772.
\v 29 The Amalekite people live in the NegevВҰ68777, and the HittitesВҰ68778, Yebusites, and AmoritesВҰ68780 live in the hill countryВҰ68782, and the Kanaanites live along the coast and \add вүҲalong\add* the YordanВҰ68790 \add river\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ68792 Kalev \add (CalebВҰ68793)\add* \add raised an arm\add* to quietenВҰ68792 the peopleВҰ68796 in front of MoshehВҰ68799 \add вүҲand stated\add*, вҖңWe'll certainly go in there and take it over, because we're capable of \add going\add* against \add #them\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 \add вүҲButВҰ68811\add* the menВҰ68811 who'd gone in with him \add вүҲargued\add*, вҖң\add No,\add*, we're not able to \add battle\add* againstВҰ68820 them because \add #they're\add* strongerВҰ68825 than us.вҖқ
\v 32 ThenВҰ68829 \add they went on to\add* bring out a bad reportВҰ68830 to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ68837\add* about the land that they'd explored, saying, вҖңThe land that we passedВҰ68842 to explore is a land that devoursВҰ68847 those who live in it. \add вүҲIn addition,\add* all the people we saw in there were \add вүҲtall\add* \add andВҰ68829 powerful\add*,
\v 33 plus we saw the NefilimВҰ68869 (descendantsВҰ68865 of AnakВҰ68866), and we felt \add as small as\add* grasshoppersВҰ68872 \add вүҲcompared to them\add*, and \add вүҲthat's how they saw us as well\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 13:33: \xt Gen 6:4.\x*
\c 14
\s1 The people rebel
\rem /s1 The People Complain; The People Rebel
\p
\v 1 The assembled \add peopleВҰ68886\add* \add вүҲcried loudly that entireВҰ68878\add* nightВҰ68887,
\v 2 and thenВҰ68890 they \add started\add* to protest againstВҰ68894 MoshehВҰ68893 and Aharon. They \add вүҲwere all saying\add*, вҖңIf only we'd died in EgyptВҰ68909 or \add back there\add* in this wildernessВҰ68911.
\v 3 Why did YahwehВҰ68918 bringВҰ68919 us to this \add вүҲplace only to be slaughtered in battle with our wivesВҰ68927 andВҰ68917 children being taken as\add* plunderВҰ68930? Wouldn't it be better for us to returnВҰ68934 to EgyptВҰ68935?вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ68937 theyВҰ68937 saidВҰ68937 to each other\add*, вҖңLet's \add вүҲchoose a new leaderВҰ68943\add* to take us back to EgyptВҰ68945.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ68947 MoshehВҰ68948 andВҰ68947 Aharon fell \add вүҲto their knees with their facesВҰ68952 bowed in frontВҰ68953 of all the assembledВҰ68956 IsraelisВҰ68958\add*.
\v 6 ThenВҰ68961 Nun'sВҰ68964 son Yehoshua andВҰ68961 Yefunneh'sВҰ68968 son Kalev, two of those who'd explored that land, tore theirВҰ68976 clothesВҰ68976 \add in grief\add*
\v 7 and spoke to all \add вүҲthose IsraelisВҰ68984 gathered there\add*, вҖңTheВҰ68986 land thatВҰ68989 weВҰ68990 passedВҰ68990 throughout and exploredВҰ68992 is a very, very goodВҰ68994 \add вүҲplace\add*.
\v 8 If YahwehВҰ69003 \add вүҲis pleased with\add* us, then he'll take us into \add *it\add* and giveВҰ69010 it to usвҖ”thatВҰ69013 land flowingВҰ69016 with milk and honeyВҰ69018.
\v 9 However, you all mustn't rebelВҰ69024 against Yahweh, and you mustn't be scared of the peopleВҰ69031 in that \add вүҲarea\add* because they'll \add be like\add* breadВҰ69034 for us. \add вүҲThere's nothing left to protectВҰ69037 them as\add* Yahweh is with us, \add so\add* don'tВҰ69022 be afraid.вҖқ
\v 10 ThenВҰ69045 the \add вүҲmass of peopleВҰ69061 talked about killing them by throwing rocksВҰ69051 at them, but\add* Yahweh's \add вүҲbrilliant light\add* \add suddenly\add* appearedВҰ69054 to all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ69061 from the sacredВҰ69055\add* tent.
\s1 Mosheh asks Yahweh to forgive
\rem /s1 Moses Prays for the People
\p
\v 11 YahwehВҰ69066 saidВҰ69065 to MoshehВҰ69069, вҖңHow long will this peopleВҰ69074 group spurn me for? \add вүҲHow long will theyВҰ69081 refuse to believeВҰ69081 in me for\add*, \add вүҲdespiteВҰ69073 all the miracles thatВҰ69085 I've done among them\add*?
\v 12 I'll strike \add #them\add* with a plague and destroyВҰ69091 them. I'm make youВҰ69093 into a nationВҰ69094 that's greaterВҰ69096 and more powerful than them.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Moses Intercedes for the People
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ69100\add* MoshehВҰ69101 \add вүҲdisagreed with\add* YahwehВҰ69104, вҖңThenВҰ69100 EgyptВҰ69106 will hearВҰ69105 about how youВҰ69109 \add вүҲused\add* yourВҰ69110 powerВҰ69110 to bring \add #these\add* peopleВҰ69113 out from amongВҰ69115 them,
\v 14 and they'll \add вүҲreport\add* to the inhabitants of \add @Kanaan\add*, because those \add вүЎinhabitants\add* have heardВҰ69123 that \add you\add*, YahwehВҰ69127, are \add right here\add* in the middle of \add вүҲus Israeli peopleВҰ69129\add*, and how your cloud rests on us, and how you lead \add вүҲus\add* with that pillar of cloud that becomes a pillar of fireВҰ69149 at nightВҰ69150.
\v 15 If you \add вүҲexterminate all the Israelis\add*, those nationsВҰ69160 who've heardВҰ69163 about your fame will say,
\v 16 вҖҳ\add That\add* YahwehВҰ69171 couldn't take those peopleВҰ69175 into the land thatВҰ69180 he promised them, so he slaughteredВҰ69184 them in the wildernessВҰ69185.вҖҷ
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ69187\add* may the powerВҰ69191 of my masterВҰ69192 be greatВҰ69188, just as you've \add previously\add* said,
\v 18 вҖҳYahwehВҰ69197 is \add вүҲslow to angerВҰ69199\add* and \add вүҲquick to show\add* loyalВҰ69202 commitment, \add вүҲforgivingВҰ69203 disobedience and rebellionВҰ69205\add*. \add вүҲYet he doesn't leave the guilty\add* unpunished, \add вүҲbringing the consequences\add* of the father's disobedience onto \add вүҲthe next three generations\add*.вҖҷ
\v 19 Please forgiveВҰ69231 \add #this\add* people for their \add вүҲdisobedience\add*, \add вүҲapplying\add* your \add вүҲincredible\add* loyal commitment like how you did when you brought these people from EgyptВҰ69234 all the way to here.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңI'veВҰ69241 forgivenВҰ69241 \add вүҲas per yourВҰ69242 request\add*,вҖқ YahwehВҰ69240 \add вүҲreplied\add*,
\v 21 вҖң\add вүҲhowever,\add* as surelyВҰ69244 as I live andВҰ69244 as all the land is filledВҰ69248 with Yahweh's \add ?вүҲlight\add*,
\v 22 \add вүҲand despite\add* \add *them\add* all seeing my \add вүҲpower\add* and the \add вүҲmiracles\add* thatВҰ69269 I did \add both\add* in EgyptВҰ69272 and in the wildernessВҰ69273, they've \add now\add* testedВҰ69274 me \add вүҲmany\add* timesВҰ69278 and \add вүҲhaven't done what I told them\add*,
\v 23 \add вүҲso there's no way\add* that they'll \add вүҲenter\add* the land that I promised to theirВҰ69291 ancestorsВҰ69291. All those who despisedВҰ69294 me won'tВҰ69295 \add get to\add* \add вүҲenter\add* itВҰ69296.
\v 24 \add вүҲHowever,\add* my servantВҰ69298 Kalev \add (CalebВҰ69299)\add* has a different spiritВҰ69302 with him, and he wholeheartedlyВҰ69305 followedВҰ69306 me, \add вүҲso\add* I'll take him into the land \add вүҲthat he explored\add*, and his descendantsВҰ69315 will inheritВҰ69316 it.\x + \xo 14:24: \xt Josh 14:9-12.\x*
\v 25 The Amalekites and Kanaanites live in the valleysВҰ69321. Tomorrow, you all must turnВҰ69323 and set off towards the wildernessВҰ69326 via the \add вүҲroute to\add* the Red Sea.
\s1 Punishment for the protestors
\rem /s1 An Attempted Invasion is Repulsed; The Lord Punishes the Israelites; The Lord Punishes the People for Complaining
\p
\v 26 Then YahwehВҰ69334 said to MoshehВҰ69337 and Aharon,
\v 27 вҖң\add вүҲHow much longer\add* \add do I have to put up with\add* this evilВҰ69347 gathering that grumbleВҰ69355 against me? I've heardВҰ69362 the \add вүҲcomplaints that the IsraelisВҰ69356 are making\add* against me.
\v 28 Tell them \add this\add*, вҖҳYahwehВҰ69371 declares that as I live, \add вүҲyour own words that I heard are exactly what\add* I'll do to you all.
\v 29 \add Indeed\add* you'll \add вүҲdie there\add* in the wildernessВҰ69382вҖ”all those men who were listed as being twentyВҰ69393 years old and older that complained againstВҰ69398 me.
\v 30 You all won't enter that land that I \add would have\add* \add вүҲused myВҰ69411 power\add* to settleВҰ69412 you into. \add The only exceptions are\add* Yefunneh'sВҰ69421 son Kalev \add (CalebВҰ69418)\add* and Nun'sВҰ69425 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*.
\v 31 The childrenВҰ69427 of you all that you saidВҰ69429 would \add be taken\add* as plunderВҰ69430, I take \em them\em* in andВҰ69427 they'll \add вүҲexperience\add* the land that you all have rejectedВҰ69439,
\v 32 \add вүҲbut your bodies will remain\add* in this wildernessВҰ69445.
\v 33 Your sons will become shepherdsВҰ69450 in the wilderness for fortyВҰ69452 years, andВҰ69448 they will sufferВҰ69454 for your unfaithfulnessВҰ69457 untilВҰ69458 you \add yourselves\add* all \add вүҲbecome\add* corpsesВҰ69461 in the wilderness.
\v 34 \add вүҲFor each day\add* thatВҰ69466 you explored the land, you'll all \add вүҲbear your disobedience for one year\add*, so forty daysВҰ69465 will be forty years \add вүҲof experiencing\add* my displeasureВҰ69487.
\v 35 I, YahwehВҰ69490, have spokenВҰ69491 that I'll certainly do that to this evilВҰ69501 communityВҰ69500 that joined togetherВҰ69503 againstВҰ69504 me. They'll meet theirВҰ69507 endВҰ69507 andВҰ69508 dieВҰ69509 thereВҰ69508 in the wildernessВҰ69505.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 36 \add вүҲNow\add* those \add ten\add* menВҰ69511 who MoshehВҰ69515 had sentВҰ69514 in to explore the land, and who'd returnedВҰ69520 and the made the whole assembly grumbleВҰ69521 against him because of their evil reportВҰ69530 about the land,
\v 37 they diedВҰ69535 of a plagueВҰ69542 \add вүҲin frontВҰ69543\add* of YahwehВҰ69544 after producing that evilВҰ69541 reportВҰ69538.
\v 38 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Yehoshua (\add Joshua\add*вҖ”Nun'sВҰ69549 son) andВҰ69546 Kalev (\add CalebВҰ69550\add*вҖ”Yefunneh'sВҰ69553 son) who had also explored that land, continue to live on.
\s1 The wrong-minded attempt to invade
\rem /s1 The First Attempt to Invade the Land
\r (Deu. 1:41-46)
\p
\v 39 \add вүҲSoВҰ69565\add* MoshehВҰ69566 \add вүҲpassed on to the IsraelisВҰ69575 what YahwehВҰ69576 had said\add*, andВҰ69565 the people \add вүҲwere extremely sad\add*.
\v 40 Early the \add next\add* morningВҰ69582, they wentВҰ69583 up towards the hilltops, saying, вҖңLook at us all here! \add вүҲYes,\add* we sinnedВҰ69600 \add yesterday, but today\add* we'll goВҰ69591 up to the placeВҰ69594 thatВҰ69595 YahwehВҰ69598 saidВҰ69597.вҖқ
\p
\v 41 вҖңWhat's that?вҖқ MoshehВҰ69603 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ69602\add*. вҖң\add вүҲDon't go against Yahweh's instructions because\add* \add @your plan\add* won'tВҰ69613 succeedВҰ69614.
\v 42 Don't \add вүҲcontinue onwards\add* because YahwehВҰ69621 \add вүҲisn'tВҰ69616 with you\add* andВҰ69623 \add for sure\add* you'll all be defeatedВҰ69624 by your enemiesВҰ69626
\v 43 because \add вүҲyou'll all be facing\add* the Amalekites and the Kanaanites and you'll die by the swordВҰ69634. Yes, you've turnedВҰ69640 away from followingВҰ69641 YahwehВҰ69642 so \add *he\add* won'tВҰ69643 be with you all.вҖқ
\p
\v 44 \add Nevertheless,\add* theyВҰ69662 daredВҰ69649 to \add вүҲcontinue\add* up to the tops of the hills, \add вүҲbut\add* \add neither\add* MoshehВҰ69659 nor the box \add вүҲcontaining\add* the agreement with YahwehВҰ69658, left the camp.
\v 45 ThenВҰ69666 the Amalekites and Kanaanites that livedВҰ69669 in that \add part of the\add* hill countryВҰ69670 attackedВҰ69672 them and \add вүҲkilled\add* them as far down as HormahВҰ69676.
\c 15
\s1 Instructions about sacrifices and offerings
\rem /s1 Supplementary Offerings; Laws about Sacrifice; Laws concerning Offerings; Various Offerings
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ69680 told MoshehВҰ69683 \add (MosesВҰ69683)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ69689\add* that when they \add вүҲenter the region that I'll giveВҰ69701 them to live in\add*, \add they must do this:\add*
\v 3 \add When\add* you all make a gift to YahwehвҖ”a burntВҰ69707 offering or a sacrificeВҰ69710, to fulfillВҰ69711 a vow, or as a freewillВҰ69715 offering, or at your appointedВҰ69717 times, to make a scent of pleasingВҰ69720 for Yahweh from the cattle or from the flockВҰ69728вҖ”
\v 4 thenВҰ69730 the \add вүҲdonor\add* must presentВҰ69730 their offering to YahwehВҰ69733, \add along with\add* a grainВҰ69734 offering of a kilogram of fine flourВҰ69735 mixedВҰ69737 with 0.9 litres of \add olive\add* oil.
\v 5 \add вүҲAlso\add* about a quarter of a litre of wine for the drinkВҰ69743 offering \add must be offered\add* with the burntВҰ69749 offering andВҰ69742/or with \add each\add* male lamb.
\v 6 For a ram, there must also be a grainВҰ69758 offeringВҰ69757 of twoВҰ69760 kilograms of fine flourВҰ69759 mixed with mixed with 1.2 litres of oil
\v 7 plus 1.2 litres of wine, all to be presented as a pleasingВҰ69774 aromaВҰ69772 to YahwehВҰ69775.
\v 8 WhenВҰ69793 youВҰ69779 offer a youngВҰ69780 bull as a burntВҰ69783 offering or as a sacrificeВҰ69786 such as fulfillingВҰ69787 a vow or as a peaceВҰ69792 offering,
\v 9 the \add вүҲdonor\add* must presentВҰ69795 a grainВҰ69801 offeringВҰ69801 of 3.5kg of fine flourВҰ69802 mixedВҰ69805 with two litres of oil,
\v 10 plus a drinkВҰ69812 offering of two litres of wine, all to be presented as a pleasingВҰ69818 aromaВҰ69816 to YahwehВҰ69819.
\p
\v 11 That's what must be done for each bullВҰ69823 or ram or lamb or young goat.
\v 12 Whatever number \add of animals\add* thatВҰ69836 you offer, \add вүҲthere must be the appropriate\add* \add grain and wine offerings\add*.
\v 13 EveryВҰ69843 \add вүҲnative-born\add* \add Israeli\add* must do that when presenting a gift, all to be presented as a pleasingВҰ69856 aromaВҰ69854 to YahwehВҰ69857.
\p
\v 14 If a \add вүҲforeigner is staying with you all\add* or living among you for \add multiple\add* generationsВҰ69868, andВҰ69869 they make an offeringВҰ69869 to YahwehВҰ69874 with a pleasingВҰ69873 aromaВҰ69871, thenВҰ69859 they must \add вүҲfollow the same instructions\add* as all of you.
\v 15 \add Yes,\add* \add вүҲthe same regulations apply to both you andВҰ69884 the foreigners living among you all\add*. \add вүҲThat will always applyвҖ”foreigners in frontВҰ69892 of YahwehВҰ69893 must do the same\add* as all of you.
\v 16 One \add set of\add* instructions and regulations for \add both\add* you and the foreigner that lives among you all.
\p
\v 17 Then YahwehВҰ69907 told MoshehВҰ69910,
\v 18 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ69916 that\add* when you get to the land that I'm taking you to,
\v 19 and \add you all settle there and\add* start eating \add вүҲfood that you've grown there\add*, you all must \add вүҲdedicate\add* a \add special\add* contributionВҰ69935 to YahwehВҰ69936.
\v 20 You must present the firstВҰ69938 portion of your doughВҰ69939 and hold it up \add just\add* like a presentation from the threshingВҰ69944 floorВҰ69944.
\v 21 YouВҰ69952 all must do that \add each year\add* with your firstВҰ69949 doughВҰ69950, even throughВҰ69954 \add future\add* generationsВҰ69954.
\s1 Handling unintentional non-compliance
\rem /s1 Offerings for Unintentional Sins
\p
\v 22 вҖң\add вүҲHowever,\add* if you \add вүҲdo something wrong\add* and don'tВҰ69959 follow all theseВҰ69965 instructions thatВҰ69966 YahwehВҰ69969 told MoshehВҰ69972,
\v 23 i.e., \add вүЎdon't follow\add* everything that YahwehВҰ69979 has commanded through MoshehВҰ69983 from when the commands were given \add right\add* through to \add вүҲfuture\add* generationsВҰ69991,
\v 24 thenВҰ69993 \add вүҲassuming that it was an accident\add*, the communityВҰ70002 must offer a young bullВҰ70003 for a burntВҰ70008 offering to make a pleasingВҰ70010 aromaВҰ70009 for YahwehВҰ70011, along with its grainВҰ70012 offering andВҰ69993 drinkВҰ70013 offering as per the instructions, plus a maleВҰ70015 goatВҰ70015 as a sinВҰ70019 offering.
\v 25 \add That way\add* the priestВҰ70022 will make atonementВҰ70021 for the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ70028 community\add* and they'll be forgivenВҰ70030 because it was a mistake and they'd broughtВҰ70037 their gift as an offering to YahwehВҰ70042 plus their sin offering because of their mistake.
\v 26 TheВҰ70055 \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ70054 community\add* will be forgivenВҰ70050 along with \add вүҲany foreigner living among them\add* because it accidentally affected the entire community.
\p
\v 27 вҖң\add вүҲNow\add* if a single person disobeys by mistake, then that person must presentВҰ70072 a one-year-old femaleВҰ70073 goatВҰ70073 as a sin offeringВҰ70077,
\v 28 andВҰ70091 the priestВҰ70080 will make atonement for that person. \add In that way,\add* the one making a mistake in frontВҰ70087 of YahwehВҰ70088 will be forgivenВҰ70091.
\v 29 \add BothВҰ70096\add* \add вүҲnative-born IsraelisВҰ70095\add* andВҰ70097 foreigners living among them must \add all\add* \add вүҲfollow the same instructions after\add* making a mistake.
\v 30 \add вүҲHowever,\add* any person who \add вүҲdisobeys defiantly\add*, whether native-born or foreigner, they are slandering YahwehВҰ70122 andВҰ70107 that person must be \add вүҲdriven out of the community\add*
\v 31 because they've despisedВҰ70135 Yahweh's messageВҰ70132 and disobeyed his instructions. That person must be \add вүҲcompletely\add* cut off and their guiltВҰ70145 \add remains\add* on them.
\s1 Violating the rest day
\rem /s1 Penalty for Violating the Sabbath; Penalty for Breaking the Sabbath; The Man Who Broke the Sabbath; The Sabbath-Breaker Put to Death
\p
\v 32 \add One day\add* when the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ70152\add* were in the wildernessВҰ70153, they \add вүҲnoticed\add* a man gatheringВҰ70156 firewood on the rest day,
\v 33 and those who \add вүҲcaught\add* him took him to MoshehВҰ70169 and AharonВҰ70172 and the rest of the community.
\v 34 They put him into custodyВҰ70180, because it hadn't been decidedВҰ70183 what to do with him,
\v 35 and YahwehВҰ70191 told MoshehВҰ70194, вҖңThat manВҰ70197 must definitely be put to deathВҰ70196вҖ”the community must do it outsideВҰ70204 the camp by throwing rocksВҰ70200 at him.вҖқ
\v 36 \add вүҲSoВҰ70207\add* the community took him outsideВҰ70214 the camp, andВҰ70207 they executed him by throwing rocksВҰ70218 at him just as YahwehВҰ70222 had commandedВҰ70221 MoshehВҰ70225.
\s1 Tassels on clothes
\rem /s1 Fringes on Garments; Rules about Tassels; Tassels on Clothing; Tassels on Garments
\p
\v 37 Then YahwehВҰ70229 told MoshehВҰ70232,
\v 38 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ70238 that\add* they must make tassels on the cornersВҰ70247 of their \add outer\add* \add вүҲrobes\add*. Each tassel must have a blue cord, and they must do this \add вүҲfor all future\add* generationsВҰ70249.
\v 39 ThenВҰ70258 when you see a tasselВҰ70260, it'll remind you of Yahweh'sВҰ70269 instructions, and \add so\add* you'll \add вүҲfollow\add* them \add вүҲrather than your own desires and lusts thatВҰ70279 lead you all into unfaithfulness\add*.
\v 40 \add Instead,\add* you'll rememberВҰ70286 and follow my instructions, and \add вүҲstay pureВҰ70294\add* for your godВҰ70295.
\v 41 I am your god YahwehвҖ”the one who broughtВҰ70301 you all out of EgyptВҰ70304 (Heb. Mitsrayim) to be your god. I am Yahweh your god.вҖқ
\c 16
\s1 Korah's rebellion
\rem /s1 Revolt of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram; Korah's Rebellion; Korah, Dathan and Abiram; The Rebellion of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* KorahВҰ70314 (son of Yitshar, son of Kehat, son of LeviВҰ70323) \add along with\add* DatanВҰ70324 and Aviram (sons of Eliav) and OnВҰ70328 (son of PeletВҰ70331)\x + \xo 16:1-35: \xt Jude 11.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲrebelled\add* against MoshehВҰ70337 along with 250 \add вүҲrespected, IsraeliВҰ70341\add* community leadersВҰ70344.
\v 3 They \add вүҲgot together and challenged\add* MoshehВҰ70355 and Aharon, вҖң\add вүҲYou think you're great but the entireВҰ70365 community is sacredВҰ70369 and has Yahweh among us, so why do you consider yourselvesВҰ70373 more important than Yahweh's community?\add*вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲWhen\add* MoshehВҰ70380 heard \add <that\add*, he fell \add вүҲto his knees with his face to the ground\add*
\v 5 and \add вүҲresponded\add* to KorahВҰ70389 and his \add вүҲsupporters\add*, вҖң\add Tomorrow\add* morningВҰ70396 Yahweh will show who's sacredВҰ70406 and who belongs to him. \add ?вүҲYahweh will present his chosen leader\add*. make known who is to him and the holy one, and he will present to him, and whom he choosesВҰ70411 he will present to him.
\v 6 \add вүҲSo\add* KorahВҰ70423 andВҰ70424 \add вүҲsupporters\add*, bring incense burners
\v 7 and put \add вүҲburning coals\add* and incenseВҰ70434 in them, and bring them to \add вүҲYahweh's presence\add* tomorrowВҰ70437. ThenВҰ70428 the manВҰ70439 that Yahweh choosesВҰ70442 will be the sacredВҰ70445 one. \add вүҲIt's you Levites who think you're\add* great.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ70452 MoshehВҰ70453 told KorahВҰ70456, вҖң\add вүҲYou Levites\add*, pleaseВҰ70459 listenВҰ70457.
\v 9 Isn't it enoughВҰ70463 for you all that Yisrael's godВҰ70468 separated you from the \add rest of\add* the IsraeliВҰ70468 community to present you to him to serveВҰ70485 in Yahweh's residence and to standВҰ70482 in frontВҰ70483 of the gatherings to minister to them?
\v 10 \add @Yahweh\add* has presented you andВҰ70487 your brothersВҰ70493, the \add other\add* \add вүҲLevites\add* to approach \add <him\add*. Are you all wanting the priesthoodВҰ70501 \add now\add* also?
\v 11 \add вүҲSo\add* it's YahwehВҰ70511 that you and yourВҰ70507 group are opposing, not \add really\add* Aharon that you're all grumblingВҰ70517 about.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ70521 MoshehВҰ70522 \add вүҲsummoned\add* Eliav's sonsВҰ70526 DatanВҰ70524 andВҰ70521 Aviram \add вүҲbut theyВҰ70528 refused\add*, вҖңWe won'tВҰ70529 comeВҰ70530.
\v 13 \add вүҲIsn't it enoughВҰ70532\add* that you broughtВҰ70534 us \em out\em* of a land flowingВҰ70536 with milk and honeyВҰ70538, to kill us \add here\add* in the wildernessВҰ70540, without also making yourself the ruler over us?
\v 14 \add вүҲWhat's more\add*, you didn'tВҰ70550 bring us into a land flowingВҰ70554 with milk and honeyВҰ70556 or give us an inheritanceВҰ70561 of land and vineyardsВҰ70563. Will you gougeВҰ70567 out the eyesВҰ70564 of thoseВҰ70566 \add @Kanaanites\add* \add so that we can defeat them\add*? \add No,\add* we won'tВҰ70550 comeВҰ70569.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add That made\add* MoshehВҰ70572 very angry andВҰ70571 he told YahwehВҰ70577, вҖңDon't \add вүҲaccept\add* theirВҰ70583 grain offeringВҰ70583. I've \add never\add* takenВҰ70588 \add even\add* one donkeyВҰ70585 from them \add вүҲor done anything bad to any of\add* them.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ70596 MoshehВҰ70597 told KorahВҰ70600, вҖңYou andВҰ70596 all yourВҰ70604 group, \add вүҲmust appear in frontВҰ70606\add* of YahwehВҰ70607 tomorrowВҰ70611, \add вүҲas will\add* Aharon.
\v 17 \add Each\add* man must bring his pan with incenseВҰ70619 \add вүҲburning in it\add* andВҰ70613 presentВҰ70620 it to YahwehВҰ70622вҖ”\add вүҲall 250 of you as well as\add* Aharon.
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ70633\add* \add the next day,\add* they all brought their pans with \add вүҲburning coals\add* and incenseВҰ70641 in them, and they stoodВҰ70642 at the entranceВҰ70643 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ70644\add* tent, as did MoshehВҰ70646 and AharonВҰ70647.
\v 19 plus KorahВҰ70651 had \add also\add* assembledВҰ70649 the entireВҰ70654 community \add вүҲto oppose\add* \add @Mosheh andВҰ70662 Aharon\add* at the entranceВҰ70659 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ70660\add* tent. ThenВҰ70649 Yahweh's \add вүҲbrilliance\add* appearedВҰ70662 to all the community
\v 20 and YahwehВҰ70674 warned MoshehВҰ70677 and AharonВҰ70680,
\v 21 вҖңGet away from \add вүҲall those people\add*, then I can destroy them in an instant.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add @Mosheh and Aharon\add* fell \add вүҲto their knees with their facesВҰ70695 to the ground and interceded\add*, вҖңGodВҰ70697, \add you are\add* the god \add вүҲwho gives life to everything\add*. Will you be angryВҰ70710 at the entireВҰ70707 community \add because of\add* the sin of one man?вҖқ
\v 23 \add вүҲSo\add* YahwehВҰ70714 told MoshehВҰ70717,
\v 24 вҖңTell the \add вүҲpeople to keep back from the homes\add* of KorahВҰ70729, DatanВҰ70730, andВҰ70731 Aviram.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ70733 MoshehВҰ70734 \add вүҲwalked to\add* \add the homes of\add* DatanВҰ70738 and Aviram, and the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ70742\add* eldersВҰ70742 followedВҰ70740 behind himВҰ70741,
\v 26 and he told the \add вүҲpeople\add*, вҖңPlease \add вүҲkeep back\add* from the tentsВҰ70753 of theseВҰ70756 wickedВҰ70755 menВҰ70754, and don'tВҰ70757 touchВҰ70759 anything of theirs, in case you get caught up in their \add вүҲdisobedience\add*.вҖқ
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ70771\add* \add @the rest of the Israelis\add* \add вүҲkept back\add* from the residences of KorahВҰ70775, Datan, and Aviram. \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Datan and Aviram had come out of their tentsВҰ70785, and were standingВҰ70783 at the entrancesВҰ70784 with their wivesВҰ70786 and childrenВҰ70787.
\p
\v 28 ThenВҰ70790 MoshehВҰ70791 saidВҰ70790, вҖңThis is how \add you'll all\add* known that \add it was\add* YahwehВҰ70796 \add вүҲwho selected me for this role\add*вҖ”it's \add never\add* \add вүҲbeen something that I aspired to\add*:
\v 29 If all theseВҰ70816 men \add вүҲdieВҰ70815 a natural deathВҰ70811 like most people\add*, then YahwehВҰ70824 didn'tВҰ70823 \add вүҲchoose\add* me,
\v 30 \add вүҲbut\add* if Yahweh \add вүҲdoes something new\add* and the ground opensВҰ70832 its mouthВҰ70836 and swallowsВҰ70837 them and their homes and tents and \add вүҲall their possessions\add*, and if theyВҰ70850 then goВҰ70845 down aliveВҰ70846 into \add вүҲtheir grave\add*, then you'll all knowВҰ70848 that it was because theseВҰ70852 menВҰ70851 rejected Yahweh.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 \add вүҲAs soon as Mosheh had finishedВҰ70858 speakingВҰ70859\add*, the ground below \add @those men\add* splitВҰ70865 open
\v 32 and the earthВҰ70871 openedВҰ70870 its mouthВҰ70874 and swallowedВҰ70875 them and their homes and everyВҰ70881 man who \add вүҲbacked\add* KorahВҰ70885 along with all \add &their\add* property.
\v 33 They wentВҰ70891 down aliveВҰ70897 to \add вүҲtheir grave\add*, along with everything they owned, and thenВҰ70891 the ground covered over them and they \add вүҲvanished\add* from the \add вүҲcommunity\add*.
\v 34 AllВҰ70908 the people who were aroundВҰ70910 them fled \add away\add* \add вүҲscreaming because they were afraid of getting swallowedВҰ70917 by the earthВҰ70918 as well\add*.
\p
\v 35 ThenВҰ70920 YahwehВҰ70923 \add вүҲsent\add* fireВҰ70920 that consumed the 250 men who were presenting incenseВҰ70930.
\s1 The incense burners
\rem /s1 The Fire Pans
\p
\v 36 Then Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 37 вҖңTell the priest Eleazar (Aharon's son) to \add вүҲcollect the incense pans\add* from \add вүҲthose who were burnt\add*, and scatter the \add вүҲcoals far away\add* because they're sacred.
\v 38 The pans of those who \add вүҲrebelled at the expense of their own lives\add* must be hammered into thin plates \add вүҲto be attached\add* to the altar, because they presented them \add вүҲin front\add* of Yahweh and \add now\add* they're sacred, and they'll become a \add вүҲreminder\add* for the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*.
\v 39 \add вүҲSo\add* the priest Eleazar took the bronze incense burners that had been presented by those men who'd been burnt up, and they were hammered into a plating for the altar
\v 40 for a memorial for the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* just as Yahweh had told him via Mosheh. That's a reminder that no one who's not a descendant of Aharon is allowed to approach Yahweh with incense burners, so they don't end up like Korah and his \add вүҲsupporters\add*.
\s1 The people complain and cause a plague
\rem /s1 Aaron Saves the People
\p
\v 41 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the next day the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* complained about Mosheh and Aharon, вҖң\add вүҲIt was you who\add* killed Yahweh's people.вҖқ
\v 42 \add вүҲBut\add* as the community gathered \add there\add* against Mosheh and Aharon, they \add вүҲlooked across\add* to the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent, and wow, the cloud covered over it and Yahweh's \add вүҲbrilliance\add* appeared.
\v 43 Mosheh and Aharon went \add over\add* to the front of the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent,
\v 44 and Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 45 вҖңGet away from this \add вүҲgathering\add* and then I'll finish them \add вүҲin an instant\add*.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲBut\add* \add @Mosheh and Aharon\add* fell \add вүҲto their knees with their faces to the ground\add*,
\v 46 and Mosheh told Aharon, вҖңTake the incense burner, and put fire in it from the altar and incense, and take it quickly to the \add вүҲpeople\add* and make atonement for them, because Yahweh's rage is \add already\add* \add вүҲburning\add*вҖ”the plague has begun.вҖқ
\v 47 \add вүҲSo\add* Aharon took it as Mosheh had told \add <him\add* and ran into the middle of the \add вүҲpeople\add*. Wow, the plague had already begun, \add вүҲso he burnt\add* incense and made atonement for \add *them\add*.
\v 48 He stood between those who were dying and those still alive, and the plague was restrained.
\v 49 There were 14,700 \add >people\add* who died from the plague, in addition to those who'd died due to Korah's \add вүҲrebellion\add*.
\v 50 Then Aharon returned to Mosheh at the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent entrance, \add вүҲas\add* the plague had been \add вүҲstopped\add*.
\c 17
\s1 The budding of Aharon's rod
\rem /s1 Aaron's Walking Stick; The Budding of Aaron's Staff; The Budding of Aaron's Rod
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ70935 told MoshehВҰ70938,
\v 2 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* to bring you twelve staffsвҖ”one from each ancestral \add tribe\add* with the leader's name inscribed on it,
\v 3 and inscribe Aharon's name on the staff for the \add вүҲLevites\add* so there's one for each tribe.
\v 4 Put them \add all\add* in the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent in front of the \add вүҲsacred box\add* where I meet with you,
\v 5 and then the staff of the manВҰ71012 that I choose \add to be the priest\add* will sprout. Then the \add вүҲpeople\add* can stop complaining to me about you.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSo MoshehВҰ71047 passed the message on to the IsraeliВҰ71041\add* leaders and they gave him one staff for each leaderвҖ”\add вүҲa total of twelve including Aharon's one\add*,
\v 7 and MoshehВҰ71065 \add вүҲlaid\add* them \add вүҲin front\add* of YahwehВҰ71079 in the \add вүҲsacredВҰ71072\add* tent.
\p
\v 8 Then the next day when MoshehВҰ71083 wentВҰ71082 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ71088\add* tent, wow, he saw that Aharon's staff (\add вүҲrepresenting\add* Levi tribe) had sprouted, plus it had blossomed and produced a flower and ripened almonds!\x + \xo 17:8-10: \xt Heb 9:4.\x*
\v 9 MoshehВҰ71097 took all the staffs \add вүҲout of the tent\add* to the people \add вүҲto look at\add* andВҰ71093 \add вүҲeach of the leaders\add* took back his own staff,
\v 10 then Yahweh told Mosheh, вҖңPut Aharon's staff \add back\add* \add вүҲin front of the sacred chest\add*. \add вүҲKeep it there as a reminder to\add* \add any\add* \add вүҲrebels to stop complaining against me so theyВҰ71108 won't\add* die.вҖқ
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ71118\add* MosesВҰ71115 did what YahwehВҰ71143 had commanded.
\p
\v 12 Then the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* \add вүҲcomplained\add* to MoshehВҰ71153, вҖңWow, \add вүҲwe're done forвҖ”it's clear that we're all going to die\add*!
\v 13 Everyone who goes close to Yahweh's residence \add вүҲgets killed\add*. \add вүҲWon't we all die\add*?вҖқ
\c 18
\s1 The work of priests and Levites
\rem /s1 Duties of Priests and Levites; Responsibility of Priests and Levites
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ71452 told Aharon \add (AaronВҰ71455)\add*, вҖңYou and your \add вүҲLevite brothers and cousins\add* and \add all\add* your descendants must bear the \add вүҲimperfections\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ71466 tentВҰ71466\add*, and you and your sons must bear the \add вүҲimperfections\add* of your priesthoodВҰ71474.
\v 2 Bring your \add вүҲLevite\add* brothersВҰ71479 (your father's tribe) to \add вүҲwork closely with\add* you and to assistВҰ71488 you \add as\add* you and your sonsВҰ71490 \add вүҲperform your duties at\add* the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent.
\v 3 They must look after the tent, however, they mustn't approach the \add вүҲfurnishings or utensils\add*, or the altarВҰ71509, so that both youВҰ71497 andВҰ71496 they won'tВҰ71510 dieВҰ71514.
\v 4 ThenВҰ71522 must \add вүҲworkВҰ71531 closely with\add* youВҰ71523 andВҰ71522 \add вүҲtake care\add* of \add вүҲall the duties to do with\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ71528\add* tent, \add вүҲbut\add* no \add вүҲoutsiderВҰ71533\add* \add вүҲis allowed to approach\add*.
\v 5 YouВҰ71554 \add priests\add* will \add вүҲtake care\add* of the sacred place and the altarВҰ71545, and thenВҰ71539 there won'tВҰ71546 be anymore fury againstВҰ71549 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ71553 peopleВҰ71553\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲNow listen\add*, I've takenВҰ71558 your brothers the LevitesВҰ71562 \add вүҲout from the rest of the IsraelisВҰ71564\add* as a giftВҰ71567 for youвҖ”they're given to \add вүҲdo the duties\add* at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ71574\add* tent.
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever,\add* it's youВҰ71579 and yourВҰ71578 sonsВҰ71578 who \add вүҲare the priests\add* who must serve for things to do with the altarВҰ71587 and insideВҰ71588 the curtainВҰ71589. Your priesthood is a giftВҰ71592 of serviceВҰ71591, and any \add вүҲoutsiderВҰ71597\add* who approaches must be executed.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Offerings for Priests and Levites; Support for the Priests and Levites; The Priests' Portion; The Share of the Priests
\p
\v 8 Then YahwehВҰ71603 told Aharon, вҖң\add вүҲAlso listen\add*, I've put you in chargeВҰ71613 of \add вүҲlooking after\add* the sacredВҰ71617 offeringsВҰ71614 \add вүҲto me\add*. I've givenВҰ71623 them to you and your sonsВҰ71625 as your \add вүҲpermanent income\add*.
\v 9 Every offering apart from the burnt offerings, will belongВҰ71632 to you. That includes their grainВҰ71644 offerings, their sinВҰ71647 offerings, and their guiltВҰ71650 offerings. \add вүҲOnce they're given, they become sacredВҰ71635,\add* and they're for you and yourВҰ71658 sonsВҰ71658.
\v 10 You and \add вүҲthe males in your families\add* may eat that sacred offering \add вүҲbut do remember that it's sacred\add*.
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add вүҲInВҰ71682 addition,\add* the \add people'sВҰ71681\add* raised offerings belong to you, andВҰ71673 they are \add вүҲpermanently givenВҰ71684 to your entire families\add* to eatвҖ”everyoneВҰ71691 who's вҖҳcleanВҰ71693вҖҷ may eat them.
\p
\v 12 вҖңAll the best of the freshВҰ71700 oil, and the new wine and grainВҰ71705 thatВҰ71707 they give to YahwehВҰ71710, I give to you.
\v 13 The firstВҰ71714 \add вүҲportions of all theirВҰ71718 harvests\add* thatВҰ71719 theyВҰ71721 bringВҰ71721 to YahwehВҰ71722, belongВҰ71724 to youвҖ”everyoneВҰ71725 in yourВҰ71728 \add вүҲfamilies\add* who's вҖҳcleanВҰ71727вҖҷ may eatВҰ71729 them.
\p
\v 14 вҖңEverythingВҰ71731 throughout YisraelВҰ71734 that's dedicated \add to Yahweh\add* will belongВҰ71736 to you.\x + \xo 18:14: \xt Lev 27:28.\x*
\p
\v 15 вҖңEveryВҰ71738 firstborn \add male\add* \add вүҲbaby\add*, as well as animals, will belongВҰ71751 to YahwehВҰ71748, \add however\add* you must buy back the \add вүҲhumanВҰ71749 babies\add* as well as the firstborns from the вҖҳuncleanВҰ71765вҖҷ livestock.
\v 16 \add вүҲThe babies\add* must be bought back when they're one monthВҰ71771 old, paying fiveВҰ71775 silverВҰ71774 coins \add вүҲof the proper weight according to the scales at the sacredВҰ71778 tentВҰ71778\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the firstborn cows or sheep or goats can'tВҰ71795 be bought back. They are sacredВҰ71797вҖ”you must sprinkleВҰ71802 their bloodВҰ71801 on the altarВҰ71805 and burn their fat as an offeringВҰ71810 that's a soothingВҰ71812 aromaВҰ71811 for YahwehВҰ71813.
\v 18 Their meat will belong to youВҰ71818, just like the breastВҰ71819 or the rightВҰ71822 thighВҰ71821 of the wave offeringsВҰ71820 are yoursВҰ71823.
\v 19 All sacredВҰ71829 donations by the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ71832\add*, I've \add вүҲpermanently\add* given to you and your \add вүҲchildren\add* to eatвҖ”it's an \add вүҲirrevocable agreement with\add* YahwehВҰ71835 for you and your \add future\add* ancestors.вҖқ
\s1 The Levites' share
\p
\v 20 YahwehВҰ71855 \add also\add* told Aharon, вҖңYou \add priests\add* won'tВҰ71860 inherit \add вүҲany land or property\add*вҖ”I am your share andВҰ71854 your inheritance \add вүҲamong the IsraelisВҰ71872\add*.
\rem /s1 The Share of the Levites
\p
\v 21 For an inheritanceВҰ71884 for the \add вүҲLevites\add*, I've given them all the tenths \add вүҲgiven by the Israelis\add* as their inheritance in exchange for their serviceВҰ71890 at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ71894\add* tent.
\v 22 TheВҰ71902 \add вүҲother IsraelisВҰ71901\add* mustn't approach that tent \add or\add* they'll \add вүҲincur guilt\add* andВҰ71897 dieВҰ71909,
\v 23 \add вүҲbut\add* the LevitesВҰ71912 must serve at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ71917\add* tent andВҰ71911 they must bear theirВҰ71921 \add вүҲinadequacies\add*. ThatВҰ71927 order \add вүҲapplies for all future generationsВҰ71924\add*, \add вүҲincluding\add* the not inheritingВҰ71929 any land \add вүҲlike the other IsraelisВҰ71926\add*.
\v 24 \add That's\add* because I've given the LevitesВҰ71944 that tenth that the \add вүҲother IsraelisВҰ71936\add* offerВҰ71940 to YahwehВҰ71941 as a donation. That's why I saidВҰ71949 that they won'tВҰ71954 receive \add вүҲany other inheritanceВҰ71955\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The Levites' contribution
\rem /s1 The Levites' Tithe
\p
\v 25 Then YahwehВҰ71960 told MoshehВҰ71963,
\v 26 вҖңTell the LevitesВҰ71968: вҖҳWhen you all receive the tenth from the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ71976\add* that I've given to you as you inheritanceВҰ71986, thenВҰ71966 you must offer a tenth of that tenth as a donation to YahwehВҰ71990.
\v 27 That will be considered as your contribution \add just\add* as if it was grainВҰ71999 from the threshingВҰ72002 floorВҰ72002, or \add вүҲjuice\add* from the winepressВҰ72006.
\v 28 \add вүҲSo\add* when you all offerВҰ72009 that donation from all the tenths that you receive from the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72020\add*, it must then be given as Yahweh's contribution to the priestВҰ72029 Aharon. DOUBLE-CHECK
\v 29 When an offeringВҰ72033 is presented to YahwehВҰ72038, it must be \add вүҲthe best parts of whatever is given\add*.вҖҷ
\v 30 Also tell them, вҖҳWhen you all present \add вүҲthe best of what was given\add*, it'll be as \add вүҲit's come straight\add* from the threshingВҰ72057 floorВҰ72057 or the winepressВҰ72059.
\v 31 \add The rest\add* is for your wages for the serviceВҰ72074 you all do at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ72075\add* tent, andВҰ72061 you all can eatВҰ72061 it \add вүҲwherever you want to\add*.
\v 32 \add вүҲAfterВҰ72093 donating the best tenth from it\add*, you won'tВҰ72078 incur guilt for what you all do with the rest of it, \add вүҲhowever\add* you all mustn't defile any sacredВҰ72090 things or you'll dieВҰ72097.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 19
\s1 The red cow's ashes
\rem /s1 The Water of Purification; Ashes of the Red Cow; Ceremony of the Red Heifer; The Water of Cleansing
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ72101 told MoshehВҰ72104 and Aharon,
\v 2 вҖңThis is \add вүҲa new\add* law that YahwehВҰ72116 has commandedВҰ72115, вҖҳTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72122\add* thatВҰ72113 they must bringВҰ72124 youВҰ72125 an unblemishedВҰ72128 red heiferВҰ72126 \add вүҲwith noВҰ72128 defectsВҰ72128\add* \add вүҲandВҰ72124 that has never had a yoke on its neck\add*.
\v 3 Give it to the priestВҰ72146 EleazarВҰ72145, and he must take it outsideВҰ72151 the camp and have \add someone\add* slaughterВҰ72153 it \add вүҲin front of him\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ72157 EleazarВҰ72158 must get some of itsВҰ72170 blood with his fingerВҰ72161 sevenВҰ72171 timesВҰ72172 andВҰ72157 \add вүҲflick\add* it onto the ground \add вүҲdirectly in frontВҰ72165\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ72167\add* tent.
\v 5 ThenВҰ72174 \add вүҲwhile he watches\add*, they must \add completely\add* burnВҰ72191 the heiferВҰ72177вҖ”its skin and fleshВҰ72184, and \add including\add* its bloodВҰ72187 and dung.
\v 6 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the priestВҰ72194 must takeВҰ72193 some cedarВҰ72196 wood, hyssopВҰ72197, and scarletВҰ72199 wool, and throwВҰ72200 them into \add the fire\add* where the cow is burningВҰ72204.
\v 7 ThenВҰ72207 the priest must wash his clothesВҰ72208 andВҰ72207 batheВҰ72210. After that, he can return to the camp, \add вүҲbut\add* \add *he'll\add* be вҖҳuncleanВҰ72218вҖҷ untilВҰ72220 that eveningВҰ72222.
\v 8 The \add man\add* who burnt \add @the cow\add* must \add also\add* wash his clothesВҰ72227 and batheВҰ72229, and he will \add also\add* be вҖҳuncleanВҰ72232вҖҷ untilВҰ72233 that eveningВҰ72235.
\v 9 AВҰ72253 вҖҳcleanвҖҷ manВҰ72239 must collect the cow's ashes andВҰ72237 place them in a \add вүҲsacred\add* place outsideВҰ72245 the camp where they can be used for waterВҰ72255 for purification for the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72251\add* to purify from \add вүҲdisobedience\add*.
\v 10 ThenВҰ72260 that man who collected the ashes must \add also\add* wash his clothesВҰ72268 and be вҖҳuncleanВҰ72269вҖҷ untilВҰ72270 that eveningВҰ72272. ThoseВҰ72275 regulationsВҰ72279 will permanently apply both to \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72274\add* and to foreigners living among them.
\s1 Contact with a corpse
\rem /s1 Contact with a Corpse
\p
\v 11 вҖң вҖҳ\add #All those\add* who touchВҰ72282 a deadВҰ72283, human bodyВҰ72283 will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ72288вҖҷ for sevenВҰ72289 daysВҰ72290.
\v 12 On the third day, they must purify themselves, and then they'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ on the seventh day. (If they don'tВҰ72303 purify themselves, they'll won'tВҰ72303 become вҖҳcleanвҖҷ on that seventh dayвҖ”
\v 13 if they've touchedВҰ72314 a dead, humanВҰ72317 bodyВҰ72316 and don'tВҰ72321 purifyВҰ72322 themselves, that would defile Yahweh's residence, and \add so\add* they must be \add ?вүҲpermanently removed from the camp\add*. If the purifying waterВҰ72333 wasn't sprinkledВҰ72337 on them, that вҖҳuncleannessВҰ72342вҖҷ will remain on them.)
\p
\v 14 вҖң вҖҳThis is the regulation if a person dies in a tent: Everyone who was in the tent, andВҰ72358 everyoneВҰ72352 that enters \add afterwards\add*, will all be вҖҳuncleanВҰ72362вҖҷ for sevenВҰ72363 daysВҰ72364,
\v 15 andВҰ72366 every container thatВҰ72369 doesn't have its lid on becomes вҖҳuncleanВҰ72375вҖҷ.
\v 16 \add вүҲOut in\add* the countrysideВҰ72385, who touchesВҰ72381 the corpse of someone killedВҰ72386 in a fight, or any dead humanВҰ72394 body or bone or graveВҰ72396, will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ72397вҖҷ for sevenВҰ72398 daysВҰ72399.
\v 17 \add вүҲSomeone\add* must takeВҰ72401 some of the ashesВҰ72403 from that burnt cow, andВҰ72401 put them into a jar with some fresh, running waterВҰ72408, thenВҰ72401 \add pour some of it over them\add*.
\v 18 ThenВҰ72414 a man who's вҖҳcleanВҰ72419вҖҷ must dip some hyssopВҰ72415 in that waterВҰ72417 and sprinkleВҰ72420 it onto the tent and all the containers \add in it\add* and everyone who lives in it or who touchedВҰ72438 the body or the bone or graveВҰ72445.
\v 19 On the thirdВҰ72453 day, that вҖҳcleanвҖҷ man must sprinkleВҰ72447 \add вүЎthat waterВҰ72462\add* on the вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ ones, and thenВҰ72447 must purifyВҰ72456 them on the seventh day. ThenВҰ72447 he \add himself\add* must wash his clothesВҰ72460 and batheВҰ72461, and will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ until that eveningВҰ72464.
\p
\v 20 вҖң вҖҳAnyoneВҰ72481 who's вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ andВҰ72466 doesn't purifyВҰ72471 themself, that person will be \add ?вүҲpermanently removed from the camp\add* because they've made Yahweh's sanctuaryВҰ72480 вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ. They didn'tВҰ72470 sprinkleВҰ72487 that purifying waterВҰ72483 on themself, so they \add remain\add* вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\v 21 That will be a \add вүҲpermanent\add* regulationВҰ72495. The person who's had the purifying water sprinkled on them must wash their clothesВҰ72502, andВҰ72492 any person who \add вүҲsprinkles\add* the water will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ72506вҖҷ untilВҰ72507 that eveningВҰ72509.
\v 22 Anything touched by an вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ person becomes вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ, andВҰ72519 anyoneВҰ72519 who touchesВҰ72520 an вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ person will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ72522 that eveningВҰ72524.
\c 20
\s1 Water from the Kadesh rock
\rem /s1 The Waters of Meribah; Events at Kadesh; Moses Strikes the Rock; Water From the Rock
\r (Exo. 17:1-7)
\p
\v 1 Then in the firstВҰ72538 monthВҰ72537 \add of the next year\add*, all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72530\add* entered the TsinВҰ72536 \add (вҖҳThornyвҖҷ or вҖҳThirstyвҖҷ)\add* wildernessВҰ72534 and the people \add вүҲcamped\add* at KadeshВҰ72541. \add While they were\add* there, Miryam died, and was buriedВҰ72545 there.
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲHowever,\add* there was no waterВҰ72551 \add вүҲto drink,\add* \add вүҲso the people\add* came againstВҰ72557 MoshehВҰ72556 andВҰ72548 Aharon\x + \xo 20:2-13: \xt Exo 17:1-7.\x*
\v 3 andВҰ72561 complained, вҖң\add вүҲItВҰ72565 would have been better if we'd diedВҰ72569 in frontВҰ72572 of YahwehВҰ72573 along with ourВҰ72571 relatives\add* \add back there\add*.
\v 4 Why did you two bringВҰ72576 Yahweh's people here to dieВҰ72585 in this wildernessВҰ72583, along with ourВҰ72588 livestockВҰ72588?
\v 5 Why did you bring us out of EgyptВҰ72592 to bring us to this miserable place? There's no \add вүҲgrain\add* or figsВҰ72604, andВҰ72590 no grapes or pomegranatesВҰ72606. There's \add not even\add* waterВҰ72607 to drinkВҰ72609!вҖқ
\v 6 ThenВҰ72611 MoshehВҰ72612 and Aharon wentВҰ72611 from \add there\add* in frontВҰ72614 of the people to the entranceВҰ72618 to the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent, where theyВҰ72621 fell \add вүҲto their knees with their facesВҰ72624 to the ground\add*, and Yahweh's brilliance appearedВҰ72625 to them.
\p
\v 7 Then YahwehВҰ72633 told MoshehВҰ72636,
\v 8 вҖңTake \add &Aharon's\add* staffВҰ72642, then the two of you must command \add that\add* rock to \add вүҲpour out\add* water. Then water will come out of it, and both the people and the animals will \add have plenty to\add* drinkВҰ72664.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ72672\add* MoshehВҰ72673 tookВҰ72672 the staffВҰ72676 from \add вүҲYahweh'sВҰ72678 residence\add* like he was told to.
\v 10 ThenВҰ72682 \add *the two of them\add* gatheredВҰ72682 the people in front of the rock andВҰ72682 told them, вҖңListen now \add вүҲyou bunch of rebelsВҰ72697\add*вҖ”do we have to bringВҰ72702 waterВҰ72704 out of this rock for you?вҖқ
\v 11 ThenВҰ72706 MoshehВҰ72707 raised \add вүҲthe staffВҰ72715\add* and hit the rockВҰ72714 twice, and waterВҰ72718 \add вүҲgushed\add* out, and so the people and theirВҰ72722 animals were able to drink.
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ72726 \add вүҲscolded\add* MoshehВҰ72729 and Aharon, вҖңBecause you two \add вүҲpublicly demonstrated that\add* you didn'tВҰ72734 believeВҰ72736 \add вүҲthat what I say is absolute truth\add*, therefore you two won'tВҰ72734 lead this community into the land that I've givenВҰ72754 them.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲThat spring was named\add* вҖҳMerivahвҖҷ \add (meaning вҖҳQuarrellingвҖҷ)\add* because that was where the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72763\add* argued with YahwehВҰ72768, and \add вүҲwhere he demonstrated his absolute truthfulness to\add* them.
\s1 Edom's king refuses the Israelis' passage
\rem /s1 The King of Edom Refuses to Let Israel Pass; Passage through Edom Refused; The approach to the promised land; Edom Denies Israel Passage; Edom Refuses Israel Passage
\p
\v 14 Then from there in KadeshВҰ72776, MoshehВҰ72774 sentВҰ72773 messengersВҰ72775 to Edom'sВҰ72780 kingВҰ72779 to \add вүҲask\add* him, вҖңThis \add message is from\add* your \add вүҲIsraeli relatives\add*. You \add вүҲare already aware\add* of all the hardshipВҰ72790 \add вүҲthatВҰ72791 we've been through\add*вҖ”
\v 15 \add how\add* our ancestorsВҰ72795 wentВҰ72794 down to EgyptВҰ72796 andВҰ72794 \add вүҲlivedВҰ72797 there for many years\add*, \add вүҲbut thenВҰ72794\add* the Egyptians \add вүҲmistreatedВҰ72801\add* \add *them\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add when\add* we criedВҰ72806 out to YahwehВҰ72809 and he heard \add вүҲus\add* and sentВҰ72812 a messengerВҰ72813 and broughtВҰ72814 us out of EgyptВҰ72815, and now we're in KadeshВҰ72818 town at the \add southern\add* border of your territoryВҰ72821.
\v 17 \add Now\add* pleaseВҰ72825 let us pass through your \add вүҲcountry\add*. We won't goВҰ72837 through the countrysideВҰ72829 or the vineyardsВҰ72830, and we won't drinkВҰ72832 waterВҰ72833 from any well. We'll stay on the king's highway without turning to the rightВҰ72840 or the left, untilВҰ72842 after we've \add вүҲexited\add* at your \add northern\add* border.
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ72848\add* Edom'sВҰ72850 \add king\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңYou can'tВҰ72851 passВҰ72852 through my country. \add вүҲIf you do try to enter\add*, \add вүҲI'll send my swordsmenВҰ72856 out againstВҰ72858 you\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72862 reiterated\add*, вҖңWe'll \add вүҲstay\add* on the highway, andВҰ72860 if we or ourВҰ72880 livestockВҰ72873 drinkВҰ72871 \add any of\add* your waterВҰ72870, thenВҰ72860 we'll \add вүҲpay what it's worth so that's no big deal\add*. \add вүҲJust let us walk\add* throughВҰ72881.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲAgain\add* \add @the king\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ72883\add*, вҖңYou may not passВҰ72885 throughВҰ72885.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ72883 EdomВҰ72887 \add вүҲsent a large, heavily-armed contingent to intimidate them\add*,
\v 21 and because they'd been refusedВҰ72894 passage through their territoryВҰ72902, the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* turnedВҰ72903 around \add and went via a longer, less direct route\add*.
\s1 Aharon's death
\rem /s1 The Death of Aaron
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲSo\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72913\add* left KadeshВҰ72909 and wentВҰ72910 to Mt. HorВҰ72917.
\v 23 \add *There\add* near the EdomВҰ72935 borderВҰ72932, YahwehВҰ72921 told Aharon andВҰ72920 MoshehВҰ72924,
\v 24 вҖңAharon will be \add вүҲtaken to join his ancestors\add* because he won'tВҰ72944 not enter the land that I have givenВҰ72950 to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ72951\add*, because you two rebelledВҰ72956 againstВҰ72956 \add вүҲwhat I said at\add* the MeribahВҰ72961 \add вүҲrock that gaveВҰ72950 waterВҰ72960\add*.
\v 25 Take Aharon and his son EleazarВҰ72969 and \add вүҲclimb\add* up Mt. HorВҰ72973 \add together\add*,
\v 26 thenВҰ72976 remove \add вүҲhis high priest's uniform\add* and put it on his son EleazarВҰ72986. \add вүҲAfter that,\add* Aharon will dieВҰ72990 thereВҰ72991 and go to join his ancestors.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ72993\add* MoshehВҰ72994 \add вүҲfollowed Yahweh's instructions\add* andВҰ72998 \add @the three of them\add* \add вүҲclimbed\add* Mt. HorВҰ73001 as the \add вүҲpeople\add* watched.
\v 28 ThenВҰ73008 Mosheh removed Aharon's \add вүҲuniform\add* and put it on his son Eleazar. Aharon diedВҰ73022 thereВҰ73024 at the top of the mountain, and thenВҰ73008 Mosheh and Eleazar went \add back\add* down.\x + \xo 20:28: \xt Exo 29:29; Num 33:38; Deu 10:6.\x*
\v 29 When the \add вүҲassembled people realised\add* that Aharon had diedВҰ73039, all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ73048\add* mournedВҰ73041 for thirtyВҰ73045 days for him.
\c 21
\s1 The defeat of Canaanites
\rem /s1 Victory over the Canaanites; The Bronze Serpent; Arad Destroyed
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲWhen\add* Kanaanite kingВҰ73054 of AradВҰ73056 who lived by the wilderness, heard that YisraelВҰ73061 was coming on the AtarimВҰ73063 road, he \add вүҲattacked them\add* and capturedВҰ73066 \add вүҲsome prisoners\add*.\x + \xo 21:1: \xt Num 33:40.\x*
\v 2 ThenВҰ73071 the \add вүҲIsraelis promised\add* YahwehВҰ73074, вҖңIf you help us defeat \add *them\add*, thenВҰ73071 we'll \add вүҲcompletely destroyВҰ73085 theirВҰ73088 towns (instead of looting them) as a way of offering them to you\add*.вҖқ
\v 3 Yahweh listenedВҰ73090 to \add вүҲwhat they said\add* and \add вүҲenabled them to defeat\add* those Kanaanites, thenВҰ73090 they dedicated the towns \add to Yahweh\add* and destroyedВҰ73098 them, and they named that area вҖҳHormahВҰ73107вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳDestructionвҖҷ)\add*.
\rem /s1 The Snake Made of Bronze; The Bronze Snake
\p
\v 4 Then they \add all\add* left Mt. HorВҰ73111 by the road \add вүҲgoing towards the Red\add* Sea to goВҰ73117 aroundВҰ73117 EdomВҰ73121, \add вүҲbut\add* the peopleВҰ73125 becameВҰ73122 impatientВҰ73122 on the wayВҰ73126\x + \xo 21:4: \xt Deu 2:1.\x*
\v 5 and they started to grumble against GodВҰ73130 and against MoshehВҰ73131, вҖңWhy did you two bring us \add вүҲout of\add* EgyptВҰ73134 \add just\add* to dieВҰ73135 in the wildernessВҰ73136, because there'sВҰ73138 no bread and no waterВҰ73141, and ourВҰ73142 \add вүҲinsides detest that tasteless\add* вҖҳstuffвҖҷ?вҖқ\x + \xo 21:5-6: \xt 1Cor 10:9.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ73147\add* YahwehВҰ73148 sent \add вүҲpoisonousВҰ73151\add* snakesВҰ73151 into the people, and many \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ73161\add* were bitten and died.
\p
\v 7 The people came to Mosheh and \add вүҲbegged\add*, вҖңWe've \add вүҲdone wrong\add* by speaking out against Yahweh and against you. Pray to Yahweh \add for us\add* to get him to take the snakesВҰ73183 away.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ73163\add* Mosheh prayedВҰ73184 on the peoples' behalf,
\v 8 and YahwehВҰ73190 told \add *him\add*, вҖңMakeВҰ73193 \add a model of\add* a snake and put it \add up\add* on a pole, and \add вүҲso that anyone who gets\add* bittenВҰ73205, can see it and liveВҰ73208.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ73210\add* MoshehВҰ73211 made a snake out of bronze and \add вүҲattached it\add* \add to the top\add* of a pole, and \add вүҲanyoneВҰ73225 who was bittenВҰ73221 by a snake\add* would \add вүҲrecover when\add* they lookedВҰ73226 towards the bronze snake.\x + \xo 21:9: \xt 2Ki 18:4; Yhn 3:14.\x*
\s1 Going around Edom via Moav
\rem /s1 From Mount Hor to the Valley of the Moabites; The Journey to Moab; Israel's Journey to Moab
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ73233 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ73235\add* set off andВҰ73236 campedВҰ73236 at OvotВҰ73237.
\v 11 \add вүҲWhen\add* they left Ovot, they campedВҰ73241 at Iye-Haavarim in the wildernessВҰ73244 \add вүҲnear\add* Moav's eastern border.
\v 12 From thereВҰ73253 theyВҰ73254 set off andВҰ73255 campedВҰ73255 by the Zared riverbed,
\v 13 \add вүҲbefore moving on\add* and camping at \add the north side of\add* the Arnon \add river\add*, in the wildernessВҰ73265 thatВҰ73264 extendsВҰ73266 from the AmoriteВҰ73269 border. (The Arnon is the border between Moav and the AmoritesВҰ73269.
\v 14 That's why it says in the book about Yahweh's battles:
\q1 вҖңVahev in SufahВҰ73289, and the riverbeds there, and the ArnonВҰ73293 River
\q1
\v 15 andВҰ73301 the sloping valleys there,
\q1 thatВҰ73297 extendВҰ73298 to ArВҰ73300 \add вүҲvillage\add* alongВҰ73302 Moav'sВҰ73303 borderВҰ73302.вҖқ)
\p
\v 16 From thereВҰ73305 they went to the well at Be'er \add (whichВҰ73309 means вҖҳWellвҖҷ)\add*, where YahwehВҰ73311 told MoshehВҰ73312, вҖңGather the peopleВҰ73316, andВҰ73317 I'll giveВҰ73317 them waterВҰ73319.вҖқ
\v 17 \add вүҲThat's where the Israelis\add* sang this song:
\q1 вҖң\add вүҲCome on\add*, well,
\q1 sing for \add @this well\add*.
\q1
\v 18 the well dug by the leadersВҰ73337,
\q1 вүҲthe \add вүҲtop citizens\add* dug it out.
\q1 with their sceptresВҰ73341 and their staffsВҰ73342.вҖқ
\p From that wildernessВҰ73343, \add the peopleВҰ73340 went on\add* to MattanahВҰ73344,
\v 19 thenВҰ73346 through NahalielВҰ73347 andВҰ73348 on to BamotВҰ73349
\v 20 andВҰ73351 from \add *there\add* to the valleyВҰ73352 in the Moav countryside \add вүҲwhere Mt. Pisgh rises above\add* the desert.
\s1 Kings Sihon and Og defeated
\rem /s1 Victory over King Sihon and King Og; King Sihon Defeated; Defeat of Sihon and Og; Victory over Sihon and Og
\r (Deu. 2:26вҖ“3:11)
\p
\v 21 Then YisraelВҰ73366 sentВҰ73365 messengersВҰ73367 to the AmoriteВҰ73373 King SihonВҰ73370,
\v 22 вҖңLet us pass throughВҰ73392 your \add вүҲcountry\add*. We won't turn off into any fieldВҰ73380 or vineyardВҰ73381. We won't \add вүҲtake\add* waterВҰ73384 from any well. We'll \add вүҲstay on\add* the king's \add вүҲhighwayВҰ73386\add* untilВҰ73389 we've \add вүҲexited at\add* your \add northern\add* border.вҖқ
\v 23 \add вүҲHowever\add* \add King\add* SihonВҰ73398 \add вүҲrefused them permissionВҰ73397\add*, thenВҰ73395 \add *he\add* \add вүҲtook his whole army\add* into the wildernessВҰ73414 to meet YisraelВҰ73401, andВҰ73395 they attacked \add *them\add* at Yahats \add village\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲNevertheless,\add* YisraelВҰ73421 defeated them \add вүҲin battle\add* andВҰ73420 tookВҰ73425 possessionВҰ73425 of his land from the ArnonВҰ73429 \add river\add* up as far as Yabok \add вүҲwhere the Ammonites' borderВҰ73439 was well fortified\add*.
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ73443\add* YisraelВҰ73444 took those AmoriteВҰ73455 cities \add вүҲincluding\add* Hesbon and \add вүҲthe surrounding villagesВҰ73459\add*, and \add started\add* living in them.
\v 26 (HeshbonВҰ73462 was where the AmoriteВҰ73466 King SihonВҰ73464 lived, as he'd \add previously\add* fought against the formerВҰ73472 king of Moav and \add вүҲcaptured\add* all his land down as far as the ArnonВҰ73482 \add river\add*.
\v 27 That was why the \add вүҲpoetsВҰ73488\add* sayВҰ73487,
\q1 вҖңCome to HeshbonВҰ73490вҖ”let it be rebuiltВҰ73491.
\q1 вүҲLet \add King\add* Sihon'sВҰ73494 cityВҰ73493 be establishedВҰ73492
\q1
\v 28 because fireВҰ73498 wentВҰ73499 out from Hesbon,
\q1 вүҲflameВҰ73501 from Sihon'sВҰ73503 cityВҰ73502.
\q1 It consumedВҰ73504 ArВҰ73505 in Moav,
\q1 \add and\add* the citizensВҰ73507 on Arnon'sВҰ73509 hilltops.\x + \xo 21:28-29: \xt Jer 48:45-46.\x*
\q1
\v 29 Moav, youВҰ73515 \add вүҲwon't end well\add*.
\q1 вүҲKemosh's peopleВҰ73516 have perishedВҰ73515.
\q1 He's made his sonsВҰ73520 into fugitivesВҰ73521,
\q1 вүҲandВҰ73522 given his daughtersВҰ73522 over to captivityВҰ73523
\q1 by the Amorite King SihonВҰ73526.
\q1
\v 30 We've \add ?вүҲoverpowered\add* them.
\q1 Hesbon has perishedВҰ73529 as far as DivonВҰ73533
\q1 вүҲandВҰ73534 shattered NofahВҰ73537 as far as Medeva.)
\p
\v 31 \add вүҲSoВҰ73544 the IsraelisВҰ73545\add* lived in the AmoriteВҰ73547 \add вүҲregion\add*
\v 32 and MoshehВҰ73550 sentВҰ73549 \add some men\add* to spy out YazerВҰ73554, and the capturedВҰ73555 \add вүҲitsВҰ73556 villagesВҰ73556\add* and \add вүҲdrove\add* the AmoritesВҰ73561 out from thereВҰ73564.
\rem /s1 King Og Defeated
\p
\v 33 ThenВҰ73566 they turnedВҰ73566 and went up the road \add towards\add* Bashan, \add вүҲbut\add* Bashan'sВҰ73569 King OgВҰ73571 came out with his army to meet them, and \add вүҲattacked them at\add* EdreiВҰ73581.
\v 34 YahwehВҰ73584 saidВҰ73583 to MoshehВҰ73587, вҖңDon't be afraid of him because I've givenВҰ73594 him and all his peopleВҰ73600 and his land to you, and you'll \add be able to\add* do to him what you did to the AmoriteВҰ73610 King SihonВҰ73608 who lived at HeshbonВҰ73613.вҖқ
\v 35 \add вүҲSoВҰ73615\add* they \add вүҲovercame\add* \add @King Og\add* and his sonsВҰ73619 and all his peopleВҰ73624 untilВҰ73625 there were no remaining survivorsВҰ73631, thenВҰ73615 they tookВҰ73632 possessionВҰ73632 of \add #their\add* land.
\c 22
\s1 King Balak sends for Bileam
\rem /s1 Israel in the plains of Moab; Balak Summons Balaam to Curse Israel; The King of Moab Sends for Balaam; Balak Sends for Balaam; Balak Summons Balaam
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ73637 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ73639\add* set off for the Moav plainsВҰ73641, andВҰ73640 they campedВҰ73640 there across the river from Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\v 2 The \add Moabite King\add* BalakВҰ73649 (Tsipor's son), sawВҰ73648 everything that YisraelВҰ73659 had done to the \add #Amorites\add*,
\v 3 andВҰ73662 when he \add вүҲrealised\add* that the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ73674\add* were very numerousВҰ73668, the Moabite \add people\add* became sick with fear.
\v 4 andВҰ73696 \add *they\add* told the eldersВҰ73681 at Midyan, вҖңNow \add вүҲall that lot\add* will \add вүҲdevour\add* everything that's aroundВҰ73690 us, \add just\add* like a cowВҰ73692 \add вүҲcompletely cleans out\add* a greenВҰ73694 fieldВҰ73695.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲNow\add* Tsipor's son BalakВҰ73696 was Moav's kingВҰ73700 at that timeВҰ73702,
\v 5 and he sentВҰ73705 messengersВҰ73706 to Beor'sВҰ73712 son Bileam \add (BalaamВҰ73709)\add* at PetorВҰ73713 (whichВҰ73714 was their tribal land near the \add Euphrates\add* riverВҰ73717). He \add вүҲrequested help\add*, saying, вҖңListen, \add вүҲthere's a population here\add* thatВҰ73714 came out from EgyptВҰ73729. Wow, they've coveredВҰ73731 the \add вүҲentire surface in this region\add* and they're livingВҰ73737 \add вүҲopposite\add* me.\x + \xo 22:5: \xt Num 31:8; 2Pe 2:15-16; Jude 11.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ73740\add* now pleaseВҰ73743 \add вүҲcomeВҰ73741 and\add* curse this peopleВҰ73749 group for me because they are more numerous than us, \add thenВҰ73740\add* perhapsВҰ73756 I'll be able to \add вүҲattack\add* them and driveВҰ73761 them out of the \add вүҲarea\add*, because I knowВҰ73766 thatВҰ73772 anyone you bless will be blessed, and those who you curse will be cursed.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ73776\add* the elders from Moav and from Midyan departedВҰ73776 \add вүҲcarrying the fees for divinationВҰ73781 with them\add*, and theyВҰ73783 wentВҰ73783 to Bileam and \add вүҲpassed\add* Balak'sВҰ73790 wordsВҰ73789 on to him.
\v 8 \add @Bileam\add* told them, вҖңStay here tonight, and \add in the morning\add*, I'll bringВҰ73797 you back \add вүҲanswer, depending on what\add* YahwehВҰ73802 tels me,вҖқ and \add so\add* the Moav leadersВҰ73805 stayed \add there\add* with Bileam.
\p
\v 9 \add That night,\add* GodВҰ73813 cameВҰ73812 to Bileam andВҰ73817 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWho are those menВҰ73819 with youВҰ73821?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңTsipor's son, King BalakВҰ73828 from Moav sentВҰ73834 me \add <a message\add*,вҖқ Bileam \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 11 вҖң\add He said that\add* \add вүҲshockingly\add* a peopleВҰ73838 group has come out of EgyptВҰ73840 and has coveredВҰ73841 \add вүҲhis region\add*. \add He wants me to\add* go \add and\add* curseВҰ73848 them for \add вүҲhim, so that he'll be able to attack them and driveВҰ73856 them out of that area\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ73858 GodВҰ73859 told Bileam, вҖңDon't goВҰ73864 with themвҖ”you mustn't curseВҰ73867 \add &those\add* peopleВҰ73870, because they're blessedВҰ73872.вҖқ
\v 13 The next morningВҰ73877, Bileam \add вүҲwent over\add* andВҰ73875 told Balak'sВҰ73882 \add вүҲmessengers\add*, вҖңGo \add back\add* to your \add вүҲplace\add*, because YahwehВҰ73889 has refusedВҰ73888 to \add вүҲlet\add* me go with you.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ73894\add* the Moav leadersВҰ73895 \add вүҲstood up\add* and wentВҰ73897 back to \add King\add* BalakВҰ73900, and told \add <him\add*, вҖңBileamВҰ73903 refusedВҰ73902 to comeВҰ73904 with us.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ73909,\add* Balak sent \add back\add* a \add вүҲlarger group of leadersВҰ73911 who were even more senior than the first ones\add*,
\v 16 and they wentВҰ73916 and told Bileam, вҖңTsipor's son \add King\add* BalakВҰ73924 saysВҰ73923, вҖҳPlease don'tВҰ73928 \add вүҲrefuse to come here\add*,
\v 17 because I'll honour you highly and do anything that you tell me to. \add вүҲJust\add* pleaseВҰ73948 comeВҰ73946 and curseВҰ73949 this population for me.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖң\add Even\add* if Balak gave me a housefulВҰ73970 of goldВҰ73972 andВҰ73956 sliver,вҖқ Bileam told Balak'sВҰ73962 servantВҰ73961, вҖңI \add still\add* couldn't goВҰ73975 \add вүҲagainst Yahweh's instructions, even if it was just to do something\add* smallВҰ73982.
\v 19 \add вүҲHowever,\add* pleaseВҰ73988 do stay here tonight, andВҰ73994 \add вүҲI'll find out if YahwehВҰ73998 might have anything else\add* to say to me.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲThat\add* nightВҰ74008, GodВҰ74003 cameВҰ74002 to Bileam and told him, вҖңIf those menВҰ74016 have comeВҰ74015 to summon you, \add вүҲget ready\add* andВҰ74002 goВҰ74018 with them, \add вүҲexcept that you must only give the messageВҰ74023 that I'll tell\add* you.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Balaam's Donkey; Balaam and His Donkey
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ74031\add* in the morningВҰ74033, Bileam \add вүҲgot ready\add* and saddledВҰ74034 his donkeyВҰ74037, and wentВҰ74038 with the Moav leadersВҰ74041.
\s1 The donkey talks
\rem /s1 Balaam and His Donkey; Balaam, the Donkey, and the Angel
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲHowever,\add* GodВҰ74047 \add вүҲgot angry\add* because he'd gone, andВҰ74044 Yahweh's messengerВҰ74053 \add вүҲstood in the middle of the roadВҰ74055 to block them\add*. \add вүҲAs\add* \add @Bileam\add* rode on his donkeyВҰ74062, accompanied by his twoВҰ74063 servantsВҰ74064,
\v 23 the donkey saw Yahweh's messengerВҰ74071 \add вүҲstandingВҰ74073 there holding a swordВҰ74075 in the middle of the road\add* and turnedВҰ74078 off the road and went into a fieldВҰ74084. \add вүҲSoВҰ74067\add* Bileam whacked the donkey and forced it back onto the road.
\v 24 ThenВҰ74093 Yahweh'sВҰ74095 messengerВҰ74094 moved to a place where the road was very narrowВҰ74096, with vineyardВҰ74097 walls on each side of the road.
\v 25 \add вүҲWhen\add* the donkeyВҰ74104 sawВҰ74103 Yahweh's messengerВҰ74107, it \add вүҲsqueezed\add* close by the wall, andВҰ74103 \add in doing so\add*, \add вүҲsquashed\add* Bileam's footВҰ74116 against the wall, \add вүҲso\add* he whacked it again.
\v 26 ThenВҰ74124 Yahweh'sВҰ74127 messengerВҰ74125 went past again andВҰ74124 stoodВҰ74129 in a narrowВҰ74131 placeВҰ74130 on the road whereВҰ74132 thereВҰ74133 was no \add roomВҰ74130\add* to \add вүҲget past on either side\add*.
\v 27 \add This time, when\add* the donkey saw the messengerВҰ74144, it lay down on the ground with Bileam sitting on top of it. Bileam \add вүҲgot very angry\add* andВҰ74140 whacked the donkey again with his staffВҰ74157.
\v 28 ThenВҰ74159 YahwehВҰ74160 \add вүҲenabled the donkeyВҰ74164 to speak, andВҰ74165 it asked\add* Bileam, вҖңWhat did I do to you that you beat me these threeВҰ74174 times?вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖңBecause \add вүҲyou've been messing me around\add*!вҖқ Bileam \add вүҲshouted\add*. вҖңIf only \add вүҲI'd been carrying a swordВҰ74186, thenВҰ74177 I would have killed\add* you!вҖқ
\p
\v 30 вҖңAren't I your donkey that you've riddenВҰ74202 \add вүҲall your life\add*?вҖқ the donkey \add вүҲasked\add* Bileam. вҖңHave I ever \add вүҲdone anything like that to you before\add*?вҖқ
\p And he said, вҖңNo.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ74217 Yahweh uncovered Bileam's eyesВҰ74221 and he sawВҰ74223 Yahweh's messengerВҰ74226 standingВҰ74228 \add in the middle of\add* the roadВҰ74229 with his swordВҰ74230 in his handВҰ74232, and \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲfell to his knees and kept bowing his faceВҰ74235 to the ground\add*.
\v 32 Yahweh's angel \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖң\add вүҲWhy did you strikeВҰ74244 you donkeyВҰ74247 those threeВҰ74249 times? Listen, I cameВҰ74253 personally to oppose you\add* because \add вүҲyou're choosing a very dangerous pathВҰ74258 as far as I'm concernedВҰ74241\add*.
\v 33 Your donkey saw me andВҰ74261 \add вүҲavoided me\add* those threeВҰ74266 timesвҖ”if it hadn't I certainly would have killedВҰ74276 you already, \add вүҲbut I would have let the donkey live\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\add Yes,\add* I've \add вүҲdone wrong\add*,вҖқ Bileam saidВҰ74280 to Yahweh's messengerВҰ74284, вҖңbecause I didn'tВҰ74288 know that you were \add вүҲwaiting\add* for me \add there\add* on the roadВҰ74294. \add вүҲButВҰ74280\add* now, if \add вүҲyou don'tВҰ74288 want me to continue\add*, I'll return \add вүҲhome again\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 35 вҖң\add вүҲContinue on\add* with those menВҰ74312,вҖқ Yahweh's angel told Bileam, вҖң\add вүҲbut make sure that you only pass on the messageВҰ74316 that I give\add* you.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ74303\add* Bileam \add вүҲcarried on\add* with Balak'sВҰ74328 leadersВҰ74327.
\s1 Balak welcomes Bileam
\rem /s1 Balak Welcomes Balaam
\p
\v 36 \add вүҲWhen\add* \add King\add* BalakВҰ74331 heard that Bileam was coming, he wentВҰ74335 out to meeting him at a cityВҰ74339 in Moav that was on his borderВҰ74344 beside the ArnonВҰ74345 \add river\add*.
\v 37 \add *He\add* \add вүҲasked\add* Bileam, вҖңDidn't I send \add вүҲan urgentВҰ74356 message\add* to summon you? Why didn'tВҰ74355 you comeВҰ74365 \add thenВҰ74350\add*? \add вүҲDid you think I couldn't pay you enough\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 38 вҖңLook, I've comeВҰ74379 \add now\add*,вҖқ Bileam \add вүҲanswered\add* BalakВҰ74376, вҖң\add вүҲbut can I say whatever I want\add*? \add No,\add* \add вүҲI have to deliver\add* whatever messageВҰ74386 GodВҰ74389 \add вүҲgives me\add*.вҖқ
\v 39 \add SoВҰ74394\add* thenВҰ74394 Bileam wentВҰ74394 to Kiryat-Hutsot with BalakВҰ74398,
\v 40 \add вүҲwhere\add* BalakВҰ74404 sacrificedВҰ74403 sheepВҰ74406 and cattleВҰ74405, and \add вүҲgave\add* \add some of the meat\add* to BileamВҰ74408 and to the leaders who were with \add #them\add*.
\rem /s1 Balaam's First Prophecy; Balaam's First Oracle
\v 41 \add вүҲThe next\add* morningВҰ74414, BalakВҰ74416 tookВҰ74415 Bileam uphill to BamotВҰ74421-BaalВҰ74422, andВҰ74413 from thereВҰ74424 \add @they\add* could see the outskirtsВҰ74425 of the \add вүҲIsraeli camp\add*.
\c 23
\s1 Bileam blesses Yisrael
\rem /s1 Balaam's First Oracle; Balaam Blesses Israel
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ74428 Bileam saidВҰ74428 to \add King\add* BalakВҰ74432, вҖң\add Get them to\add* buildВҰ74433 seven altarsВҰ74438 for me \add вүҲhere\add*, and prepareВҰ74439 me seven bullsВҰ74443 and seven rams.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ74447\add* BalakВҰ74448 did what Bileam had \add вүҲinstructed\add*, thenВҰ74447 \add вүҲthe two of them\add* offered up a bullВҰ74455 andВҰ74447 a ram on \add each\add* altarВҰ74457.
\v 3 Then Bileam told BalakВҰ74461, вҖң\add вүҲYou standВҰ74462 here beside\add* your burntВҰ74465 offeringВҰ74465, and I'll \add вүҲmove away\add*. Perhaps YahwehВҰ74469 will \add вүҲwant\add* to meet me, and thenВҰ74459 I'll \add вүҲtell you whateverВҰ74472\add* he showsВҰ74474 me.вҖқ Then he wentВҰ74477 to a bare hilltop
\v 4 \add вүҲwhere\add* GodВҰ74481 met \add *him\add*, and \add @Bileam\add* told him, вҖңI \add вүҲorganised\add* sevenВҰ74489 altars and offeredВҰ74492 up a bullВҰ74493 and a ram on \add each\add* altar.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ74497 YahwehВҰ74498 \add вүҲgave Bileam a messageВҰ74499\add* and told \add <him\add*, вҖңGo back to BalakВҰ74506 and tell \add <him\add* that.вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ74510\add* he went back to \add @Balak\add* \add вүҲwho\add* was \add вүҲstill\add* standingВҰ74513 by his burntВҰ74516 offeringВҰ74516 \add вүҲalong with\add* all of Moav'sВҰ74521 officials.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ74523\add* \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲgave his pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖң\add It's\add* BalakВҰ74530 has broughtВҰ74529 me \add here\add* from AramВҰ74528.
\q1 вүҲMoav's kingВҰ74531 \add вүЎsummoned me\add* from the easternВҰ74536 mountainsВҰ74534.
\q1 вҖҳGo curseВҰ74538 Yakov \add (Jacob)\add* for me,
\q1 вүҲandВҰ74523 go denounceВҰ74543 YisraelВҰ74544.вҖҷ
\q1
\v 8 How can I curse those who GodВҰ74550 hasn't cursed?
\q1 вүҲHow can I denounce those who YahwehВҰ74555 hasn't denounced?
\q1
\v 9 \add вүҲYes,\add* I can seeВҰ74561 \add #them\add* from the top of \add those\add* rocksВҰ74560.
\q1 вүҲI look at \add #them\add* from the hillsВҰ74562.
\q1 Look, a population that lives by itself.
\q1 вүҲIt doesn't count itself among the \add other\add* nationsВҰ74569.
\q1
\v 10 Who can count the dust that Yakov \add leaves behind\add*?
\q1 вүҲ\add вүЎWho can even\add* count a quarter of the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ74580\add*?
\q1 Let me dieВҰ74582 like \add those\add* honourable \add >people\add*,
\q1 вүҲand let my endВҰ74587 be like \add #theirs\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ74590\add* BalakВҰ74591 \add вүҲdemanded from\add* Bileam, вҖңWhat have you done to me? I broughtВҰ74600 you \add here\add* to curseВҰ74598 my enemiesВҰ74599, andВҰ74590 \add вүҲblast it all\add*вҖ”you've actuallyВҰ74603 blessedВҰ74602 \add <them\add*!вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңShouldn't I be careful to \add only\add* say \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ74611 tells me\add*?вҖқ Bileam \add вүҲansweredВҰ74605 back\add*.
\s1 Bileam's second blessing
\rem /s1 Balaam's Second Prophecy; Balaam's Second Oracle
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ74617 \add King\add* BalakВҰ74619 told \add @Bileam\add*, вҖңPlease come with me to anotherВҰ74628 placeВҰ74627 \add вүҲthat you'll be able to see them from\add*. You won'tВҰ74636 \add be able to\add* see all of \add #them\add*, only the edge \add of that large group\add*, \add вүҲbut\add* you'll will curseВҰ74638 \add @Yisrael\add* for me from there.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ74643\add* he tookВҰ74643 \add @Bileam\add* to a fieldВҰ74644 at the top of \add Mt.\add* PisgahВҰ74649, and he builtВҰ74650 sevenВҰ74651 altars and offered up a bullВҰ74654 and a ram on \add each\add* altar.
\p
\v 15 Bileam saidВҰ74658 to \add вүҲthe king\add*, вҖңYou standВҰ74662 here beside your burntВҰ74666 offeringВҰ74666, while I \add вүҲgo over there so\add* \add Yahweh\add* \add вүҲcan meet me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ74671 YahwehВҰ74672 met with Bileam and \add вүҲgave him a message\add* and told \add >him\add*, вҖңGo back to BalakВҰ74683, and \add вүҲgive him that message\add*.вҖқ
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ74687\add* he \add вүҲreturned\add* to him where he was standingВҰ74690 with the leaders from MoavВҰ74695 beside the altar, andВҰ74687 BalakВҰ74699 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңWhat did YahwehВҰ74703 say?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ74705 \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲgave his speech\add*,
\q1 вҖң\add вүҲLook here\add*, BalakВҰ74709, andВҰ74705 listenВҰ74711.
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲPay attention\add* to me, son of Tsipor.
\q1
\v 19 GodВҰ74718 doesn't lie because he's not a humanВҰ74717 being,
\q1 вүҲand he's not a mortal who might changeВҰ74723 his mind.
\q1 Whatever he's saidВҰ74725, he'll do it.
\q1 вүҲAnything he \add вүҲpromised\add*, he'll make it \add вүҲhappen\add*.
\q1
\v 20 Listen, I've receivedВҰ74734 \add a command\add* to bless.
\q1 вүҲ\add Yes,\add* he's \add decided to\add* bless and I can'tВҰ74736 reverse itВҰ74737.
\p
\v 21 \add @YahwehВҰ74749\add* hasn't \add вүҲconsidered\add* hardship for Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*,
\q1 вүҲand he hasn't seenВҰ74746 troubleВҰ74747 for YisraelВҰ74748 \add (IsraelВҰ74748)\add*.
\q1 His godВҰ74750 Yahweh is with \add @that people group\add*,
\q1 and the king's shoutВҰ74752 is over him.
\q1
\v 22 GodВҰ74756 brought them out of EgyptВҰ74758 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*,
\q1 вҶ’\add giving them strength\add* like a wild bull's hornsВҰ74759.
\q1
\v 23 \add вүҲNo,\add* there's no spell against Yakov,
\q1 вүҲand no divinationВҰ74770 against Yisrael.
\q1 \add People\add* will talk about Yakov/Yisrael,
\q1 вҶ’\add saying look\add* what GodВҰ74779 has done.
\q1
\v 24 That population stands up like a lionessВҰ74784,
\q1 вүҲand like a lionВҰ74786, it liftsВҰ74787 itselfВҰ74787 up.
\q1 It won'tВҰ74788 lie down untilВҰ74790 it's devourВҰ74792 its prey
\q1 and drunk the bloodВҰ74794 of thoseВҰ74796 it killed.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ74799 \add King\add* BalakВҰ74800 \add вүҲscolded\add* Bileam, вҖңEven \add вүҲif you won'tВҰ74807\add* curse them, definitely don'tВҰ74807 \em bless\em* them!вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңDidn't I \add already\add* tell youВҰ74823,вҖқ BileamВҰ74816 answeredВҰ74815 BalakВҰ74820, вҖң\add вүҲthat I can only pronounce what YahwehВҰ74829 tells me to\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Bileam's third prophecy
\rem /s1 Balaam's Third Prophecy; Balaam's Third Oracle
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ74833 \add King\add* BalakВҰ74834 told Bileam, вҖңCome \add вүҲwith me\add*. I'll takeВҰ74841 you to anotherВҰ74845 placeВҰ74844. Perhaps it will \add вүҲpleasedВҰ74840\add* God \add вүҲif\add* you curseВҰ74850 \add #them\add* for me from thereВҰ74852.вҖқ
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ74854\add* BalakВҰ74855 tookВҰ74854 \add *him\add* to the top of \add MtВҰ74858.\add* PeorВҰ74860 \add вүҲthat faces down\add* to the wilderness,
\v 29 and \add again\add* Bileam told \add *him\add*, вҖңBuild seven altarsВҰ74877 and prepareВҰ74878 seven bullsВҰ74882 and seven rams for me \add вүҲhere\add*.вҖқ
\v 30 \add вүҲSoВҰ74886\add* BalakВҰ74887 \add вүҲfollowed those instructions\add* and offered a bullВҰ74892 and a ram on \add each\add* altarВҰ74894.
\c 24
\rem /s1 Balaam's Third Oracle
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲBy now,\add* Bileam \add вүҲhad realised\add* that YahwehВҰ74901 wanted to blessВҰ74902 \add вүҲthe Israelis\add*, \add вүҲso\add* he didn'tВҰ74906 \add вүҲuse his usual divinations\add* \add вүҲbut instead, he just looked towards\add* the wildernessВҰ74917.
\v 2 He \add вүҲlooked up\add* andВҰ74920 sawВҰ74925 YisraelВҰ74928 \add вүҲin their tents laid out by tribeВҰ74930\add*. ThenВҰ74920 God's spiritВҰ74933 came onto him,
\v 3 andВҰ74936 he \add вүҲmade his pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖң\add This is\add* the declaration of Bileam, son of BeorВҰ74942вҖ”
\q1 вүҲthe utteranceВҰ74936 of a manВҰ74944 whose eyes are open.
\q1
\v 4 The declaration of someone who heard God's message,
\q1 вүҲsomeone who seesВҰ74956 the all-powerful one's visionВҰ74954,
\q1 who bows to the ground with his eyesВҰ74959 \add вүҲwide open\add*.
\q1
\v 5 \add вүҲYes\add* Yakov, your tentsВҰ74964 look goodВҰ74963.
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲYes\add* YisraelВҰ74967, \add вүҲthe places where you're living\add*:
\q1
\v 6 They stretchВҰ74970 out like a riverbed.
\q1 вүҲLike gardensВҰ74971 beside a riverВҰ74973.
\q1 Like \add вүҲpalms\add* thatВҰ74970 YahwehВҰ74976 has plantedВҰ74975,
\q1 вүҲLike cedarВҰ74977 \add trees\add* beside the watersВҰ74980.
\q1
\v 7 Water will \add вүҲspill over the top of\add* his bucketsВҰ74985,
\q1 and his \add вүҲdescendants will flow out\add* like water.
\q1 \add @Yisrael's\add* kingВҰ74991 will be greater than \add King\add* AgagВҰ74990,
\q1 and his kingdomВҰ74993 will become honoured.
\q1
\v 8 GodВҰ74995 is bringingВҰ74996 him \add here\add* from EgyptВҰ74997
\q1 \add with power\add* like the hornsВҰ74998 of a wild bullВҰ74999.
\q1 He'll \add вүҲdevastate\add* those nationsВҰ75002 \add вүҲthat oppose him\add*.
\q1 He'll breakВҰ75005 theirВҰ75004 bonesВҰ75004, and hisВҰ74996 arrowsВҰ75006 will pierce them.
\q1
\v 9 He crouchedВҰ75009вҖ”lying down like a lionВҰ75011 or a lionessВҰ75012.
\q1 Who will rouseВҰ75014 himВҰ75014?
\q1 Those who bless, you will be blessed,
\q1 ^\add вүҲbut\add* those who curse you, will be cursed.\x + \xo 24:9: a \xt Gen 49:9; \xo b \xt Gen 12:3.\x*
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ75020 \add King\add* BalakВҰ75023 \add вүҲgot very angry\add* with Bileam, and he banged his handsВҰ75030 togetherВҰ75027 and saidВҰ75031 \add angrily\add*, вҖңI called you to \em curseВҰ75036\em* my enemiesВҰ75037, and \add вүҲblast you\add*, you've actuallyВҰ75041 blessedВҰ75040 \add <them\add* threeВҰ75043 timesВҰ75044 \add now\add*!
\v 11 \add вүҲNow get back to where you came from\add*! I said that I'd honour you \add вүҲvery well\add*, but man, YahwehВҰ75058 has kept you from any honour!вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲButВҰ75061\add* Bileam \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңDidn't I also tell the messengersВҰ75070 that youВҰ75073 sentВҰ75073 to me that
\v 13 even if you gave me a houseВҰ75085 full of goldВҰ75087 andВҰ75087 siler, I wouldn't be able \add вүҲto say anything other than what Yahweh tells me\add*вҖ”whether goodВҰ75096 or evil? Whatever Yahweh tells me, that's what I have to say.
\rem /s1 Balaam's Final Prophecies
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ75107 yes,\add* I'llВҰ75108 go back home now, \add вүҲbut first, allow me\add* to tell you what thatВҰ75113 people group will do to your people in the future.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Balaam's Final Prophecies; Balaam's Fourth Oracle
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ75121 Bileam gave this pronouncement to Balak,
\q1 вҖң\add This is\add* the declaration of Bileam, son of BeorВҰ75127вҖ”
\q1 вүҲthe utteranceВҰ75121 of a manВҰ75129 whose eyes are open.
\q1
\v 16 The statement from someone who hearsВҰ75134 God's messages,
\q1 вүҲand the one who receives knowledgeВҰ75139 from the highest one,
\q1 who seesВҰ75143 visionsВҰ75141 from the powerful one.
\q1 вүҲThe one who fallsВҰ75144 to his knees with his eyesВҰ75146 opened.
\q1
\v 17 I seeВҰ75151 him, \add вүҲbut\add* not now.
\q1 вүҲI'll look at him, \add вүҲbut\add* he's not close.
\q1 A starВҰ75155 has marchedВҰ75154 out from Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*,
\q1 вүҲand a staff has risen from YisraelВҰ75159 \add (IsraelВҰ75159)\add*.
\q1 He will crushВҰ75160 Moav's cornersВҰ75161,
\q1 вүҲand destroy all of Shet's \add (Seth's)\add* descendantsВҰ75166.
\q1
\v 18 EdomВҰ75171 will become \add &their\add* possession,
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲas will\add* his enemy, SeirВҰ75175.
\q1 YisraelВҰ75177 \add вүҲwill project\add* strengthВҰ75179.
\q1
\v 19 A ruler \add will come\add* from Yakov,
\q1 вҶ’and destroyВҰ75183 the city's survivorsВҰ75184.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Balaam's Final Oracles
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ75187 \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲlooked towards\add* AmalekВҰ75190 andВҰ75187 \add вүҲmade this pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖңAmalek is the firstВҰ75194 of the nationsВҰ75195,
\q2 ^\add вүҲbut\add* its endВҰ75197 will be destructionВҰ75199.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ75201 he \add вүҲlooked towards\add* the Kenites and \add вүҲmade this pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖңYour dwellingВҰ75209 is permanent,
\q1 вүҲand your nest is set in the cliffs.
\q1
\v 22 but you Kenites will be destroyedВҰ75218
\q1 when Ashhur \add ?(the Assyrians)\add* take you captiveВҰ75224.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ75226 \add finally,\add* \add @Bileam\add* \add вүҲmade this pronouncement\add*,
\q1 вҖңOh dear, who can \add вүҲsurvive\add* when GodВҰ75233 does \add all\add* that?
\q1
\v 24 Ships will come from the KittimВҰ75237 coastВҰ75236 \add (Cyprus)\add*,
\q1 and they'll \add вүҲdamage\add* AsshurВҰ75239 and Ever,
\q1 \add вүҲbut they themselves\add* will be destroyedВҰ75247 as well.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ75249 Bileam \add вүҲpacked up\add* and went home, and \add King\add* BalakВҰ75256 also went on his wayВҰ75258.
\c 25
\s1 Yisrael worships Baal at Peor
\rem /s1 Moab Seduces Israel; The People of Israel at Peor; Worship of Baal of Peor
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* \add вүҲthe Israelis settled down\add* at ShittimВҰ75263, and \add вүҲtheir men started sleeping with women from Moav\add*
\v 2 \add вүҲwho thenВҰ75272\add* invitedВҰ75272 them to sacrificesВҰ75274 to their \add вүҲidols\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ75272\add* \add @the Israelis\add* bowedВҰ75278 down \add to the idols\add* andВҰ75272 ateВҰ75276 \add at the feasts\add*,
\v 3 andВҰ75286 \add when\add* YisraelВҰ75283 consecrated themselves to BaalВҰ75284-PeorВҰ75285, Yahweh's angerВҰ75288 burned towards \add *them\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ75292 Yahweh told MoshehВҰ75296, вҖң\add вүҲExecute\add* all the people'sВҰ75303 leaders and \add вүҲdisplay their bodies in broad daylight\add*, and thenВҰ75292 Yahweh's \add вүҲangerВҰ75311\add* might turnВҰ75309 back away from YisraelВҰ75314.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ75316\add* MoshehВҰ75317 to Yisrael's judgesВҰ75320, вҖң\add вүҲEach of you must execute your menВҰ75324 who have joinedВҰ75325 others to serve\add* BaalВҰ75326-PeorВҰ75327.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲJust thenВҰ75329, unbelievably,\add* an \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ75332\add* manВҰ75330 \add вүҲcame past\add* MoshehВҰ75342 and \add вүҲall the peopleВҰ75347\add* who were \add there outside\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ75353\add* tent weepingВҰ75351, and he was bringing a Midyanite woman \add вүҲwith him\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhen\add* Pinehas (son of EleazarВҰ75360, son of Aharon) sawВҰ75356 \add <that\add*, he \add вүҲcame out\add* from among the \add вүҲgathered people\add*, grabbed a spearВҰ75369,
\v 8 and followed the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ75374\add* man into \add &his\add* tent. He \add вүҲplunged\add* the spear through the two of themвҖ”right through the man and the woman'sВҰ75389 bellyВҰ75392, and \add thus\add*, stoppedВҰ75393 the plagueВҰ75394 \add that had started\add* against the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ75374\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲHowever,\add*, twenty-four thousandВҰ75404 people had \add already\add* diedВҰ75400 from the plagueВҰ75401.
\p
\v 10 Then YahwehВҰ75408 spokeВҰ75407 to MoshehВҰ75411,
\v 11 вҖңAharon's grandson Pinehas has \add вүҲdeflected my angerВҰ75425\add* from the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ75427\add* by \add вүҲdemonstrating my seriousness about theirВҰ75434 behaviour\add*, \add вүҲso now\add* in my zeal, I won'tВҰ75435 \add вүҲeliminate the Israelis\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲSo\add* tell him that I'm \add вүҲmaking\add* a peaceВҰ75453 agreement with him.
\v 13 It'sВҰ75470 an agreement that gives him and his \add вүҲdescendantsВҰ75457\add* \add вүҲthe rights to be priestsВҰ75460\add* becauseВҰ75462 he was zealousВҰ75464 \add вүҲon his god's behalf\add* and he \add вүҲworked towards removing the guilt\add* of the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ75469\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 The \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ75473\add* manВҰ75473 \add вүҲwho was killed\add* with the Midyanite woman was Salu'sВҰ75484 son ZimriВҰ75481, a \add вүҲclan leaderВҰ75485\add* from the Shimeon tribe.
\v 15 The Midyanite womanВҰ75492 \add вүҲwho was killed\add* was Kozbi, the daughterВҰ75496 of TsurВҰ75498, a Midyanite clan leader.
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehВҰ75509 told MoshehВҰ75512,
\v 17 вҖң\add вүҲAttack\add* the Midyanites andВҰ75519 \add вүҲdestroy\add* them
\v 18 because they were \add вүҲtreacherously deceiving\add* you all over the matter of Peor and Kozbi, the daughterВҰ75540 of one of their leadersВҰ75542 who was killedВҰ75545 on the dayВҰ75546 of the plagueВҰ75548 at \add Mt.\add* Peor.вҖқ
\c 26
\s1 The second census
\rem /s1 The Second Census; A Census of the New Generation; Israel's Second Census
\p
\v 1 After \add the incident of\add* the plague, YahwehВҰ75562 told MoshehВҰ75565 and Aharon's son EleazarВҰ75567 the priestВҰ75571,\x + \xo 26:1-51: \xt Num 1:1-46.\x*
\v 2 вҖң\add вүҲCountВҰ75595 all the IsraeliВҰ75582 peopleВҰ75582\add* \add again\add* \add вүҲlisting all those by theirВҰ75590 clans\add* who're twentyВҰ75586 and over, and \add вүҲcapable of going out to battle\add* for YisraelВҰ75584.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ75597\add* there in the Moav plainsВҰ75602, across the YardenВҰ75606 river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*, MoshehВҰ75598 andВҰ75599 the priestВҰ75600 EleazarВҰ75599 \add вүҲgave these instructions\add* to \add @the people\add*,
\v 4 вҖңYahwehВҰ75616 has orderedВҰ75615 \add *us\add* \add вүҲto list\add* the names of the \add men\add* who cameВҰ75622 out from EgyptВҰ75624 who're twentyВҰ75611 years old or older.
\s1 Reuven's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Reuben
\v 5 Reuven was Yisrael's eldest son, and his descendantsВҰ75629 came via his sons Hanok, PalluВҰ75634,
\v 6 Hetsron, and Karmi.
\v 7 ThoseВҰ75647 clansВҰ75646 added up to 43,730 men.
\v 8 Pallu'sВҰ75659 son was EliavВҰ75660,
\v 9 and Eliav's son were NemuelВҰ75664, Datan, and Aviram. (That was the Datan and Aviram who were the leaders that rebelled\x + \xo 26:9 \xt 16:1-33.\x* against MoshehВҰ75678 and Aharon when they joined Korah'sВҰ75684 rebellion against YahwehВҰ75688.
\v 10 ThenВҰ75690 the earthВҰ75691 \add вүҲsplit open\add* and swallowedВҰ75695 them and KorahВҰ75699. Yahweh had also sent a fireВҰ75703 that consumed 250 men, and theyВҰ75708 became a warningВҰ75709 sign.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Korah'sВҰ75713 descendants hadn't diedВҰ75716 \add thenВҰ75711\add*.)
\s1 Shimeon's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Simeon
\p
\v 12 Shimeon's descendantsВҰ75719 came via his sons NemuelВҰ75722, YaminВҰ75725, Yakin,
\v 13 Zerah, and ShaulВҰ75735.
\v 14 ThoseВҰ75741 clansВҰ75740 added up to 22,200 men.
\s1 Gad's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Gad
\p
\v 15 Gad'sВҰ75749 descendantsВҰ75748 came via his sons Tsefon, HaggitВҰ75754, ShuniВҰ75757,
\v 16 OzniВҰ75763, Eir,
\v 17 Arod, and AreliВҰ75771.
\v 18 ThoseВҰ75779 clansВҰ75776 added up to 40,500 men.
\s1 Yehudah's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Judah
\p
\v 19 YehudahВҰ75788 \add (Judah)\add* had two sonsВҰ75787 ErВҰ75789 and OnanВҰ75790 who diedВҰ75791 \add childless\add* in Kenaan.
\v 20 \add *His\add* descendantsВҰ75798 came via his \add other\add* sons ShelahВҰ75802, Perets, andВҰ75797 ZerahВҰ75808.
\v 21 Perets's descendantsВҰ75813 \add came via his sons\add* Hetsron andВҰ75812 HamulВҰ75819.
\v 22 ThoseВҰ75825 clansВҰ75824 added up to 76,500 men.
\s1 Yissakar's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Issachar
\p
\v 23 Yissakar's \add (Issachar'sВҰ75835)\add* descendantsВҰ75834 came via his sons TolaВҰ75837, PuahВҰ75840,
\v 24 Yashuv, and ShimronВҰ75847.
\v 25 ThoseВҰ75853 clansВҰ75852 added up to 64,300 men.
\s1 Zevulun's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Zebulun
\p
\v 26 Zevulun's descendantsВҰ75862 came via his sons SeredВҰ75865, Eylon, and Yahle'el.
\v 27 ThoseВҰ75877 clansВҰ75876 added up to 60,500 men.
\s1 Menashsheh's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Manasseh
\p
\v 28 Yosef'sВҰ75886 \add (Joseph's)\add* descendants came via his sonsВҰ75885 Menashsheh \add (ManassehВҰ75888)\add* andВҰ75889 Efrayim.
\v 29 Menashsheh's descendantsВҰ75891 came from his son MakirВҰ75893 andВҰ75896 then his son GileadВҰ75900.
\v 30 Gilead'sВҰ75907 descendantsВҰ75906 came via his sons IezerВҰ75908, HelekВҰ75911,
\v 31 Asriel, Shekem,
\v 32 Shemida, andВҰ75925 HeferВҰ75925.
\v 33 Hefer'sВҰ75932 son Tselofehad had no sonsвҖ”only daughters named MahlahВҰ75945, NoahВҰ75946, HoglahВҰ75947, MilcahВҰ75948, andВҰ75929 Tirtsah.
\v 34 ThoseВҰ75953 clansВҰ75952 added up to 52,700 men.
\s1 Efrayim's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Ephraim
\p
\v 35 Efrayim's descendantsВҰ75963 came via his sons ShutelahВҰ75967, BekerВҰ75970, and TahanВҰ75973,
\v 36 Shutelah'sВҰ75979 descendantsВҰ75978 came via his son EranВҰ75980.
\v 37 Those clans added up to 32,500 men. TheseВҰ75984 last twoВҰ75990 totals were \add all\add* Yosef's \add (Joseph's)\add* descendants.
\s1 Benyamin's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Benjamin
\p
\v 38 Benyamin'sВҰ76003 descendantsВҰ76002 came via his sons BelaВҰ76005, AshbelВҰ76008, Ahiram,
\v 39 Shefufam, and HufamВҰ76018.
\v 40 Bela'sВҰ76025 descendantsВҰ76023 came via his sons ArdВҰ76026 andВҰ76027 NaamanВҰ76027.
\v 41 ThoseВҰ76037 clansВҰ76038 added up to 45,600 men.
\s1 Dan's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Dan
\p
\v 42 Dan'sВҰ76050 descendantsВҰ76048 came via his son ShuhamВҰ76052.
\v 43 ThatВҰ76063 clan had 64,400 men.
\s1 Asher's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Asher
\p
\v 44 Asher'sВҰ76073 descendantsВҰ76072 came via his sons Yimnah, YishviВҰ76078, and BeriahВҰ76081.
\v 45 Beriah'sВҰ76086 descendantsВҰ76085 came via his sons Hever and Malkiel.
\v 46 Asher'sВҰ76097 daughterВҰ76095 was named SerahВҰ76098.
\v 47 ThoseВҰ76104 clansВҰ76101 added up to 53,400 men.
\s1 Naftali's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Naphtali
\p
\v 48 Naftali'sВҰ76114 descendantsВҰ76113 came via his sons Yahtse'el, GuniВҰ76119,
\v 49 Yetser, and ShillemВҰ76126.
\v 50 ThoseВҰ76132 clans added up to 45,400 men.
\s1 The census total and the division of land
\rem /s1 The Census Results
\p
\v 51 TheВҰ76144 total of all those tribes counted came to 601,730 men.\f + \fr 26:51 \ft Slightly smaller than the total of 603,550 from the first census, see \xt 1:46.\f*
\p
\v 52 Then YahwehВҰ76156 told MoshehВҰ76159,\x + \xo 26:52-56: \xt Num 34:13; Josh 14:1-2.\x*
\v 53 вҖңThe land should be allocated to those \add clans\add* according to the numberВҰ76166 of their namesВҰ76167, to become their inheritanceВҰ76165.
\v 54 Those with largerВҰ76169 numbers should receive more, andВҰ76172 the smallerВҰ76172 groups receive less, \add i.e.,\add* each inheritance \add вүҲdepends on the number of family members\add*.
\v 55 \add вүҲYou must throw\add* lots to determine \add вүҲwhich clan gets which piece of land\add*. \add вүҲThe lands of the clans must be within theirВҰ76191 tribal lands\add*.
\v 56 \add вүҲThen the size of the area that will become\add* their inheritanceВҰ76199 must be apportioned according to the \add вүҲcensus numbers\add*.
\s1 Levi's descendants
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Levi
\p
\v 57 The listed LevitesВҰ76207 included the clansВҰ76208 \add from Levi's sons\add* GershonВҰ76209, KohatВҰ76212, andВҰ76205 MerariВҰ76215,
\v 58 which were the Livnites, the Hevronites, the Mahlites, the Mushites, andВҰ76233 the Korahites. \add вүҲAlso,\add* Korah fatheredВҰ76234 AmramВҰ76237
\v 59 \add *whose\add* wifeВҰ76241 was Levi'sВҰ76246 daughterВҰ76244 Yokeved who'd been born in EgyptВҰ76251. \add #They\add* had two sons Aharon \add (AaronВҰ76256)\add* and MoshehВҰ76259 \add (MosesВҰ76259)\add*, and theirВҰ76262 \add older\add* sisterВҰ76262 Miryam \add (MiriamВҰ76261)\add*.
\v 60 Aharon's \add вүҲsons were\add* Nadav, Avihu, EleazarВҰ76274, andВҰ76264 ItamarВҰ76277,\x + \xo 26:60: \xt Num 3:2.\x*
\v 61 \add вүҲbut\add* Nadav andВҰ76281 Avihu had diedВҰ76279 when they'd offeredВҰ76282 YahwehВҰ76287 \add вүҲfireВҰ76283 in a disobedient manner\add*.\x + \xo 26:61: \xt Lev 10:1-2; Num 3:4.\x*
\v 62 The maleВҰ76296 \add Levites\add* who were a monthВҰ76299 old or older came to 23,000, but they weren't \add вүҲincluded in the above nation-wide count\add* because they \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ76303 inheritВҰ76313 land in the same way as other tribes\add*.
\s1 Census summary
\p
\v 63 Those were the \add вүҲcensus results from when\add* MoshehВҰ76320 andВҰ76321 the priestВҰ76322 EleazarВҰ76321 counted the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76327\add* on the Moav plainsВҰ76329 \add вүҲon the east side of\add* the Yarden river opposite Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*.
\v 64 \add вүҲNone of the men on those lists were on the previous lists done\add* by MoshehВҰ76341 andВҰ76342 the priestВҰ76343 Aharon when they'd countedВҰ76340 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76348\add* in the SinaiВҰ76351 wildernessВҰ76350,
\v 65 because YahwehВҰ76356 had told them that they'd certainly die \add there\add* in the wildernessВҰ76360 until none of \add @those alive\add* were left other than Yefunneh'sВҰ76372 son Kalev \add (CalebВҰ76369)\add* and Nun'sВҰ76376 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*.
\c 27
\s1 Inheritances without sons
\rem /s1 The Daughters of Zelophehad; Zelophehad's Daughters
\p
\v 1 Then the daughters of Tselofehad (son of HeferВҰ76384, son of GileadВҰ76387, son of MakirВҰ76390, son of Menashsheh) approachedВҰ76379. \add *Their\add* namesВҰ76400 were MahlahВҰ76402, NoahВҰ76403, Milkah, and Tirtsah.
\v 2 They stoodВҰ76408 \add вүҲin frontВҰ76409 of\add* MoshehВҰ76410 and the priestВҰ76413 EleazarВҰ76412 and all the leadersВҰ76415 and the people \add there\add* at the entranceВҰ76419 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ76420\add* tent, \add and\add* \add вүҲasked\add*,
\v 3 вҖңOur fatherВҰ76425 died in the wildernessВҰ76427, \add вүҲalthough\add* he wasn't \add вүҲpart of the group who joined KorahВҰ76440 to rebel\add* against YahwehВҰ76437вҖ”it was \add вүҲfor his own personal disobedience\add* that he died. He didn'tВҰ76429 have any sonsВҰ76445
\v 4 \add but\add* why should his family nameВҰ76453 disappear from our clan \add just\add* because he had no sons? \add So\add* giveВҰ76462 us \add вүҲsome land like\add* our father'sВҰ76455 relatives will be getting.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ76470\add* MoshehВҰ76471 took their case to YahwehВҰ76477
\v 6 andВҰ76480 \add *he\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ76480\add*,
\v 7 вҖңIt's right what Tselofehad's daughtersВҰ76488 are saying. You must give them \add вүҲsome land like their father's relatives will be getting\add*. \add вүҲGive them whatever would have been given to their father as his\add* inheritance.
\v 8 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ76509,\add* tell the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ76508\add* that if a manВҰ76512 dies \add вүҲwithout sons\add*, thenВҰ76506 his inheritanceВҰ76522 should go to his daughter(s).
\v 9 If he had no \add вүҲchildren\add*, thenВҰ76525 \add вүҲit should go\add* to his brothersВҰ76534,
\v 10 and if he has no brothers, then \add вүҲit should go\add* to his father'sВҰ76547 brothers.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if his fatherВҰ76553 had no brothersВҰ76552, thenВҰ76549 the inheritanceВҰ76557 \add вүҲshould go to his nearestВҰ76559 blood-relative to become his possessionВҰ76562\add*. That will \add вүҲbecome a permanent regulation\add* for YisraelВҰ76566, just as YahwehВҰ76571 has commandedВҰ76570.вҖқ
\s1 Yehoshua succeeds Mosheh
\rem /s1 Joshua to Succeed Moses; Joshua Chosen to Lead Israel; Joshua Is Chosen as Successor to Moses; Joshua Appointed Moses' Successor
\r (Deu. 31:1-8)
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ76578 told MoshehВҰ76581 \add (MosesВҰ76581)\add*, вҖңGo up MtВҰ76585. Avarim and look at the land thatВҰ76592 I've givenВҰ76593 to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76594\add*,\x + \xo 27:12-14: \xt Deu 3:23-27; 32:48-52.\x*
\v 13 and thenВҰ76597 you'll \add вүҲdie and join your ancestors\add* just like your brotherВҰ76609 AharonВҰ76608 \add вүҲdid\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲThat's because back\add* in the Tsin wilderness when the \add вүҲpeople complained about water\add*, you two rebelledВҰ76612 againstВҰ76612 my \add вүҲcommandВҰ76613 and failed to respect my holinessВҰ76619\add* in front of them. That was \add when you struck the rock\add* at MeribahВҰ76625 \add near\add* KadeshВҰ76626 in the Tsin wilderness.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 Then MoshehВҰ76633 \add вүҲrequested\add* YahwehВҰ76636,
\v 16 вҖңYahwehВҰ76640, \add you\add* \add вүҲare the godВҰ76641 who directs the spiritsВҰ76642 of all humankind\add*, \add so please\add* appointВҰ76639 a \add вүҲnew leader for the Israeli people\add*
\v 17 who will \add вүҲstand in front of\add* them and lead them out and bringВҰ76661 them in \add вүҲso\add* \add *they\add* won'tВҰ76662 be like sheepВҰ76666 without a shepherdВҰ76671.\x + \xo 27:17: \xt 1Ki 22:17; Eze 34:5; Mat 9:36; Mrk 6:34.\x*
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ76673 YahwehВҰ76674 told MoshehВҰ76677, вҖңGet Nun'sВҰ76686 son Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*, a manВҰ76687 who has \add &my\add* spiritВҰ76690 in him, andВҰ76673 place yourВҰ76695 hands on him \add to indicate the transfer of leadership\add*.\x + \xo 27:18: \xt Exo 24:13.\x*
\v 19 Stand him in frontВҰ76700 of the priestВҰ76702 EleazarВҰ76701 and all the assembly, and \add вүҲcommissionВҰ76707 him as they watch\add*.
\v 20 GiveВҰ76720 him some of yourВҰ76712 authorityВҰ76712 so that all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ76719\add* peopleВҰ76719 can hearВҰ76715 \add <it\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲWhen\add* \add he needs guidance\add*, he must standВҰ76725 \add вүҲin frontВҰ76730\add* of the priestВҰ76724 EleazarВҰ76723 and ask for Yahweh's decisionВҰ76728 \add to be given via\add* the Urim. ThenВҰ76722 \add @Yehoshua\add* and all the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ76743\add* will goВҰ76735 in or comeВҰ76739 out as per \add @Yahweh's\add* \add вүҲinstructions\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 27:21: \xt Exo 28:30; 1Sam 14:41; 28:6.\x*
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ76751\add* MoshehВҰ76752 did what YahwehВҰ76755 had orderedВҰ76754 him to, and he \add вүҲpresented\add* YehoshuaВҰ76760 to the priestВҰ76764 EleazarВҰ76763 and to the entireВҰ76766 community.
\v 23 \add @Mosheh\add* placed his handsВҰ76773 on \add @Yehoshua\add* andВҰ76770 \add вүҲcommissionedВҰ76775\add* himВҰ76775, just has YahwehВҰ76778 had said \add *he\add* should.
\c 28
\s1 The daily offerings
\rem /s1 The Regular Offerings; The Daily Offerings; Daily Offerings
\r (Exo. 29:38-46)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ76785 told MoshehВҰ76788 \add (MosesВҰ76788)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңGive the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ76794\add* \add <these instructions\add*: Ensure that you presentВҰ76806 to me the offerings \add and\add* food for offerings to be burnt at the \add вүҲproper\add* timeВҰ76808.
\v 3 ForВҰ76816 the \add вүҲdaily\add* burntВҰ76824 offering, present twoВҰ76822 one-year-old, male lambsВҰ76817 thatВҰ76814 have noВҰ76821 defectsВҰ76821.
\v 4 One of those lambs must be offered in the morningВҰ76832, andВҰ76833 the other in \add вүҲlate afternoon\add*,
\v 5 \add each offeredВҰ76843\add* along with a kilogram of fine flourВҰ76842 mixedВҰ76844 with a litre of \add olive\add* oil.
\v 6 That's the regular burntВҰ76850 offering done like the first one at Mt. SinaiВҰ76854вҖ”the soothingВҰ76856 aromaВҰ76855 from the fireВҰ76857 will be pleasingВҰ76856 to YahwehВҰ76858.
\v 7 The drink offering must \add also\add* be one litre for each lamb. That strongВҰ76868 drink must be poured out in the sacred area as an offering to YahwehВҰ76869.
\v 8 \add вүҲAt the end of the afternoon,\add* offer the secondВҰ76873 lamb with the same-sized offerings of flour andВҰ76879 wine as in the morningВҰ76878. \add вүҲWhen they're burnt,\add* the aromaВҰ76882 will be pleasingВҰ76883 to YahwehВҰ76884.
\s1 The Rest Day offerings
\rem /s1 The Sabbath Offerings; The Sabbath Offering; Sabbath Offerings
\p
\v 9 вҖңOn the Rest Day, \add it must be\add* two one-year-old, male lambsВҰ76891 with noВҰ76895 defectsВҰ76895, along with 2 kilograms of fine flourВҰ76898 mixedВҰ76900 with oil, as well as the drinkВҰ76902 offering.
\v 10 That will be burnt every Rest Day, in addition to the regularВҰ76910 \add daily\add* burnt offering and its drinkВҰ76911 offering.
\s1 The new month offerings
\rem /s1 Monthly Offerings; The Monthly Offerings; The Offering on the First Day of the Month
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add вүҲOn the first day of each monthВҰ76915\add*, you all must bringВҰ76916 YahwehВҰ76918 a burntВҰ76917 offeringВҰ76917 of twoВҰ76923 young bullsВҰ76919, one ram, and sevenВҰ76930 one-year-old, male lambsВҰ76926 with noВҰ76931 defectsВҰ76931.
\v 12 Each bullВҰ76939 must be offered with threeВҰ76933 kilograms of fine flour mixed with oil, each ram with twoВҰ76941 kilograms,
\v 13 andВҰ76950 each lamb with one kilogram. \add All of that\add* will be a burntВҰ76958 offering with an aromaВҰ76959 that will be pleasingВҰ76960 to YahwehВҰ76962.
\v 14 Their \add respective\add* drinkВҰ76964 offerings will be two litres of wine with the bullВҰ76968, 1.3 litres with the ram, andВҰ76964 one litre with each lamb. That will be the burntВҰ76977 offering \add вүҲfor the start of each new\add* monthВҰ76980 throughoutВҰ76980 the yearВҰ76981.
\v 15 In addition to those burntВҰ76990 offerings andВҰ76993 drinkВҰ76993 offerings, a maleВҰ76983 goatВҰ76983 must \add also\add* be presented to YahwehВҰ76987 as a sinВҰ76986 offering.
\s1 The вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ offerings
\rem /s1 The Passover; Offerings for the Passover; The Offerings at the Festival of Unleavened Bread; Offerings at Passover
\r (Lev. 23:5-14)
\p
\v 16 вҖңYahweh's вҖҳpassoverВҰ77002вҖҷ \add ceremony will start\add* on the 14th of the firstВҰ76997 month \add (Nisan = March/April) each year\add*.\x + \xo 28:16: \xt Exo 12:1-13; Deu 16:1-2.\x*
\v 17 The 15th will be \add the start of\add* the celebrationвҖ”\add вүҲall your breadВҰ77013 must be made without any rising agent\add*.\x + \xo 28:17-25: \xt Exo 12:14-20; 23:15; 34:18; Deu 16:3-8.\x*
\v 18 That firstВҰ77017 day, there's to be a sacredВҰ77020 assemblyВҰ77018. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.
\v 19 YouВҰ77031 all must offer twoВҰ77036 \add вүҲyoung\add* bullsВҰ77032, one ram, andВҰ77028 sevenВҰ77039 one-year-old lambsВҰ77040 with noВҰ77043 defectsВҰ77043 to be burntВҰ77030 on the fireВҰ77029.
\v 20 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77047 offeringsВҰ77047 must be threeВҰ77051 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77048 mixedВҰ77049 with \add olive\add* for the bullВҰ77053, twoВҰ77054 kilograms for the ram,
\v 21 \add and\add* one kilogram for each of the sevenВҰ77064 lambsВҰ77065.
\v 22 \add вүҲAlso,\add* bring one maleВҰ77067 goatВҰ77067 as a sinВҰ77068 offeringВҰ77068 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*.
\v 23 Those offerings must be \em in additionВҰ77073\em* to the regularВҰ77078 morningВҰ77075 offerings
\v 24 \add and\add* must be offered for each of the sevenВҰ77087 daysВҰ77088. The aromaВҰ77091 of those burnt offerings will be pleasingВҰ77093 to YahwehВҰ77094, along with the regularВҰ77098 burnt offering and its drinkВҰ77100 offering.
\v 25 On the seventhВҰ77103 day, there's to be \add another\add* sacredВҰ77106 assemblyВҰ77104. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.
\s1 Harvest festival offerings
\rem /s1 The Offerings at the Harvest Festival; Offerings for the Festival of Harvest; Feast of Weeks; Offerings at the Festival of Weeks
\r (Lev. 23:15-22)
\p
\v 26 вҖңOn the firstfruitsВҰ77118 day of the harvest festival, when you all presentВҰ77119 an offeringВҰ77120 of fresh grainВҰ77120 to YahwehВҰ77122, there's to be a sacredВҰ77126 assemblyВҰ77124. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.\x + \xo 28:26-31: \xt Exo 23:16; 34:22; Deu 16:9-12.\x*
\v 27 You all must present a burntВҰ77137 offeringВҰ77137 that's a pleasingВҰ77139 aromaВҰ77138 for YahwehВҰ77140, \add presenting\add* twoВҰ77145 \add young\add* bullsВҰ77141, one ram, andВҰ77136 sevenВҰ77148 one-year-old male lambsВҰ77149.
\v 28 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77153 offeringsВҰ77153 will be threeВҰ77157 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77154 mixedВҰ77155 with \add olive\add* oil for each bullВҰ77159, twoВҰ77161 kilograms for the ram,
\v 29 and one kilogram for each of the lambs.
\v 30 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77173 goatВҰ77173 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*.
\v 31 Those offerings along with theirВҰ77188 drink offerings must be offered in additionВҰ77179 to the regularВҰ77181 burntВҰ77180 offering and drink offerings. Ensure that they have noВҰ77184 defectsВҰ77184.
\c 29
\s1 The trumpeting celebration
\rem /s1 Offerings at the Festival of Trumpets; The Offerings at the New Year Festival; Feast of Trumpets; Offerings for the Festival of Trumpets
\r (Lev. 23:23-25)
\p
\v 1 вҖңOn the firstВҰ77193 day of the seventhВҰ77192 month \add (Tishrei = September/October) each year\add*, there's to be a sacredВҰ77197 assemblyВҰ77195. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that dayвҖ”it'll be a day of blowingВҰ77207 horns.
\v 2 You all must present a \add вүҲyoung\add* bullВҰ77216, a ram, andВҰ77211 sevenВҰ77227 one-year-old lambsВҰ77223, \add all\add* with noВҰ77228 defectsВҰ77228 as a burntВҰ77212 offeringВҰ77211 to be a pleasingВҰ77214 aromaВҰ77213 for YahwehВҰ77215.
\v 3 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77230 offeringВҰ77230 will be threeВҰ77234 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77231 mixedВҰ77232 with \add olive\add* oil with the bullВҰ77236, twoВҰ77237 kilograms with the ram,
\v 4 andВҰ77241 one kilogram for each of the sevenВҰ77245 lambsВҰ77246.
\v 5 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77248 goatВҰ77248 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*.
\v 6 Those are in additionВҰ77256 to the monthly and regularВҰ77261 \add daily\add* burnt offerings with their \add associated\add* grain offerings and drinkВҰ77263 offerings. The aromaВҰ77265 of those burnt offerings will be pleasingВҰ77266 to YahwehВҰ77268.
\s1 The sacrifice for forgiveness
\rem /s1 Offerings for the Day of Atonement; The Offerings at the Day of Atonement; Offerings on the Day of Atonement; Day of Atonement
\r (Lev. 23:26-32)
\p
\v 7 вҖңEach year on the 10th of this seventhВҰ77273 monthВҰ77272 \add (Tishrei = September/October)\add*, there's to be a sacredВҰ77277 assemblyВҰ77275. \add вүҲDon't eat any food or do any regular workВҰ77286 on that day\add*.\x + \xo 29:7-11: \xt Lev 16:29-34.\x*
\v 8 You all must presentВҰ77290 a \add вүҲyoung\add* bullВҰ77295, a ram, andВҰ77290 sevenВҰ77306 one-year-old male lambsВҰ77302 as a burntВҰ77291 offeringВҰ77291 that will be a pleasingВҰ77294 aromaВҰ77293 for YahwehВҰ77292. Ensure that theyВҰ77308 have noВҰ77307 defectsВҰ77307.
\v 9 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77311 offeringsВҰ77311 will be threeВҰ77315 kilograms of fine flourВҰ77312 mixedВҰ77313 with \add olive\add* oil for the bullВҰ77317, twoВҰ77318 kilograms for the ram,
\v 10 and one kilogram for each of the sevenВҰ77327 lambsВҰ77328.
\v 11 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77330 goatВҰ77330, in additionВҰ77335 to the one to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add* and the regularВҰ77339 burntВҰ77338 offerings with theirВҰ77341 \add associated\add* grainВҰ77340 and drinkВҰ77341 offerings.
\s1 Offerings during the celebration in shelters
\rem /s1 Offerings at the Festival of Booths; The Offerings at the Festival of Shelters; Feast of Tabernacles; Offerings for the Festival of Shelters
\r (Lev. 23:33-44)
\p
\v 12 вҖңOn the 15th of that seventh monthВҰ77347, there's to be \add another\add* sacredВҰ77351 assemblyВҰ77349. No \add вүҲregular\add* workВҰ77356 may be done that dayВҰ77346 \add which will begin\add* sevenВҰ77363 daysВҰ77364 of celebrationВҰ77360.\x + \xo 29:12-38: \xt Lev 23:34; Deu 16:13-15.\x*
\v 13 вҖңYou all must presentВҰ77366 thirteen \add вүҲyoung\add* bullsВҰ77372, twoВҰ77379 rams, fourteen one-year-old male lambsВҰ77380 as a burntВҰ77367 offering that will be a pleasingВҰ77370 aromaВҰ77369 for YahwehВҰ77371. Ensure that theyВҰ77387 have noВҰ77386 defectsВҰ77386.
\v 14 Their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77389 offeringsВҰ77389 will be three kilograms of fine flourВҰ77390 mixedВҰ77391 with \add olive\add* oil for each bullВҰ77395, two kilograms for each ram,
\v 15 andВҰ77407 one kilogram for each of the seven lambsВҰ77414.
\v 16 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one male goat to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77421 to the regularВҰ77423 burntВҰ77422 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77424 andВҰ77425 drinkВҰ77425 offerings.
\p
\v 17 вҖңOn the secondВҰ77429 dayВҰ77428, you all must offer twelve \add вүҲyoung\add* bullsВҰ77430, two rams, fourteen one-year-old male lambsВҰ77438 withoutВҰ77444 defectsВҰ77444,
\v 18 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77446 and drinkВҰ77447 offeringsВҰ77446 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 19 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77454 goatВҰ77454 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77459 to the regularВҰ77461 burntВҰ77460 offerings with theirВҰ77463 \add associated\add* grainВҰ77462 andВҰ77454 drinkВҰ77463 offerings.
\p
\v 20 вҖңOn the thirdВҰ77467 dayВҰ77466, \add the sacrifice will be\add* eleven youngВҰ77468 bullsВҰ77468, twoВҰ77473 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77474 withoutВҰ77480 defectsВҰ77480,
\v 21 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77482 and drinkВҰ77483 offeringsВҰ77482 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 22 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77490 goatВҰ77490 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77493 to the regularВҰ77495 burntВҰ77494 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77496 andВҰ77490 drinkВҰ77497 offerings.
\p
\v 23 вҖңOn the fourth dayВҰ77500, \add the sacrifice will be\add* tenВҰ77503 youngВҰ77502 bullsВҰ77502, twoВҰ77505 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77506 withoutВҰ77512 defectsВҰ77512,
\v 24 and their \add associated\add* grain and drinkВҰ77515 offeringsВҰ77514 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 25 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77522 goatВҰ77522 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77527 to the regularВҰ77529 burntВҰ77528 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77530 andВҰ77531 drinkВҰ77531 offerings.
\p
\v 26 вҖңOn the fifthВҰ77535 dayВҰ77534, \add the sacrifice will be\add* nineВҰ77537 youngВҰ77536 bullsВҰ77536, twoВҰ77539 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77540 withoutВҰ77546 defectsВҰ77546,
\v 27 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77548 and drinkВҰ77549 offeringsВҰ77548 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 28 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77556 goatВҰ77556 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77559 to the regularВҰ77561 burntВҰ77560 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77562 andВҰ77556 drinkВҰ77563 offerings.
\p
\v 29 вҖңOn the sixthВҰ77567 dayВҰ77566, \add the sacrifice will be\add* eightВҰ77569 youngВҰ77568 bullsВҰ77568, twoВҰ77571 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77572 withoutВҰ77578 defectsВҰ77578,
\v 30 and their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77580 and drinkВҰ77581 offeringsВҰ77580 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 31 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77588 goatВҰ77588 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77591 to the regularВҰ77593 burntВҰ77592 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77594 andВҰ77595 drinkВҰ77595 offerings.
\p
\v 32 вҖңOn the seventh dayВҰ77598, \add the sacrifice will be\add* sevenВҰ77601 youngВҰ77600 bullsВҰ77600, twoВҰ77603 rams, fourteen year-old male lambsВҰ77604 withoutВҰ77610 defectsВҰ77610,
\v 33 and theirВҰ77618 \add associated\add* grainВҰ77612 and drinkВҰ77613 offeringsВҰ77612 \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 34 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77620 goatВҰ77620 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77623 to the regularВҰ77625 burntВҰ77624 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77626 andВҰ77627 drinkВҰ77627 offerings.
\p
\v 35 вҖңOn the eighthВҰ77631 \add and final\add* day, there's to be \add another\add* sacred assemblyВҰ77632. No \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done that day.
\v 36 You all must presentВҰ77642 a youngВҰ77648 bullВҰ77648, a ram, andВҰ77642 sevenВҰ77656 one-year-old male lambsВҰ77652, \add all\add* unblemishedВҰ77657, as a burntВҰ77643 offering that will be a pleasingВҰ77646 aromaВҰ77645 for YahwehВҰ77647.
\v 37 Their \add associated\add* grain and drinkВҰ77660 offeringsВҰ77659 must be \add вүҲas already stipulated\add*.
\v 38 \add Also\add* for your sins, sacrifice one maleВҰ77667 goatВҰ77667 to make \add вүҲyourselves right with God\add*, in additionВҰ77670 to the regularВҰ77672 burntВҰ77671 offerings with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ77673 andВҰ77667 drinkВҰ77674 offerings.
\p
\v 39 вҖң\add The above are the regulations for what\add* you all must do for YahwehВҰ77678 at the appointedВҰ77679 timesВҰ77679, in additionВҰ77680 to your vows and voluntary offerings, burntВҰ77683 offerings, grainВҰ77684 and drinkВҰ77685 offerings, and your peace offerings.вҖқ
\p
\v 40 \add вүҲSo\add* Moses passed on to the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* everything that Yahweh had instructed \add *him\add*.
\c 30
\s1 Instructions about vows
\rem /s1 Rules about Vows; Vows Made by Women; Vows; Laws concerning Vows
\p
\v 1 Then Mosheh \add (MosesВҰ77690)\add* \add вүҲgave\add* the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ77693 leaders\add* \add вүҲthese further instructions from\add* YahwehВҰ77699,
\v 2 вҖңIf a man makes a solemn promise to YahwehВҰ77719, or makes a binding vow on his own life, he mustn't dishonour \add вүҲwhat he said\add*вҖ”he must follow whatever came out of his mouth.\x + \xo 30:2: \xt Deu 23:21-23; Mat 5:33.\x*
\p
\v 3 If a \add вүҲyoung\add* woman who is \add вүҲstill living with her parents\add* solemnly promises to YahwehВҰ77727 \add <to do something\add*,
\v 4 and \add вүЎif\add* her fatherВҰ77756 hears her make the binding vow on her life and he remains silent, then her vow and \add вүҲall her obligationsВҰ77754\add* will stand.
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if her father forbids her \add вүҲwhen\add* he hearsВҰ77760 her, then thatВҰ77766 vow and \add вүҲits obligationsВҰ77780\add* won't stand, and Yahweh will forgive her, because her father \add вүҲstepped in\add*.
\p
